title: kielbasi bourbon hors d'oeuvres
directions: Mix ketchup, brown sugar and bourbon together and let simmer over medium heat together until it comes to a boil.
Turn heat down and simmer on low for 5 minutes.
Toss kielbasi into mixture and let simmer for an additional 15 minutes.
Serve with toothpicks.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Boil sugar, milk and salt in Dutch oven pan to soft ball stage.
Remove from burner.
Add peanut butter and mix.
Add jar of marshmallow.
Put in buttered dish and let set.

title: hamburger hot dish
directions: Brown the hamburger and place in buttered casserole. Add the peas, celery and onion. Thin the soup with the milk.
Pour over the ingredients.
Sprinkle the potato chips over top. Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: hot cocoa mix
directions: Store ingredients in a dry can with a tight cover.
To use, fill cup 1/2 full with mix.
Add boiling water.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix Crisco and sugar; add egg yolks, flour, baking powder, vanilla and egg whites.
Cut apples into thin wedges and put in batter on edge; sprinkle sugar and cinnamon over top with bits of butter.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: stuffed shells italiano(yield: 20 servings, 2 shells each)
directions: Cook pasta shells according to package directions.
Hold in cold water until ready to fill.
Combine garlic powder, salt, chicken bouillon and flour.
Add milk gradually; blend with wire whisk until smooth.
Bring to boil over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Stir in Mozzarella cheese.
Set aside 2 cups of sauce. Combine eggs, chicken, onion, mushrooms, pimento, spinach, Parmesan cheese and pepper.
Stir in 2 cups of reserved sauce.
Place #30 scoop (approximately 2 tablespoons) of filling into each shell. Place 20 shells in each 12 x 10 x 2-inch steamtable pan.
Spoon remaining sauce over shells.
Cover with foil and bake in preheated 350° oven for 35 to 40 minutes or until heated thoroughly.

title: yummy potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes in their skins in salted water.
Let cool.
Peel and shred into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Combine remaining ingredients and cover potatoes.
Bake 30 minutes in a 350° oven. Sprinkle with 1/2 cup grated cheese and 1/2 cup crushed corn flakes.
Bake 5 minutes more until cheese bubbles.

title: 4 layer dessert
directions: Layer 1:
Cream the margarine and flour.
Add the chopped walnuts.
Pat into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 20 minutes at 350° and cool.

title: memorial house chicken
directions: Combine soups with mayonnaise. Add onion, water chestnuts or celery and chicken.
If very thick, add 1/4 to 1/2 cup chicken broth. Bake at 375° for 40 to 45 minutes. About 10 minutes before it is done, spread bread cubes over mixture and then sprinkle cheese on top. Serves 6 to 8.

title: favorite dressing for salad
directions: *I use 1 tablespoon parsley, 1/2 teaspoon each:
chives, celery salt, paprika and garlic and salt and pepper.

title: rice casserole
directions: Mix together the rice and onion soup mix.
Add margarine in the water.
Cook at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Pour enough oil into pot to cover bottom.
Sprinkle in as much garlic salt as desired.
When oil is hot, add the rest of the ingredients.
Simmer sauce for 2 hours, stirring occasionally. After simmering for 2 hours, sprinkle in about 1/4 cup Romano cheese and simmer for another 30 minutes.
Pour over spaghetti.

title: persimmon pudding
directions: Mix persimmons, beaten eggs and milk together.
Sift dry ingredients together and pour liquid mixture into them.
Pour into shallow oiled pan to depth of 2-inches.
Bake 1 hour at 350° or until done.
When cool, cut into squares.

title: chicken and dressing casserole
directions: Remove bone from cooked chicken and break chicken into bite size pieces.
Layer in large deep dish casserole dish.
Heat soups and milk; season.
Then pour over chicken.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Combine flour, sugar, baking powder and salt; cut in shortening until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Gradually add milk, mixing with fork; shape into ball.
On lightly floured surface, roll out 2/3 of dough to fit a 10 x 6-inch baking dish. Line dish with pastry; flute edges.

title: chili relleno bake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Brown beef and onions; drain off grease. Season with salt and pepper.

title: butterscotch chewy cake
directions: Beat eggs with	rotary	beater	in top of double boiler just until blended.
Blend
in
brown sugar and butter.	Place over rapidly
boiling
water,
stirring	constantly
until hot (about 5 minutes).
Remove from heat.
Sift together flour and baking powder.
Add
all
at once to cooked mixture; mix until well blended.
Stir
in	chopped nuts.
Turn into well-greased and lightly floured 13	x
9-inch pan.	Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Serve with ice cream or whipped cream or sprinkle with sifted powdered sugar while still warm.

title: key lime pie
directions: Beat yolks of eggs until lemon color.
Add condensed milk and beat again lightly.
Add lime juice and beat until smooth.
Pour mixture into pastry shell.
Top with meringue.

title: king ranch chicken
directions: Boil chicken; chop in chunks.
Keep broth.
Dip tortillas in pint of warm broth.
Grease casserole dish and line with tortillas overlapping.
Layer ingredients in this order: chicken, onion, pepper, mushroom soup and chicken soup.
Cover with grated cheese. Be sure casserole is completely covered.
Then spread tomatoes (mash well so there are no lumps) over the cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
It
should not be juicy.

title: overnight potato bake
directions: Boil potatoes.
Mash with cream cheese and butter.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Refrigerate overnight in buttered casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: key lime pie
directions: Mix the condensed milk, lime juice and sour cream together. Make crust for pie using approximately 2 cups of cinnamon bear cookies.
Mix with margarine until well blended.
Press into a 9-inch pie plate.
Pour filling into crust; then refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: cherry cheesecake
directions: Place 1 wafer in bottom of each of 12 paper-lined muffin pan cups. Beat cream cheese, sugar and eggs in large bowl with electric mixer on medium until light and fluffy. Spoon filling into each cup, filling about 2/3 full. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Turn off oven. Open door slightly. Let cool in oven. Remove. Cool completely. Top with pie filling. Refrigerate 1 hour.

title: milky way cake
directions: Melt candy bars with 1 stick oleo.
In separate bowl, cream together sugar and 1 stick oleo.
Add alternately flour, baking soda and buttermilk to creamed mixture.
Mix well.
Stir in melted candy mixture.
Add nuts.
Pour mixture into a greased 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 10 minutes or until done.

title: zucchini squash
directions: Slice zucchini and saute in butter in skillet.
Debone chicken (amount to taste) and add squash.
Add stewed tomatoes.
Season as you like and eat over rice.

title: peanut butter candy balls
directions: Mix peanut butter, butter, sugar and Rice Krispies in a bowl. Roll well blended batter into balls and place on waxed paper covered cookie sheet.
Refrigerate until firm.

title: mandarin orange salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water. Add sherbet and juices.
Chill. Mash oranges and fold into jello.
Add crushed pineapple.
Chill until firm.
Top with sour cream and marshmallows, mixed together.

title: hamburger quiche pie
directions: Brown beef.
Drain grease on paper towel.
Add to other ingredients.
Pour into 2 unbaked 9-inch pie plates.
Bake at 325° for 15 minutes.
Turn to 350° and bake 20 to 30 minutes.

title: blueberry crunch
directions: Mix flour, brown sugar, and 1/4 cup
white sugar.
Spread in rectangular baking pan.
Melt butter and pour over flour and sugar mixture, stirring with a fork until completely moist.
Bake at 400 degrees, stirring every 5 minutes until golden brown (at least 20 minutes).
Remove from oven and stir in pecans.
Bake another 5 to 10 minutes to keep broken up.
Remove and let cool.

title: five cup salad
directions: Sprinkle orange jello over mandarin oranges, pineapple and cottage cheese.
Fold in prepared envelope of Dream Whip.

title: mini-pizzas
directions: Put Ritz crackers on a plate.
On each cracker, put one slice of pepperoni.
Sprinkle grated cheese on top of the pepperoni. Put in the microwave and heat on High for 35 seconds.

title: peach cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Generously grease two round (8 1/2-inch) pans.
Drain peaches.
Save syrup.
Add enough water to syrup to measure 1 1/4 cups liquid.
Prepare cake mix by package instructions, except use the syrup mixture instead of water called for.
Bake and cool.

title: sweet and sour chicken(it's time for a hawaiian delight!)
directions: In a small bowl, combine 1/2 cup water, cornstarch, brown sugar and salt.
Stir until mixture is smooth.
Combine with reserved pineapple juice and brown sugar mixture in a large saucepan.
Cook over medium heat about 5 to 7 minutes, until mixture starts to thicken.
Add Chicken Mix, soy sauce and vinegar.
Cover and simmer 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Put Chicken Broth and 2 cups water in a saucepan.
Add rice.
Cover and cook about 25 minutes. Add pineapple chunks, onion slices and green peppers to Chicken Mix mixture.
Cook until vegetables are slightly tender.
Just before serving, stir in tomato wedges.
Serve over the hot, cooked rice. Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: kolache
directions: Stir well.
Roll out dough, cut out with cookie cutter.
Make small indentation in the middle of kolache.
Put jelly or jam in the middle of the indentation.
Put on pan and bake for 10 minutes at 425°.

title: crab imperial
directions: Beat egg; blend in mayo.
Add seasonings and stir until blended.
Fold in green pepper, pimento and crab.
Bake at 350° until top is brown.
Serves 4.

title: hot dog sauce
directions: Brown onions and hamburger.
Add all other ingredients except cornstarch.
Let simmer for awhile, then add cornstarch mixture and cook until thick.
Makes 1 1/2 quarts.

title: hidden valley ranch cheese ball
directions: Mix Ranch and cream cheese.
Beat.
Add Cheddar and blend. Freeze 30 minutes.
Shape into ball and roll in almonds.

title: dill pickles
directions: Sterilize quart jars.
Fill jars with seasonings and cucumbers.
Add boiling liquid.
Seal jars.
Cold pack in canner for 20 minutes.

title: mini cheesecakes
directions: Line cupcake pan with paper cupcake holders.
Put vanilla wafer on bottom of each.
Blend remaining ingredients and fill cupcake holders 1/2 full.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Top with cherry pie filling or any other topping.

title: buried treasure
directions: Remove the grass and dirt it is growing in.
Save top put on top later.
Dig a hole 8-inches deep and 1 foot long and wide.
Put the dirt on the board or wheel barrow to protect the ground.
Drop your buried treasure in the hole.
Be easy.
Space the bulbs 4 to 6-inches apart with the points up.
Cover with dirt.
Replace the dirt and grass.
Wait.
The buried treasure will grow up to surprise you.

title: margaret's irish soda bread
directions: Prepare your favorite pancake batter.
Dip teaspoon into batter and let excess drain off.
Using the batter remaining on the spoon, draw any letters or numbers on the hot greased griddle.
Make the letters or numbers backwards.
When the underside is lightly browned, pour additional batter over the letters or numbers to form the pancake.
Make certain batter covers all of the letters or numbers.
Cook until bubbles appear; turn and brown second side. The letters or numbers will stand out being darker than the surrounding pancake.
(You can make animal pancakes in much this same way.)

title: cowboy chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix sugar, Crisco and eggs until creamy. Add flour, then stir in nuts, chocolate chips and oatmeal (will be stiff). Bake at 350° for 10 minutes or until brown. Yields 3 to 4 dozen.

title: rice ortega
directions: Saute onions in butter until light brown.
Add the cooked rice, jalapeno (if used), the cottage cheese, Longhorn cheese and crumbled bay leaf.
Alternate layers of rice mixture with strips of the chili peppers to form 4 layers in a greased casserole. Bake in a 375° oven for 25 minutes.
Top with 1/2 cup grated Longhorn cheese.
Bake for 10 minutes more.
Serves 10.

title: spoon bread
directions: Scald
cup
of
white
corn
meal with 1 1/2 cups of boiling water.
Cool for
hour.
Add
the well beaten eggs, milk, baking powder, salt
and
sugar.
In
baking dish, put 1 tablespoon of butter and melt in a 400° oven.
Remove dish and swish butter around sides
and bottom.
Add batter and bake at 400° for 45 minutes.

title: watergate salad
directions: Combine instant pistachio pudding mix, miniature marshmallows, chopped nuts and crushed pineapple.
Mix well.
Blend in Cool Whip.
Chill.

title: polly's refrigerator wheat rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1 cup warm water.
Pour other water over Crisco and sugar.
When cool to lukewarm, add yeast, eggs, salt and flour.
Put in greased bowl.
Place in refrigerator and use as needed.
Let rise until double, after cutting.
Bake at 400° until brown.

title: cheese balls
directions: Add sausage and Bisquick to cheese.
Mix well.
Form into small balls.
Bake at 400° for about 20 minutes.
Recipe may be doubled.

title: cranberry chutney
directions: In large saucepan, combine all ingredients except the ginger preserves.
Cook over moderate heat until the mixture thickens and the cranberries pop, 30 to 45 minutes.

title: night before french toast casserole
directions: Grease a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Arrange bread in pan.
Beat together eggs, milk, sugar, salt and vanilla.
Pour over bread evenly.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Before baking, uncover and dot the top with butter.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Cut into squares and serve immediately with warm maple syrup.

title: rock hen or quail italiano
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Mix the butter, rosemary, garlic and oregano.
Brush on hens; season to taste with salt and pepper. Add a few dashes of paprika and Parmesan cheese.
Wrap in foil; cook for 1 hour, or until done inside.
When meat is done, open foil to brown.
Serve with steamed rice.
Pour butter juices from hen over rice before serving.
(Can add chicken or beef bouillon to juice before adding to rice.)
Serve with chilled white Zinfandel wine.
Serves 2.

title: hot dog chili
directions: Brown hamburger.
Drain.
Add paste, juice, ketchup and sugar. Simmer for 30 minutes.
Freezes great!

title: holiday spinach and artichoke party dip
directions: Combine sour cream and party dip mix in medium bowl.
Stir in artichokes, spinach and pimientos.
Spray a 2-quart baking dish with Pam; spread mixture in pan.
Bake in preheated 400° oven for 20 to 25 minutes.
A big hit at any gathering!

title: layered cranberry mold
directions: Dissolve raspberry jello in boiling water; stir in 1 cup cold water.
Pour 1 1/2 cups of this mixture in 6-cup mold.
Chill until slightly firm.
Reserve remaining jello.
Do not chill. Beat 1/2 cup sugar and cream cheese until smooth.
Add evaporated milk slowly and vanilla.
Soften unflavored gelatin in remaining 1/4 cup cold water in small saucepan.
Heat until gelatin dissolves.
Blend into cream cheese.
Spoon over jello in mold. Chill until slightly firm.
Add remaining 1/2 cup sugar and cranberries to reserved raspberry jello.
Stir until blended. Pour over cheese layer.
Chill until firm; unmold.

title: tortillas
directions: Brown ground beef or chicken until done.
Add taco seasoning mix plus 1/2 cup water, refried beans and 1/2 bottle of salsa. Put in flour tortillas and top with cheese, plus remaining amount of salsa.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and place in a casserole dish. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour or until brown on top. When you can see butter bubble in the top, this will tell you it is not too dry.

title: pie pastry
directions: Combine the flour and salt in a large bowl.
Cut in the butter and shortening until the mixture resembles coarse meal.
Add the water, 1 tablespoon at a time, tossing until the dough forms a ball.
Add more than 1/3 cup water, if needed.

title: hodgepodge
directions: Brown ground beef and onions together and drain.
Mix together all remaining ingredients in large pot.
Add in beef and onion mixture and simmer covered for 15 to 20 minutes.
Serves 12 to 14.

title: chocolate crinkles
directions: Melt chocolate in double boiler.
Cool.
Sift flour, baking powder, and salt.
Mix oil, cooled chocolate, and sugar in bowl. Beat eggs in one at a time.
Add vanilla and sifted dry ingredients; mix well.
Fold in chocolate chips.
Chill, covered for 4 hours.
Preheat oven to 350.
Roll mixture by teaspoonfuls in powdered sugar.
Arrange on greased cookie sheet.
Bake for 9-11 minutes or until cookies test done.
Cool on cookie sheet for 5 minutes.
Remove to wire rack to cool completely.

title: vegetable medley
directions: Melt oleo.
Add rice, milk, cheese and vegetables.
Mix.
Pour in casserole (9 x 13-inch pan).
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: hawaiian venison
directions: Cut steaks in 1-inch cubes.
Flour and brown in hot margarine. Add water and salt.
Simmer until tender.
Cut peppers in 1-inch squares.
Boil 10 minutes and drain.
Add peppers and pineapple to meat.
Pour sauce over meat mixture.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Serve over Chinese noodles or rice.

title: white chocolate party mix
directions: Combine last 6 ingredients and mix well.
Melt chocolate in double boiler.
Pour over mix and spread on wax paper.
Let cool; break in pieces.
Store in tight container and refrigerate.

title: bean salad(oriole maggard)
directions: Toss lightly and chill.
Serve with slotted spoon.

title: sausage swirls
directions: Mix pastry ingredients (will be stiff).
Roll into 10 x 18-inch thin rectangles.
Spread sausage; roll from long side.
Chill. Slice and bake in preheated oven at 350° for 20 minutes or until golden brown.

title: baked ham with pineapple
directions: Remove and discard casing from ham.
Score top of ham in a diamond design and stud with cloves.
Place ham in a shallow baking dish.
Arrange pineapple slices over top.
Pour ginger ale over ham and evenly sprinkle each pineapple slice with cinnamon. Bake ham at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes or until thoroughly heated. Cut into 12 slices and serve.
Yields 12 servings (1 slice each). Calories:
Exchanges:
2 medium-fat meat.

title: vanilla lemon nutmeg sauce
directions: Mix first 2 ingredients in saucepan.
Add boiling water; boil 1 minute.
Add rest of ingredients as wanted.
Good on plain cake or gingerbread.

title: meat loaf parmesan
directions: Combine cracker crumbs and milk.
Add meat, egg, Worcestershire sauce, salt, cheese, green pepper, onion and garlic salt.
Mix thoroughly.
Pack into 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Bake in a slow oven (325°) for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: low-fat orange dream cheesecake
directions: Sprinkle crumbs on bottom of 8 or 9-inch spring-form pan (or 9-inch pie plate sprayed with Pam).
Stir boiling water into Jell-O until completely dissolved.
Cool 5 minutes.
Pour into blender. Add cheeses; cover.
Blend at medium speed until well blended. Scrape down sides occasionally.
Pour into large bowl.
Add whipped topping.
Stir gently until blended.
Pour into pan.
Smooth top. Refrigerate 4 hours.
Store in refrigerator.
Makes 8 servings.

title: marshmallow pie
directions: Prepare pie filling with 1/2 cup sugar and egg yolks by package directions.
Prepare meringue with egg whites and remaining sugar.
Fold
meringue and marshmallows into pie filling.
Pour into pie shell.
Chill until firm.

title: chicken and brown rice
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Put chicken on top and pour dry onion soup mix over top.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 2 hours.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: wild turkey casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.

title: philly cheese ball
directions: Combine cheese, softened cream cheese food and 2 tablespoons oleo.
Mix until well blended.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Mold into preferred shape.
Chill.

title: spice dream cake
directions: Blend all ingredients in a large bowl, then beat at medium speed for 2 minutes.
Bake in a greased and floured 10-inch tube pan at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes, until center springs back when touched lightly.
Cool right side up for about 25 to 30 minutes, then remove from pan.

title: cucumber relish
directions: Mix cucumbers, onions and mangos; ground fine.
Add 1/2 cup salt.
Let stand overnight.
Squeeze out with hand; add sugar, vinegar and celery seed.
Simmer 1 hour.
Can in hot jars.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients together. Slowly add enough buttermilk, mixing well, until dough is of right consistency to hold it's shape when rolled into a ball.
Drop in a couple of inches of hot grease and deep fry until brown and crispy. Drain on paper. Serve hot.

title: letourneau candy
directions: Mix together and stir carefully sugar, cream of tartar, salt and 1 cup of cream.
Wipe sides of bowl so no sugar sticks to sides.
Cook mixture on medium heat, stirring until it forms a soft ball when dropped into cold water or 238°.
Slowly add second cup of cream to mixture as it continues to boil.
Cook until it forms a soft ball again when dropped in cold water.
Slowly add the Karo and continue cooking until soft ball stage.
Slowly add the third cup of cream and continue boiling until it forms a hard ball when dropped into cold water or 248°.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Pour into well buttered pan.
Do not scrape bowl.
Have a buttered dish set aside to pour scrapings into.
When mixture is cool and well set, turn it out on a cutting board and cut in small squares.
Wrap each piece in waxed paper.
Do not let it set too long or it will be difficult to cut.

title: cheese soup
directions: Saute onion in butter until golden.
Sprinkle with flour; add salt and pepper.
Stir and cook about 3 minutes.
Add hot milk slowly, stirring constantly.
Add cheese and stir until it melts. Simmer, covered, about 15 minutes.
Add tomato sauce and Tabasco sauce, then simmer 10 minutes.

title: saucy broccoli topper
directions: In 2-quart saucepan, combine soup, cheese, mustard and pepper. Over low heat, heat until cheese is melted.
Stir often.
Add broccoli.
Heat through.
Stir often.
Serve over potatoes.

title: chicken-rice casserole
directions: Place 1 cup uncooked rice in bottom of greased casserole dish. Lay pieces of fryer chicken on top of rice.
Sprinkle with 1 package onion soup mix.
Combine 1 can cream of chicken soup, with milk and salt and pepper.
Pour over chicken.
Bake at 300° for 2 1/4 hours.
Cover with foil for first part of baking.

title: hawaiian chicken
directions: Drain pineapple; mix juice, brown sugar and Worcestershire to make marinade.
Place chicken pieces in 13 x 9-inch glass baking pan; pour marinade over chicken and let stand 3 to 4 hours, turning chicken occasionally.
Remove about 1/2 to 3/4 cup marinade.
Bake in oven at 350° about 1 hour, basting often.
Turn oven to 375°; add pineapple chunks and bake 7 to 10 minutes until chunks are glazed.
Add toasted almonds.
Serve over rice.

title: yams and apples
directions: Peel potatoes and apples. Slice thin. In a large pot, heat 1/4 cup water to boiling. Add potatoes and simmer for about 5 minutes. Add apples, butter, vanilla and cinnamon. Cook over low heat for about 5 minutes. Add syrup and cook until tender. Makes about 6 to 8 servings.

title: pineapple "philly" pie
directions: Blend 1/3 cup sugar with cornstarch; add pineapple.
Cook, stirring constantly, until mixture is thick and clear.
Cool. Place the cream cheese in a bowl and cream it until soft and smooth.
Slowly blend in 1/2 cup sugar and salt.
Add eggs, stirring well after each egg is added.
Blend in milk and vanilla. Spread cooled pineapple mixture over bottom of pie crust.
Pour in cream cheese mixture and sprinkle with chopped pecans.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes, then reduce to 325° for additional 50 minutes.
Cool before serving.

title: banana split cake
directions: Blend graham crackers and butter and press into pan.
Mix confectioners sugar, margarine, eggs and vanilla together and beat mixture for 5 minutes.
Spread over crust and chill overnight. Slice 3 or 4 bananas lengthwise.
Drain 1 medium can of crushed pineapple and spread pineapple over the bananas.
Spread Cool Whip over the bananas and pineapple.
Top with nuts and cherries and refrigerate.

title: banana nut bars
directions: Blend in a large bowl the margarine, sugars, eggs, vanilla and bananas.
Sift together flour, soda, salt, cinnamon and nutmeg. Add flour mixture alternately with mashed bananas, raw oats, raisins and walnuts.
Bake in a well greased pan at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes and cut into squares.

title: open jar dill pickles
directions: These ingredients do not need to be boiled.
Put sliced cukes into one
quart
canning
jar.
Pour
the rest of the ingredients into the jar after mixing them in a separate bowl. Put cap on and
let stand on counter for 3 to 4 days.
Refrigerate. They should
be
ready to eat.
You will find they are delicious.

title: monster cookies
directions: Blend together sugar, peanut butter, butter, eggs, baking soda, syrup and salt; mix well.
Add oatmeal, chips, M&M's and nuts.
Mix well.
Use ice cream scoop or large spoon to shape cookies.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.
Do not overbake!

title: chili dip
directions: Combine chili and cream cheese in medium saucepan.
Cook until cheese melts, stirring occasionally.
Stir in salsa and drained olives.
Serve warm with chips.
Yield: 3 cups.

title: cream cheese bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Beat together the cream cheese, egg, sugar and vanilla until smooth. Line bottom (not sides) of pan with 1 package of crescent roll dough.
Pour in cream cheese mixture.
Cover mixture with other package of dough.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Allow to cool before serving.
Also good after being refrigerated.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Cover chicken well; salt and cook until tender. Stand in broth to cool. Then remove and debone. Save broth. Saute peppers in butter on low heat. Add chicken to water (broth) and cook. Add cheese and stir until melted. Add onions, peppers, tomatoes, peas, chopped chicken, olives and pimentos. Mix well. Makes 2 large 13 x 9 casseroles. Bake until heated. Freezes well.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix ingredients.
Put zucchini in last.
Grease and flour 2 loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken and shred.
Place in casserole dish.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Mix soup, sour cream, broth and dash of lemon juice together.
Pour over chicken.
Crumble crackers and mix with melted margarine.
Place on top of casserole and bake for 30 to 45 minutes in 350° oven.

title: deviled eggs
directions: Cut eggs in half lengthwise. Slip out yolks and mash with fork. Mix in mayonnaise, mustard, salt and pepper. Fill egg whites with yolk mixture. Cover and refrigerate up to 24 hours.

title: banana shake
directions: In blender container, combine all ingredients except ice; blend well.
Gradually add ice, blending until smooth.
Garnish as desired.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: janet's oven beef casserole
directions: *If no mushrooms, use cream of mushroom soup.

title: banana muffins
directions: Bake approximately 30 minutes at 350°.

title: fruit and nut rice casserole
directions: Prepare rice according to package directions (substitute chicken broth for water and omit butter).
Preheat oven to 350°. In a large skillet, melt 1 tablespoon butter over medium heat. Add cashews; cook for 2 minutes.
Remove from skillet.
Add celery and carrots; saute for 5 minutes in remaining butter.
Remove from heat.
Stir in rice, cashews and remaining ingredients.
Spoon into a greased 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Loosely cover with foil. Bake for 30 minutes in preheated oven.
Makes 6 servings.

title: beef barbecue
directions: Put brisket in roasting pan.
Add remaining ingredients to beef.
Bake at 275° for 5 to 6 hours.
Reserve 1 cup juice.
Let meat cool and refrigerate.

title: lemon bars
directions: Pat into an 8 x 8-inch pan and bake for 20 minutes at 350°. (I usually melt the butter in the oven, then mix with a fork.)

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix sugar and cornstarch together.
Add 7-Up.
Cook until it comes to a boil.
Cook on low until clear.
Keep stirring; add jello.
Pour over strawberries that have been placed in the pie shells.
Top with Cool Whip and chill.
Makes two pies.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs; add oil, sugar, vanilla and grated zucchini and beat again.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Add to batter and beat until smooth.
Fold in nuts and coconut (reserving 1/2 cup to sprinkle over batter).
Pour batter into 2 greased loaf pans and sprinkle with remaining coconut.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: hamburger corn pone pie
directions: Cook together ground beef, onion and oil until done.
Add chili powder, salt, Worcestershire sauce, tomatoes, kidney beans and corn bread batter on top.
Bake at 425° for 20 minutes.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Mix all together.
Put into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Keep frozen.

title: zucchini and parmesan casserole
directions: Mix zucchini, tomato, green pepper and onion in a buttered casserole dish.
In separate bowl, mix flour, salt, pepper and Parmesan cheese.
Pour over vegetables; mix well and dot with butter.
Cube Velveeta over top.
Bake covered at 350° for 1 hour.

title: connie's chicken casserole
directions: Boil breasts 1/2 hour, then dice.
Saute vegetables in butter. Cook noodles.
Throw in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Spray large baking dish with spray oil.
Put uncooked rice in bottom of dish (you may want to use more rice).
Pour chicken soup and 1 can liquid (water or milk) over rice.
Place the deboned chicken on top.
Place mushrooms over chicken, then mushroom soup. Cover with foil and bake at 350° until chicken is tender.

title: cathedral window cookies
directions: Place marshmallows and nuts in a large bowl; set aside. In a saucepan, melt chocolate chips and butter over medium-low heat. Pour over marshmallow mixture and mix well. Cover and refrigerate for 1 hour, stirring occasionally. Shape marshmallow mixture into a 12-inch roll; wrap in wax paper. Refrigerate up to 4 hours or until firm. Unwrap and cut into 3/8-inch slices; cut slices in half. Yields 4 1/2 dozen.

title: monkey bread
directions: Warm butter and 1 cup sugar together in a saucepan.
Cut biscuits into quarters.
Shake each piece in a Ziploc Baggie with 1 1/2 cups sugar and 2 tablespoons cinnamon.
Line Bundt pan with a layer of biscuits.
Pour some of the butter mixture over top; sprinkle with nuts.
Put another layer of biscuits, more butter mixture and nuts.
Keep doing until all biscuits and butter mixture are gone.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Let cool, inverted onto plate.
Pull apart with fingers to eat.
Makes 12 servings.

title: mushroom beef roast
directions: Sprinkle roast
with
salt,
pepper and garlic powder to suit taste; brown
in oil or shortening and drain.
Add desired amount of onions,
soup
and beef stock; cover and simmer until tender, 3 to 4 hours.

title: marinated steak
directions: Mix together the wine, sherry, soy sauce and seasonings. Place the steak in a long glass baking dish and pour the marinade over the meat.
Cover and chill at least 12 to 18 hours, turning meat once or twice.

title: b & k coney sauce
directions: Mix all the ingredients together and simmer 1 hour after it starts to cook.
Can be frozen.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix sugar, oil and eggs.
Mix well.
Combine flour, salt, soda, spices and flavorings.
Add nuts, coconut and apples.
Mix well.
(Important to mix well.)
Pour in greased and floured tube pan. Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: italian crescent casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In large skillet, brown beef and onion; drain.
Stir in spaghetti sauce.
Heat through.

title: black bottom cupcakes
directions: Blend together, then set aside the cream cheese, 1/3 cup sugar, egg, 1/8 teaspoon salt and chocolate chips.
Mix in separate bowl the flour, cocoa, 1 cup sugar, baking soda and 1/2 teaspoon salt. To this, add water, oil, vanilla and vinegar; mix well.
Fill paper liners 1/3 full with chocolate mixture.
Spoon heaping teaspoonful cream cheese mixture on top.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: german potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes until soft.
Let cool.
Add all the other ingredients.
Mix well and chill before serving.

title: custard pie
directions: Beat eggs in large bowl.
Add sugar, salt, vanilla, nutmeg and milk and mix well.
Pour in unbaked pie crust.
Preheat oven to 425° and bake about 30 minutes or until a knife in center comes out clean.

title: nana's coffee cake
directions: Cream the margarine with the sugar.
Add eggs and sour cream. Add flour, baking powder, baking soda, vanilla and lemon juice and mix thoroughly.

title: cowboy cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, and vanilla; beat.
Gradually add flour, soda and salt. Stir in oatmeal, pecans and chocolate chips.
Drop by spoon on well-greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: franya's corn and potato soup
directions: Mix soup with corn using the corn's liquid to dilute soup. Add green onion and pepper to taste; heat.
Serve topped with bacon bits.

title: pina colada fruit dip
directions: Combine all ingredients in blender.
Blend 30 seconds. Refrigerate several hours or overnight.
Serve with fresh fruit.

title: cream cheese ball
directions: Form in ball; put in freezer 15 to 20 minutes.
Roll in chipped beef (chopped).
Very good.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix together in a large bowl shortening, brown sugar, white sugar, vanilla and eggs.
Add flour, soda and salt in with the rest.
Bake at 375°.

title: barbecue hamburgers
directions: Melt shortening in skillet.
Add onion.
Cook a few minutes. Add browned ground beef. Mix well.
Add all other ingredients. Cook well.

title: chicken breasts
directions: Thoroughly mix chicken and celery soup with rice.
Spread on bottom of a large casserole.
Place chicken breasts (unseasoned) on top.
Sprinkle with dry onion soup over chicken.
Cover very tightly with heavy foil.
Bake at 325° for 2 hours.
Delicious!

title: deviled ham quiche
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Spread deviled ham on the bottom of the pastry shell.
Sprinkle cheese and onion on top of ham. In
a bowl, lightly beat eggs; beat in cream, salt and nutmeg. Mix thoroughly.
Pour
mixture
into pastry shell over cheese and onion.
Sprinkle
with paprika.
Bake 15 minutes.
Reduce oven temperature to 300° and bake 30 minutes longer, or until knife inserted
into
center
comes
out clean.
Let stand 10 minutes before cutting.
Makes 8 to 10 appetizer servings.

title: slush punch
directions: Mix all but pop.
Freeze thoroughly in large Tupperware container.
Remove from freezer 1/2 hour before serving.
Scoop or scrape into punch bowl as much as desired.
Pour pop over and slightly mash with potato masher.
Serve thick or thin.
Add pop and scoop mixture as needed.
Keeps in freezer for a few months. Just use leftovers as desired.

title: onion corn bread
directions: Mix well
and
pour
into a well greased pan (or muffin tins). Bake at 400° about 30 minutes or until brown on top.

title: hamburger soup
directions: Brown ground beef with onion.
Add remaining ingredients, except tomato juice.
Bring to a boil.
Cover and simmer for 20 minutes.
Add tomato juice; bring to a boil.
Cover and simmer for 1 hour.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Bring onions to boil in 1 cup water.
Add chili sauce, ketchup and brown sugar and mix.
Drop in meatballs.
Cook for 1 hour.

title: great grapes
directions: Give each child a cone to fill with grapes.

title: summer dessert
directions: Bake cake in an 8 x 9-inch pan according to directions.
Let cool.
Mix pudding.
Spread pudding on top of cake in the pan. Spread pineapple on top of pudding.
Cover with Cool Whip, if desired.

title: bonbon candy
directions: Mix butter, sugar, milk, coconut and pecans together. Let set 2 hours, then roll into balls.

title: dad's mexican casserole
directions: In a large skillet, brown meat and onion.
Add all other ingredients, except cheese and chips, in 2 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Layer meat mixture and Doritos, repeating until meat is all gone.
Top with Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 350° until cheese is all melted.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: After chicken is cooked, reserve broth for cooking spaghetti. Do not drain.
Saute onion, bell pepper and mushrooms in margarine or butter.
Add to spaghetti along with deboned chicken, Ro-Tel tomatoes and cheese.
(Cheese should be grated or cut in small pieces.)
Mix thoroughly and place in casserole dish.
Cook for an hour at 350°.
Let set a few minutes before serving.

title: pound cake
directions: Mix all ingredients, adding milk and flour last.
Pour into greased and floured pan. Put into cold oven.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: pina colada cake
directions: Cream oleo and sugar; add eggs one at a time.
Stir in buttermilk and cake mix.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake according to cake mix box directions.
When done and still hot, punch holes in the top.
Pour Eagle Brand milk over the top. When cool, pour coconut cream over the cake and top with Cool Whip.
Store in refrigerator until serving time.

title: chicken-n-dumplings
directions: Place chopped onion, celery and carrots in large stock pot. Add cut up chicken and bouillon cubes.
Cover with water.
Cook until chicken falls off the bone.
Remove bones.
Bring broth to boil and add the Bisquick dumplings.
Cover and cook for about 10 minutes.
(Note:
This recipe calls for grated carrots, but we like them better sliced or chopped.)
Serves 6.

title: green chili enchiladas
directions: Brown meat.
In a saucepan, mix soup, green chilies, onions and cheese.
After mixture is hot add browned meat.
Layer casserole dish with tortillas and pour mixture over them.

title: broccoli and cheese casserole
directions: Prepare Minute rice and set aside.
Cook slightly the frozen broccoli and drain; melt Velveeta, butter and onion over low heat. Mix broccoli, rice, cheese and cream of mushroom soup and bake at 350° for one hour.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Many women like to make up enough dry mix for several pies. Use these amounts, depending on how much mix you wish to keep on hand.

title: apple crunch
directions: Put in 9 x 11-inch buttered baking dish the apples, sugar and cinnamon.
Mix remaining ingredients together.
Sprinkle over apples.
Work in 1/3 cup butter.
Press lightly over sliced apples. Bake at 350° until apples are done and topping is golden brown.

title: mary's old fashioned corn bread
directions: First, heat oven to 450°.
Grease generously 12 medium muffin cups.
Then beat eggs until fluffy.
After that, mix in the other ingredients until smooth.
Pour batter into hot pans until almost full.
Bake muffins for 15 to 20 minutes.
Serve piping hot. Makes 12 servings.

title: raspberry-topped lemon pie
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In small saucepan, combine raspberries and cornstarch; cook and stir until thickened and clear.
In medium bowl, beat egg yolks with sweetened condensed milk, lemon juice and food coloring if desired.
Pour into crust; bake 30 minutes.
Spoon raspberry mixture evenly over top.
Chill 4 hours or until set. Spread with whipped cream.
Garnish as desired.
Refrigerate leftovers.
Makes 1 pie.

title: pot pie dough
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Roll out dough on floured surface.
Cut into squares.
Drop squares into prepared broth and cook 20 minutes.

title: easy lemon pie
directions: Mix all but last ingredient together.
Pour into graham cracker crust.
Chill.

title: hot chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except the soup and potato chips.
Place in a 2-quart casserole.
Pour soup over top without mixing.
Top with crushed potato chips.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all ingredients and roll in balls.
Place on cookie sheet. Bake at 300° to 350° for about 30 minutes.
These can be frozen.

title: hoska
directions: Scald milk.
Stir in sugar, salt, oleo and vanilla.
Cool to lukewarm.
Put warm water into warm bowl and add yeast.
Stir until dissolved.
Stir in lukewarm milk mixture, 2 eggs and 3 cups flour. Beat until smooth.
Add enough flour to make a soft dough.
Turn out onto lightly floured board.
Knead until smooth and elastic (about 10 minutes).
Place in greased bowl, turning to grease top. Cover and let rise in a warm place until double in size (1 hour). Punch down.
Turn out onto lightly floured board.
Knead in raisins until well distributed.
Bake as a loaf or form a braid.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes.
Brush with melted butter.

title: no fail meringue
directions: Cook 2 tablespoons of sugar, cornstarch and water until clear. Cool and set aside.
Beat egg whites, adding remaining 5 tablespoons of sugar gradually.
Add salt and cooled cornstarch mixture to egg whites and beat well.
Bake at 350 degrees for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: dorito casserole
directions: Brown beef
and
drain;
add
soup
and Ro-Tel and stir well. Add
beans and heat to boiling.
Place Doritos in large casserole; cover
with beef mixture and top with cheese.
Bake at 350° until cheese melts, about 15 minutes.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Combine first five ingredients in a large mixing bowl.
Set aside.
In another bowl combine buttermilk and eggs.
Add corn and remaining ingredients.
Pour over dry ingredients and stir until blended.
Do not overmix.
Pour batter into a greased 8-inch square baking dish or pan.
Bake at 400° for 35 minutes or until bread tests done.
Cool 5 minutes before cutting into squares.

title: russian tea cakes
directions: Cream the butter in a large mixing bowl.
Gradually add 1/2 cup sugar, beating until light and fluffy.
Stir in vanilla. Combine flour, salt and pecans; gradually add to creamed mixture, blending well.
Chill until firm.
Shape dough into 1-inch balls. Place 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes, or until edges are lightly browned.
Roll in additional powdered sugar while warm.
Cool on wire racks.
Roll again in powdered sugar.
Yields about 4 dozen.

title: yummy cake
directions: Mix and pour 1/2 of batter into tube pan.
Pat 1/2 cup chocolate chips, 1/2 cup nuts and miniature marshmallows on top of batter.
Add remaining batter.
Put on top of the batter 1/2 cup chocolate chips and 1/2 cup nuts.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: mexican goulash
directions: Brown meat and saute onion.
Add remaining ingredients; simmer for 1 hour.

title: 7-layer salad
directions: Layer lettuce, green pepper, onion, celery, peas and cheese. Mix sour cream, mayonnaise and sugar.
Pour over all layers. Crumble bacon on top.

title: tiny pecan tarts
directions: Combine cream cheese and butter; blend in flour.
Chill about 1 hour.
Shape into balls about 1-inch in diameter.
Press into lightly greased or sprayed tart pan or mini muffin pan.

title: lasagna
directions: Cook noodles.
Brown hamburger; drain.
Add spaghetti sauce. Layer ingredients in 9 x 13-inch pan, starting with small layer of sauce, then noodles, then cheese, then sauce, ending in cheese on top.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes or until cheese is melted on top.

title: cheese cake
directions: Make jello with boiling water and lemon juice.
Cream the cheese and sugar; mix with jello mixture.
Put your mixer bowl in freezer with Pet milk in it until ice forms around bowl.
Beat until stiff peaks, then fold into the lemon mixture.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Layer lettuce, onion and bacon in order.
Layer cauliflower on top.
Spread sugar, mayo, Parmesan cheese and salt and pepper over the top.
Cover tightly and chill overnight.
Toss just before serving.

title: german heaven and earth
directions: Boil potatoes in water for 10 minutes.
Add apples and boil until tender.
Drain and mash mixture.
Add sugar and lemon juice. Add butter, spices and mix well.
Cook bacon and crumble; set aside.
Saute onion.
Mix onion with bacon and sprinkle over mixture.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: creamed tacos
directions: Combine ground meat, tomatoes and chili beans, mixing well. Add brick chili, whipping cream and cheese.
Heat until cheese is melted.
Pour over Doritos chips.

title: chocolate marshmallow cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add egg, milk and vanilla; mix well. Combine flour, cocoa, baking soda and salt.
Beat into creamed mixture.
Drop by rounded teaspoonful onto ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° for 8 minutes.

title: apple crisp
directions: Mix together the first 4 ingredients; place in a greased 8-inch pan.
Mix together the next 3 ingredients; sprinkle over apple mixture.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes.

title: mexican tortilla soup
directions: Cut raw kernels off corn cob with a sharp knife.
In a large saucepan, melt the butter over moderate heat.
Add the garlic, onion, celery, corn, carrots and chili and cook for 3 minutes, stirring occasionally, until the onion is translucent.
Stir in the cumin, chili powder and oregano and continue stirring another minute to toast the spices.
Add the tomatoes, stock, cilantro and chicken.
Bring mixture to a boil and simmer for 10 minutes. Season with salt and pepper.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into greased skillet.
Bake at 375° for approximately 25 minutes or until golden brown.

title: white brownies
directions: Sift and set aside flour, baking powder and salt.
Melt shortening in pan.
Stir in brown sugar and allow to cool slightly. Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Add flour mixture, nuts and chocolate chips.
Pour into greased or wax paper lined cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Keep in an airtight container.

title: pistachio pineapple salad
directions: Pour pineapple and juice into bowl.
Add the mix and blend well.
Fold in Cool Whip and nuts.
Read to eat in 5 minutes.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Stir together margarine and peanut butter.
Gradually add sugar until combined.
Roll into 1 inch balls and place on waxed paper. Let dry about 20 minutes.
Melt almond bark or confectioners coating.
Let cool slightly.
Dip balls and let excess coating drip off.
Place on waxed paper until coating is dry.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Cut peppers in half lengthwise.
Remove seed and scald slightly.
Combine beef, rice, egg, onion, salt, pepper and 1/4 can tomato sauce.
Pile meat mixture lightly into pepper halves. Place in large baking dish.
Top each pepper with rest of tomato sauce.
Add 1/4 cup water in bottom of pan.
Cover dish tightly. Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours or until peppers are tender.
Baste occasionally.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and drain.
Butter casserole.
Add all ingredients together; mix all and bake 1 hour at 350°.
Sprinkle top with bread crumbs before baking.

title: butterscotch (or chocolate) crunchies
directions: 1. Place chips in a medium, microwave-safe bowl. Cover and microwave on medium for 3-1/2 to 5-1/2 minutes, until chips are melted. Stir until smooth (or melt using a double boiler).

title: dirt cake
directions: Cream confectioners sugar and cream cheese in mixer bowl until light and fluffy.
Add pudding mix and milk.
Beat until smooth. Fold in whipped topping.
Sprinkle half the crushed cookies into clean decorative flower pot.
Spoon in cream cheese mixture. Sprinkle remaining crushed cookies over top to resemble "dirt". Chill until serving time.
Place silk flowers in mixture to resemble potted plant.
Yield:
15 servings.

title: apple cake(diabetic)
directions: Blend all ingredients. Bake at 350° in greased tube pan for 1 hour.

title: speedy little devils
directions: Combine melted butter and dry cake mix.
Reserve 1 1/2 cups of this topping for top crust.
Pat remaining crumb mixture into a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Top layer with combined peanut butter and Marshmallow Creme.
Spread evenly.
Crumble remaining mixture over that.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Cool.
Makes 3 dozen bars.

title: lemon bars
directions: Stir together cake mix and pie filling (do not use electric mixer) and pour into ungreased jelly roll pan (10 x 15-inch pan). Bake in 350° oven for 20 to 25 minutes.
When cool, frost with powdered sugar frosting.
These bars freeze well.

title: witch's brew(hot cinnamon-apple punch)
directions: In a large electric percolator (24 to 30 cups), combine cider, sugar, orange juice and water.
In basket (where you usually put the coffee), add cinnamon sticks, allspice and cloves.
Plug in coffee maker and let it complete regular cycle.
Serve!

title: yum yum pudding
directions: Mix instant pudding as directed on box and set aside. Crush or break cookies in small pieces and layer in large bowl as follows: cookies, pudding, Cool Whip and mini chips. Repeat layering, ending with Cool Whip on top and sprinkles of mini chips.

title: jello pudding pecan pie
directions: Blend pudding and corn syrup.
Gradually add milk and egg, blending well.
Add pecans.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° until firm and top cracks, about 40 to 45 minutes.
Cool at least 3 hours.
Serve with Cool Whip, if desired.

title: devil's food cake
directions: Sift together first 4 ingredients.

Mix cocoa and hot coffee; set aside.	Cream Crisco and sugar; add eggs, slightly beaten. Add flour mixture and cocoa mixture alternately to sifted ingredients and beat well.	Pour into large flat cake pan that has been greased and lightly floured.
Bake 45 to 55 minutes at 350°. Test with toothpick.

title: cherry delight
directions: Crumble graham crackers.
Melt butter in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Make crust from cracker crumbs, butter and
3 tablespoons of sugar.
Chill.

title: party punch
directions: In a large bowl, combine all ingredients except ginger ale. Pour over ice in punch bowl.
Add ginger ale before serving. Makes twenty 4 oz. servings.

title: dressing covered pork chops
directions: Brown pork chops on both sides.
Prepare dressing.
Line pan (at least 2-inches deep) with aluminum foil, leaving enough to cover top.
Place 3 pork chops in pan and cover with 1/2 of dressing.
Place other 3 pork chops on top and cover with remaining dressing.
Bake at 375° until meat is tender.
Serves 6.

title: buttermilk dressing
directions: Measure ingredients into container, seal and shake well. Refrigerate several hours, then shake before serving. Makes 1 cup.

title: teriyaki steak
directions: Marinate overnight.
Grill or broil in oven.
Also great with chicken.

title: coconut pineapple cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch pan. Combine flour, baking soda and salt.
In separate bowl, whisk together oil, buttermilk, eggs and vanilla.
Stir in sugar, pineapple and 1 1/2 cups coconut; mix well. Stir in flour mixture. Pour into pan.
Bake on center oven rack for 30 to 35 minutes or until toothpick inserted near center comes out clean.
Cool in pan on wire rack.

title: banana sticky buns
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Place 2 teaspoons brown sugar, 2 teaspoons butter and 3 pecan halves in each of 12 medium muffin cups.
Place in oven to melt sugar and butter.
Stir baking mix and banana to a soft dough.
Gently smooth into a ball on floured cloth covered board.
Knead 5 times.
Roll into rectangle, 15 x 9-inch.
Spread with 2 tablespoons butter and sprinkle with 1/4 cup brown sugar. Roll up, beginning at long side.
Pinch edge of dough into roll to seal.
Cut roll into twelve 1 1/4-inch slices.
Place slices, cut side down in muffin cups.
Bake 10 minutes.
Immediately invert pan onto serving tray or baking sheet; let pan remain a minute so butterscotch drizzles down over buns.
Serve warm.
Makes 12 buns.

title: coconut-banana cream pie
directions: Preheat oven to 300°; mix coconut, oats and 4 tablespoons butter by hand.
Pat coconut mixture onto bottom and up side of 9-inch pie plate.
Bake crust 15 minutes, until golden; cool.
In saucepan, combine milk, cornstarch, salt, egg yolks, 1/2 cup sugar and remaining 2 tablespoons butter.
Cook over medium-low heat, stirring constantly until mixture boils and thickens.
Boil 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Stir in vanilla.
Line pie crust with bananas (sliced 1/4-inch thick); pour filling over bananas.
Cover with plastic wrap.
Refrigerate until cold.
Mix whipping cream and 2 teaspoons sugar until stiff peaks.
Spread over pie; garnish with sliced toasted almonds.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: no sugar oatmeal cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350° and lightly spray a cookie sheet with cooking spray.
In a large bowl, combine all ingredients until moist.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto cookie sheet about 1-inch apart. Bake for 20 to 25 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: easy cobbler
directions: Melt butter in oblong baking dish.
In a separate bowl, mix well:
sugar, milk, flour and baking powder. Pour into baking dish.
Cover with fruit and syrup.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: jello salad
directions: Pour jello into pan with pineapple.
Stir and bring to a boil. Refrigerate until half jelled (not hard).
Mix in cottage cheese. Mix in the Cool Whip.
Refrigerate at least 1 hour.

title: pie crust
directions: Mix flour, salt and oil with fork, then add water, mixing with fork to form ball.
Using hands, mix a little before rolling out between 2 sheets of wax paper. Do not double recipe.
(No flour on wax paper.)
Makes one 8 or 9-inch pie crust.

title: carrot cake(diabetic dessert)
directions: Combine flour, whole wheat flour, baking powder, baking soda, cinnamon and ginger.
In second bowl combine oil, sugar or substitute, eggs, pineapple juice and vanilla.
Stir liquid into dry ingredients until smooth.
Stir in carrots, raisins and pineapple.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 5-inch loaf pan. Bake 35 to 40 minutes at 350° or until inserted toothpick comes out clean.
Cool in pan on rack for an hour.
Unmold cake and serve.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar if desired.

title: berry chocolate pie
directions: In medium microwave-safe bowl, combine chocolate chips and milk.
Microwave on Medium 1 1/2 minutes, stirring every 30 seconds.
Stir until chocolate is completely melted and smooth. Stir in vanilla.

title: marinated fish
directions: Place fish in shallow serving dish.
Marinate with mixture of lemon juice, soy sauce, melted butter, garlic, green onion and lemon pepper.
I measure to my taste.

title: yummy cookies
directions: Cream butter or margarine with sugar.
Add flour and then vanilla, baking powder and egg.
Mix all.

title: diabetic spice cookies
directions: Boil water, shortening, raisins and spices together for 3 minutes.
Let cool; beat in eggs.
Dissolve salt, soda and saccharin tablets in water and add to eggs.
Sift flour and baking powder and add and mix well.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: pasta salad
directions: In large pot, boil water.
Add tri-color pasta and cook until done.
Drain and rinse with cold water until pasta is cool.
In large bowl, cut cheese.
Add pepperoni, olives and shrimp.
Then add pasta.
Pour dressing on pasta and stir.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients except potatoes and cornflakes.
Mix potatoes throughout all combined ingredients.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch baking pan and sprinkle cornflakes over top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Cut potatoes thin.
Put a layer of potatoes, mushroom soup, garlic and salt; repeat.
Pour canned milk and sweet milk.
Cook at 350° for 1 hour until brown.

title: creamy chicken - rice casserole
directions: Cook rice according to package directions. Combine rice and next 10 ingredients; spoon into a shallow 3-quart baking dish. Top with cheese. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until bubbly around edges. Yield: 6 to 8 servings.

title: mincemeat cookies
directions: Combine ingredients as listed adding enough flour to make soft but not stiff.
Spoon onto greased cookie sheet at 350° until brown.

title: butterfinger cake
directions: Bake cake in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
After cooling slightly, poke holes in cake with the end of a knife.

Pour the caramel topping over the cake, spreading it to fill the holes and cover the cake. Allow the cake and topping to cool to room temperature, then spread the Cool Whip on top of the caramel topping.
Sprinkle Butterfinger crumbs on top of the Cool Whip.
Keep refrigerated.

title: noodle pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook noodles as directed and drain.
In a large bowl, combine hot noodles, eggs and 1/2 of cheese.
Mix well.
Press mixture into greased 12 x 9-inch baking dish.
Bake 20 minutes or until lightly browned.
Spoon sauce onto noodle "crust." Add topping and additional cheese.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes more. Serves 8.

title: polynesian chicken
directions: Melt butter.
Add mushrooms, onion and pepper.
Saute until tender.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cook until thoroughly heated. Serve over rice.
Serves about six.

title: sunday morning caramel rolls
directions: Melt together margarine, brown sugar and cinnamon.
Place frozen rolls in Bundt pan.
Sprinkle pudding over rolls.
Pour melted mixture over all.
Keep uncovered overnight on counter. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Invert on large plate.
Serve.

title: stuffed shells
directions: Saute last four ingredients until cooked.
Add sauce and simmer 20 to 30 minutes.

title: freezer corn(cream style)
directions: Combine all ingredients in roaster or similar pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool.
Freeze.

title: christmas rock cookies
directions: Mix butter, sugar; cream then add eggs and water.
Mix cinnamon, cloves and flour; all but 1/2 cup sprinkle over fruit to keep it from all sticking together.
Stir fruit into dough mixture.
Bake at 375° 10 to 15 minutes or until lightly brown around edges.
Cool on wire rack.
Store tightly in plastic container for up to 3 weeks.

title: beef brisket
directions: Brown beef brisket. Put on rack in pressure cooker. In a separate bowl, mix together remaining ingredients. Pour over beef. Cook according to pressure cooker's manufacturer's directions. This recipe can also be used with roast.

title: sour cream biscuits
directions: Combine flour, soda and sour cream in bowl.
Mix until smooth. Knead several times on lightly floured surface.
Pat dough to 1/2-inch thickness.
Cut with 2-inch biscuit cutter.
Place on lightly greased baking sheet.
Bake at 450° for 10 to 12 minutes or until lightly golden.
Yields 6 servings.

title: fruit dessert
directions: Drain juice from fruit and reserve.
Mix juices with vanilla pudding.
Cook.
Pour over fruit.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix and cook on medium until clear.
Cool slightly.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Salt and pepper to taste. Place in a greased dish and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: ice cream pies
directions: Mix cream cheese and condensed milk until creamy.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Place 1/4 mixture in each pie crust.
Top with 1/2 of coconut/nut mixture.
Drizzle about 1/2 of the caramel syrup on that.
Repeat.
Place plastic covers on pies and freeze.
Before serving, remove from freezer a few minutes so that it will be the consistency of ice cream.

title: spoon yeast rolls
directions: Mix sugar, yeast and water in large bowl, stirring until dissolved.
Blend in flour and let stand 10 minutes.
Spoon into greased muffin pan and bake at 400° for 10 to 15 minutes. Remaining dough will keep 1 week in refrigerator, if covered tightly.

title: dad's vegetable soup(canning)
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large stockpot.
If too thick, add more tomatoes or a large can of tomato juice (do not add water). (Note:
Okra, turnips, butter beans, or any other vegetable may be added.
Commercial canned vegetables can be substituted if fresh or frozen are not available.)
Cook on high heat to bring to boiling point.
Lower heat slightly and continue to cook until all vegetables are soft and flavors blended (2 to 3 hours).

title: chocolate chip-cheese bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Cut cookie dough in half; press into bottom of greased 8-inch baking pan. In a mixing bowl, combine cream cheese, sugar and egg; mix until smooth. Spread over crust. Crumble remaining cookie dough over top. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean. Cool and enjoy. Refrigerate any leftovers. Really good with ice cream.

title: chocolate cake(dark and moist)
directions: Put 2 squares unsweetened chocolate, the shortening and boiling water in microwave-safe bowl.
Cover and microwave just until chocolate melts.
Cool slightly.
Add the sugar; mix.
Add the flour; mix.
Put the 1 tablespoon lemon juice in measuring cup. Add milk to 1/4 cup.
Stir.
Add soda; mix and add to batter.
Mix well.
Add egg; mix well.
Batter will be very thin.
Put in greased 8-inch pan.
Bake at 350° to 375° for 25 to 30 minutes, or until center is done.
Double for 2 layer cake.

title: caramel apple dip
directions: Mix and cream the brown sugar and cream cheese; add vanilla and peanuts.
Quarter apples; take out seeds.
Leave apple peel on apples.
Dip apples in dip and eat.

title: bread pudding
directions: Heat milk to scalding.
Pour milk over bread cubes; cool.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into buttered 1 1/2-quart casserole at 350° for 40 or 45 minutes.
Serve warm with cream.
Makes 6 servings.

title: carrot casserole
directions: Mix and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: pecan pie
directions: In a quart saucepan over moderate heat, bring the 1/2 cup of sugar, corn syrup and butter to a boil, stirring occasionally. Meanwhile, in a medium size mixing bowl, beat eggs lightly. Stirring vigorously, slowly pour hot mixture over eggs.
Stir in vanilla, salt and pecans.
Shake 1 tablespoon of flour and sugar together and sprinkle in bottom of unbaked pie shell.
Add hot mixture and bake at 350° for
a metal pan for 45 minutes.
Use cake tester; insert halfway between center and outside, if it comes out clean it's done.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Peel and devein shrimp.
Cook onions and pepper in butter until almost tender.
Add celery and cook a little longer.
Add water and tomato paste; simmer.
Add shrimp and cook until done (about 5 minutes).
Serve over white rice.

title: chicken florentine
directions: Grease (or Pam) 9 x 9-inch casserole.
Spread spinach on bottom, then chicken.
In saucepan, melt 3 tablespoons butter. Stir in flour to form roux.
Slowly stir in milk, then add seasonings.
Cook until thick and just beginning to boil.
Add Parmesan and cream, stirring, over low heat until cheese melts. Pour sauce over chicken.
Combine crumbs and melted butter. Sprinkle on sauce.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until heated through.
Serve with rice.
Serves 6.
Can be doubled in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Spread croutons in 9 x 13-inch lightly greased pan.
Cook sausage and cover croutons with it.
Mix eggs, milk, soup, mushrooms and mustard together and pour over croutons and sausage. Refrigerate 8 hours or overnight.
Remove; let stand 30 minutes before putting in oven.
Bake at 325° for 50 to 55 minutes, uncovered.
Add cheese and cook 5 more minutes.

title: italian cookies
directions: Cream eggs, sugar and butter together.
Add rest of ingredients.
Mix well.
Drop by teaspoon on ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.

title: microwave poppycock
directions: Microwave on High for 11 minutes in a large bowl.
Pour over popped corn.
Can add nuts if desired.
Mix well.
Be careful, syrup is very hot.
Spread out on cookie sheet until cool, then break up and store in airtight container.

title: squash stuffed chicken
directions: Melt butter, onion and basil in pan.
Add zucchini; cook 2 minutes on medium-low.
Remove from heat; add bread, egg, cheese, salt and pepper.
Stuff mixture under skin of chicken.
Bake at 375° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: frozen frappuccino
directions: Make double strength coffee by brewing with twice the coffee. (2 Tbsp.
Coffee per Cup).
Chill.
Combine all ingredients in a blender and blend on high until ice is crushed and drink is smooth. Makes 2 - 16 oz.
Glasses.
Add Whipped Cream.

title: cheyenne's cajun roast
directions: Stuff roast with garlic. Brush sides of roast with hot pepper sauce, brown gravy mix and Creole seasoning. Put oil in Dutch oven pan or roasting pan; brown meat well on all sides over high heat. Add water; cover and simmer gently over a low heat for 2 to 3 hours or until meat is tender.

title: orange frost soda
directions: Place 2 scoops of orange sherbet in a tall glass;
fill with orange soda.
Yields 5 servings.

title: death by chocolate
directions: Bake brownies.
Cool.
Punch holes in brownies with fork. Pour Kahlua over brownies; set aside.
Make Jell-O mousse.
Break candy bars into small pieces.
Crumble 1/2 the soaked brownies and place in bottom of glass trifle dish.
Cover with 1/2 of mousse. Layer with 1/2 of candy; add 1/2 topping.
Repeat with remaining ingredients.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: hot sausage casserole
directions: Brown sausage and drain on paper towel.
Cook onion and hash browns.
Add drained sausage and cook slow about 5 minutes.
Place in baking dish, rotating layers, beginning with potato mixture, then cheese.
Top with cheese, then warm just enough to melt cheese.

title: speedy scalloped corn
directions: Combine corn, cracker crumbs, evaporated milk, egg, onion, salt and pepper in a buttered 10 x 6 x 2-inch baking dish; sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Allow to stand 5 minutes before serving.

title: ranger cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Roll into balls.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes on a baking sheet sprayed with Pam.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Butter casserole dish and layer with potatoes, pepper and onion.
Cover each layer with soup.
Top with pork chops and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
After first 30 minutes, take out and turn pork chops over for next 30 minutes.
Rice can be used instead of potatoes.

title: barbecue cocktail franks
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients in slow cooker.
Cut hot dogs in 1-inch pieces and add to sauce mixture in slow cooker.
Heat on high until hot dogs are thoroughly heated, then cook on low until ready to serve.
(If you double the recipe, don't add more vinegar.)

title: bible cake
directions: Beat Jeremiah 17:11 until light.
Blend in Jeremiah 6:20. Beat in Judges 5:25.
Into another bowl, sift 1 Kings 4:22.
Add Amos 4:5, Leviticus 2:13 and 2 Chronicles 9:9.
Combine dry ingredients with liquid mixture alternately with an additional 1 1/2 cups of Judges 4:19.
Fold in 1 Samuel 14:25.
Chop Nahum 3:12 and Numbers 17:8.
Add to the mixture, folding in gently.
Beat well.

title: chicken diablo
directions: Mix together in baking pan.
Dip both sides of chicken in mixture.
Baste once or twice during cooking.
Will be golden brown.
Serve hot or cold.
Freezes well.
Bake at 375°.

title: cucumber-party-slices
directions: Soften cream cheese; blend in Italian dressing mix.
Spread on party slices.
Place a cucumber slice on each piece and sprinkle with dill weed.
Refrigerate until serving time.

title: sandwich spread
directions: Grind and drain tomatoes and sweet and hot peppers.
Cook together sugar, flour, salt, mustard and vinegar.
Bring to a boil (stir constantly to prevent scorching).
Add drained vegetables. Cook 10 minutes.
Remove from stove and add 1 pint salad dressing. Mix well and put in jars.
Process jars for 10 minutes in boiling water.

title: pork chop with rice casserole
directions: Salt and pepper chops to taste.
Heat oven to 350°.
Place rice in large baking dish..
Mix soup, water, soy sauce and onion. Add drained vegetables.
Place pork chops on top.
Bake 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: ham and cheese treats
directions: Roll out crescents.
Using a small glass, cut dough into circles.
Put in small muffin tin.
Brush with melted oleo.
Cut ham into small pieces.
Mix with cheese, garlic powder and onion. Fill crescent dough.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Makes 24.
(I always double the recipe.)

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Cream cheese, mayonnaise and sugar in mixer.
Mix bananas with lemon juice.
Fold in fruit, nuts and marshmallows.
Stir in Cool Whip and freeze.
Serve frozen.

title: ambrosia
directions: Combine all ingredients and chill overnight.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix together crushed pretzels, sugar and melted butter.
Press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 8 minutes at 400°.
Cool thoroughly.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix all ingredients. Bake in tube pan 1 1/2 hours at 325°.

title: mexican dip
directions: In a 9-inch pie plate, preferably Pyrex, starting with the cream cheese, spread each ingredient over the one before, ending with the Cheddar cheese.
Bake in oven at 350°, until cheese is melted and bubbling, approximately 20 to 25 minutes.
May be microwaved.

title: strawberry shortcake biscuits
directions: Mix together flour, baking powder, salt and sugar, then add the egg and milk.
Stir together with a fork.
Pat into 6 mounds on a lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes.

title: rocky road cookie pizza
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Line 12-inch pizza pan with foil; grease foil.
Press cookie dough into bottom of foil-lined pan; bake at 350° for 13 to 16 minutes or until light golden brown.
Remove from oven.
Sprinkle peanuts, marshmallows and chocolate chips. Drizzle with caramel.
Bake an additional 5 to 10 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool completely.
Remove foil from pizza.
Cut into wedges.
Makes 16 servings.

title: tasty potatoes
directions: Cut potatoes into bite size pieces (skins on).
Put in shallow casserole dish (greased).
Sprinkle on top the cheese and garlic. Put pat of butter on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes, stirring every 15 minutes.

title: chicken parmigiana
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. In bowl, combine bread crumbs and 1/4 cup of Parmesan cheese. Put egg in another bowl and beat thoroughly. Dip chicken into egg and then dip into the bread crumbs. Shake chicken to remove excess crumbs. In large skillet, heat 1/4 cup of olive oil. Add chicken and cook 5 minutes on each side, until golden brown.

In small bowl, mix spaghetti sauce, garlic and oregano; mix thoroughly. Pour into a baking dish and arrange chicken over mixture. Cover loosely with foil and bake for 40 minutes. Remove chicken from oven and put slice Mozzarella cheese on top chicken. Bake another 10 minutes. Serve with ziti with parsley sprinkled on top.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Boil eggplant, onions and pepper until tender and drain well. Mix in other ingredients except crackers and cheese.
Place a layer of broken crackers and a layer of eggplant mixture and sprinkle with cheese.
Repeat layers.
Put crackers on top.
Bake in 13 x 9 x 2-inch dish at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: baked cheese grits
directions: Cook the grits and water slowly until the mixture thickens. While hot, add the grated Cheddar cheese, Longhorn or Velveeta cheese, butter or oleo, seasoning salt (Lawry's or Beau Monde), salt, eggs and Tabasco sauce.
Mix together and bake in a greased 9 x 13-inch casserole at 250° for
1 hour. Serves 12 to 16.

title: chex mix
directions: Bring the oleo and sugar to a boil, stirring constantly; let this come to a full boil, then
pour over crackers.
Bake in 400° oven for 5 minutes; take out of oven and add chocolate and butterscotch chips.
After they melt, spread over all, then sprinkle with chopped nuts.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Wash chicken breasts; cover with water in pan and bring to a boil.
Cook slowly for about an hour.
Cut up into small pieces. Crumble 1/2 of the crackers into bottom of baking dish.
Mix chicken, soups and sour cream; pour over crackers.
Crumble rest of crackers on top.
Slice stick of butter or margarine into small pieces and scatter over top of casserole.
Bake in oven at 350° until bubbly, about 45 minutes.
Delicious and easy.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix together and bake in oven at 325° for 55 to 60 minutes.

title: mustard sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
If desired, you may add Tabasco sauce or Texas Pete to make hot.
Store in the refrigerator.

title: pumpkin pecan bisque
directions: In large saucepan, melt butter; saute onion and garlic 7 to 8 minutes until lightly browned.
Add broth, pumpkin, water, brown sugar, thyme, rosemary, cumin and salt.
Bring to simmer.
Reduce heat; cook 10 minutes, stirring frequently.
Remove from heat. Stir in half and half.
In blender, combine soup mixture and pecans in two batches at low speed for 1 minute.
Pour into same saucepan.
Heat through, stirring often.
Yields 6 servings.

title: lite vegetable spread
directions: Blend all ingredients together in a food processor.
Spread on crackers or use as a dip with raw veggies.

title: picante sauce
directions: Mix in large kettle and bring to boil.
Reduce to simmer. Cook for 1 1/2 hours, uncovered, stirring frequently.
Ladle into jars and seal.
Yields 8 to 10 pints.

title: chocolate sheet cake
directions: Combine salt, flour and sugar in large mixing bowl; set aside. Bring to boil 1 stick margarine, cocoa, water and Crisco.
Pour over the mixture.
Add 2 eggs, milk, vinegar, soda and vanilla. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes in greased cookie sheet.

title: kraut salad
directions: Mix sugar and vinegar.
Bring to a good boil and pour over mixture.
Let set overnight before eating.

title: sweet potato pudding
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar, milk, potatoes and vanilla.
Fold in raisin and coconut.
Stir in butter and pour in greased casserole dish.
Bake at 400° for 40 minutes or until pudding is set.

title: frozen fruit cups
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into baking cups and freeze.

title: salsa
directions: Boil tomatoes and then peel and chop.
Add rest of ingredients and blend to the desired texture.

title: skillet bread
directions: Grease an iron skillet.
Mix the ingredients and pour into skillet.
Bake at 400° for 35 minutes.

title: persimmon pudding
directions: Add sugar to the persimmon pulp, then add beaten eggs, stirring well.
Add soda to buttermilk and stir until foaming ceases.
Add buttermilk mixture to the persimmon mixture and stir well.
sift flour, salt, and baking powder into persimmon mixture and beat well.

title: sour cream apple pie
directions: Preheat oven and cookie sheet to 400°.
In small bowl mix together flour, salt, sugar and nutmeg.
In another small bowl, mix together egg, sour cream and extract.
Add to dry ingredients and mix well.
Stir in apples.
Pour into pie crust.
Bake on preheated cookie sheet for 15 minutes.
Reduce oven temperature to 350° and continue baking for 30 minutes or until golden.
Meanwhile prepare topping.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Combine dressing ingredients and toss with salad.

title: black-eyed peas casserole
directions: Cook peas well done.
Mix with rice, ham, tomatoes, chopped onions and chopped green pepper.
Mix well.
Season with salt and pepper.
Pour into buttered casserole and bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: country dinner grits and cheese
directions: Combine grits, water and salt.
When almost done, add cheese and milk and cook about 15 minutes longer or until thick.
(Serve with smothered chicken or pork chops and hot buttered biscuits. Use gravy from chicken over grits.)

title: green tomato mincemeat
directions: Cook until thick, about 1 hour.
Add 1 cup vinegar.
Seal in hot jars or cool and freeze.
Makes 2 cups per container.

title: chocolate delight
directions: First Layer:
Spray 13 x 9 Pyrex (or 11 x 8) with Pam.
Mix flour, margarine and pecans and pat in Pyrex.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool and add Second Layer.

title: honey apple cake
directions: Combine
all
ingredients except apples in small mixing bowl. Beat
with electric mixer on low speed about 4 minutes. Stir in apples.
Bake
in
8-inch
or 9 1/2-inch round pan in 350° oven about 30 minutes, or until done.

title: pumpkin dessert
directions: Mix the first 7 ingredients together; pour into 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Sprinkle yellow cake mix over the mixture.
Melt oleo; sprinkle over cake mix.
Put in a 350° oven for 38 minutes. Remove and sprinkle nuts over the cake and bake for an additional 30 minutes.

title: chicken gumbo
directions: Saute celery, onions and bell pepper in butter; salt and pepper to taste. Add this to other ingredients. Simmer for 30 minutes. Serve over rice.

title: my favorite fruit dip
directions: Beat together until smooth. Serve with fresh fruit; especially good with apples.

title: easy meat loaf
directions: Put oatmeal in a bowl with milk and eggs and let soak for 5 minutes.
Mix all other ingredients, then add the oatmeal mixture. Shape in a loaf in baking dish.
Cover well with catsup.
Bake in oven at 300° for about 45 minutes or until meat is done.

title: spinach dip
directions: Cook and drain spinach.
Mix in other ingredients.
Chill. Cut center out of bread and fill with dip.
Cut bread into dipping-size pieces.

title: puppy chow
directions: Melt first 3 ingredients, fold in cereal.
Put all in Ziploc bag and shake it up . Get the kids involved in this one.

title: butterscotch delights
directions: Mix flour and butter and press in baking dish, then press nuts on top of it.
Bake at 350° until light brown.
Let cool.

title: scripture cake
directions: Beat eggs.
Add remaining ingredients;	mix well.
Bake in tube pan at 325° for approximately 1 hour.

title: mocha swiss chocolate almond(homemade ice cream)
directions: Whisk the eggs in a mixing bowl until light and fluffy, 1 or 2 minutes.
Whisk in the sugar, a little at a time, then continue whisking until completely blended, about 1 minute more.
Add the cocoa and coffee and whisk to blend.
Whisk in the cream and milk thoroughly.
Transfer the mixture to an ice cream maker and freeze following the manufacturer's instructions.
After the ice cream stiffens (about 2 minutes before it is done), add the almonds, then continue freezing until the ice cream is ready.

title: old time bread pudding
directions: Put into greased 1 1/2-quart baking dish toast, cut in quarters.
Sprinkle raisins over toast.
Mix eggs, 1/4 cup sugar, salt, Pet milk, water and vanilla.
Pour over toast.
Let stand 10 minutes, then sprinkle with 4 teaspoons sugar and the cinnamon. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until knife comes out clean.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix softened cream cheese with all ingredients, except pecans.
Roll the cheese ball in the pecans.
Place in refrigerator over night.

title: sour cream fudge
directions: Mix sugar, corn syrup, butter and sour cream together.
Cook over medium heat until reaches the soft ball stage.
Cool to room temperature.
Beat until thick and pour all at once onto buttered platter.
Do not spread top, it will be glossy and uneven.

title: cream cheese brownies
directions: Melt chocolate and 3 tablespoons of butter in a small saucepan over very low heat, stirring constantly.
Cool.
Blend remaining butter with cheese until softened.
Gradually add 1/4 cup of sugar, beating well.
Blend in 1 egg, 1 tablespoon flour and 1/2 teaspoon vanilla.
Set aside.
Beat remaining 2 eggs until thick and light color.
Gradually add remaining sugar; beat until thick.
Add baking powder, salt, and 1/2 cup flour.
Blend in cooled chocolate mixture, nuts, and vanilla.
Spread about 1/2 of the batter in a greased 8 or 9-inch square pan.
Add cheese mixture; spread evenly. Top with tablespoonfuls of remaining batter.
Zigzag a spatula through to marble.
