Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes, or until top springs back when touched.
Cool.
Cut into bars.

title: sweet and sour green beans
directions: Drain beans, fry bacon, then saute onions in bacon fat.
Mix in sugar and vinegar.
Pour over beans while hot.
Top with bacon pieces; marinate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Cream peanut butter, cream cheese, powdered sugar and milk together.
Fold Cool Whip into mixture.
Blend on low speed.
Pour into crust.
Chill.
Top with chocolate shavings, cinnamon or crushed nuts.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.

title: bushrod's corned "beast" hash
directions: Saute onions and garlic.
Add corned beef (or any cooked "beast"), sliced potatoes and chopped celery.
Cook until hash is heated through and potatoes are tender.
Season to taste.
For Red Flannel Hash, add chopped cooked beets (or canned).

title: banana cake
directions: Combine all of the ingredients, except for the pecans; mix thoroughly by hand.
Stir in the pecans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 5 minutes.

title: butterdips
directions: Melt butter in an oblong 13 x 9-inch pan.
Sift together dry ingredients; add milk.
Stir slowly until dough just clings together.
Turn onto a floured board.
Coat with flour and knead lightly about 10 times.
Roll dough out to 1/2-inch thick rectangle.
Cut into strips using a pizza cutter.
Dip strips into melted butter on both sides and arrange in pan.
Bake for 15 to 20 minutes at 450° in a metal pan or 425° in a glass pan.

title: german chocolate fudge
directions: Combine chocolate chips, German's sweet chocolate and Marshmallow Creme in large bowl.
Combine sugar, butter, evaporated milk and salt in heavy skillet.
Bring to a boil over medium heat.
Cook for 6 minutes, stirring constantly.
Pour hot syrup over chocolate mixture.
Stir with wooden spoon until smooth.
Stir in pecans.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except stuffing and margarine. Mix stuffing with melted butter.
Put 1 cup of stuffing in bottom of buttered 2-quart casserole dish.
Top with squash mixture.
Add remaining stuffing mixture to top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: donna's chicken casserole
directions: Heat the soups, onion, green chilies, chicken broth and celery together.
Layer Doritos, chicken, sauce and Cheddar cheese and then start over until full.
Cook for 30 to 40 minutes or until it has boiled good at 350°.
Serve over rice.

title: chicken sauce bake(microwave)
directions: Arrange chicken pieces, skin side down, and thick edges to outside of 2-quart baking dish.
Cover with plastic wrap, pierced with holes.
Microwave 10 minutes.
Drain and turn chicken.
Mix soup with milk and spices.
Pour over chicken.
Cover with plastic wrap.
Microwave on Medium 24 minutes or until tender.
Let stand 5 minutes.
This may be served over rice.

title: ham, eggs and fried rice
directions: Have all ingredients handy.
Heat skillet or wok over high heat for 30 seconds.
Add 1 tablespoon oil; fry eggs until very moist film appears; remove and set aside.
Add 2 tablespoons oil; stir-fry rice 2 to 3 minutes.
Add thawed peas; stir through until warm.
Add ham and green onions; stir through until warm.
Add eggs; stir until all ingredients are warm and well mixed, then serve.

title: garden casserole
directions: Brush both sides of eggplant with oil.
Place in microwave dish; cover tightly.
Microwave on High for 3 to 5 minutes, until tender.
In small bowl, microwave onion and garlic in 1 tablespoon of oil at High temperature for 3 minutes.
Oil a microsafe dish. Arrange eggplant slices, slightly overlapping.
Sprinkle half of garlic mixture over eggplant.
Top with half of cheese, basil, salt and pepper.
Arrange tomatoes over eggplant.
Sprinkle with remaining garlic mixture, seasonings and cheese.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Cover with waxed paper.
Microwave on Medium-high for 7 to 10 minutes until melted.

title: peppermint's cough remedy
directions: Put peppermint candy and rock candy into a glass gallon jar. Pour in whiskey (don't cheat and drink a swallow) and let dissolve.
Add honey, lemon juice and brown sugar.
Stir or shake until mixed thoroughly.
Take about 1 tablespoon every 4 hours or to your own needs.
Good for coughs, colds and bronchitis.
Not good for hangover.

title: dill potato salad
directions: Cook and dice tomatoes.
Stir in other ingredients.
Mix well.

title: raymond's fruit cobbler
directions: Melt 1/2 stick margarine in baking dish. Mix ingredients together in a bowl; pour in baking dish. Place fruit of your choice on top, not too much juice. Sprinkle cinnamon on top. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: orange tapioca salad
directions: Combine jello, pudding and water in pan.
Bring to full boil. Let set.
Add Cool Whip and fold in oranges.
May change to strawberry jello and strawberries.

title: oven deodorizer
directions: Fill an 8 oz. drinking glass 1/3 full of water.
Dissolve 2 aspirins in the glass Add ll drops of Spirits of Ammonia (aromatic).
You can purchase over the counter at any drugstore. 1/2 tsp. of baking soda.
Stir well and drink immediately.

title: peanut butter drops
directions: Cream the butter and sugar.
Mix in peanut butter.
Add Rice Krispies and mix well. Form small balls.
In top of double boiler, melt Hershey bar, chocolate chips and paraffin.
Stir until well blended.
Dip balls into chocolate and cool on waxed paper.

title: molasses cookies
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and egg together.
Add molasses and tea.
Gradually add dry ingredients.
Roll out on floured board and cut.
Bake on an ungreased pan for 10 to 13 minutes at 375°.

title: cauliflower nut loaf
directions: Saute
onions
and cauliflower in butter.
Combine
all other ingredients, except beaten eggs; mix
with	onions	and cauliflower.
Place in bread loaf pan.
Pour
in
beaten eggs. Bake for 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: zucchini muffins
directions: Beat eggs, oil, sugar and salt together.
Combine flour, soda, baking powder and cinnamon.
Blend together.
Fold in zucchini and pecans.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: grapefruit pineapple slush
directions: Mix juices and tequila.
Pour all but one cup into ice cube trays (preferably metal) fitted with dividers.
Freeze for several hours or up to 2 days.
Refrigerate remaining one cup mixture.

title: beer batter halibut
directions: Open beer; pour into pancake mix until it is the proper consistency for batter.
Drink remainder of beer.
Deep fry batter dipped halibut chunks in hot oil.
Halibut should rise to the top of oil quickly or oil is not hot enough.
Do not overcook.

title: herb roasted chicken and vegetables
directions: Mix soup, water, 1 tsp. Oregano, carrots and potatoes in shallow roasting pan. Top with chicken. Season with remaining oregano and paprika. Bake at 400 degrees for 50 minutes or until done. Stir vegetables.

title: easy sunday chicken casserole
directions: Combine rice and broth in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Lay chicken on rice mixture.
Pour melted margarine over chicken.
Combine soups and soup mix; spoon over chicken.
Cover tightly with foil and bake 3 hours at 275°.
It's ready when you come home from church.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Combine ingredients from corn meal through oil in mixing bowl. Stir well. Add enough milk for desired consistency.
Pour batter into greased baking pan. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until bread tests for doneness.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix sugar, Karo, butter and flour and set over a low heat, stirring constantly, until sugar is melted.
Remove from heat and add well beaten eggs and vanilla, also pecans.
Turn into unbaked pie shell and bake in slow oven until mixture will not shake in the middle or until knife blade inserted in filling comes out clean.

title: calico beans
directions: Brown and drain hamburger.
Chop, brown and drain bacon. Chop and saute onion.
Add to bean mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: sugar-free jello cake
directions: Slice loaf angel food cake into 1-inch slices.
Place in bottom of 9 x 13-inch clear baking pan.
Mix jello with boiling water until dissolved.
Add cold water, pour over angel food cake slices.
Let jello set.
May frost in pan with Cool Whip or set in hot water and unmold, then frost with Cool Whip.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix ingredients together in order.
Pour into 2 greased loaf pans.
Place on lower rack of oven.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes.

title: punch
directions: Mix pineapple juice, dry Kool-Aid and ginger ale.
When ready to serve, add sherbet.

title: banana cream pie(or meringue)
directions: Combine flour, sugar and salt in saucepan.
Blend scalded milk in slowly.
Cook, stirring constantly, over medium heat until mixture thickens and boils.
Continue cooking and stirring 1 minute.
Remove from heat and add a little hot mixture to beaten egg yolks.
Quickly stir into mixture in saucepan.
Return to medium heat and cook, stirring constantly, for 3 minutes or until it thickens and mounds slightly.
Remove from heat and add margarine and vanilla, stirring until margarine is melted. Cool.

title: mildred's famous tamale pie
directions: Blend cornmeal and milk together, then mix in tomatoes, corn and eggs.
Saute in olive oil the chopped onions, garlic cloves, bell pepper, chili powder, pitted olives and salt and pepper to taste.
Add boned chicken, vinegar and sugar.
Bake 1/2 hour at 350°.
Serves 15.

title: strawberry baked alaska
directions: Chill baked pie shell well. Spread bottom with strawberry jam or topping. Reserve a little to drizzle over top.
Soften ice cream at room temperature. Beat with electric mixer until smooth and creamy. Spread ice cream evenly over bottom of pie shell, mounding it in the center.
Place in freezer immediately while preparing the meringue topping.

title: 9 or 10-inch double pie crust
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Cut in 1/3 cup of shortening and then cut in the other 1/3 cup.
Add about 1 more tablespoon of Crisco and cut in with pastry blender.
Sprinkle water, one tablespoon at a time, over the mixture.
Gently mix with fork.
Push mixture to one side of bowl and sprinkle the next tablespoon of water over dry part.
Mix and repeat until all is moistened.
Gather
up with wet fingers and form into a ball.
Let stand in refrigerator for a little while.
Cut in half and use for 2 crusts.
Roll on floured cloth to size needed.

title: delicious grilled burgers
directions: In a medium bowl, combine beef, onion, garlic salt and pepper. Mix well.
Shape into 6 patties.
In a small bowl, combine cheese, mushrooms, bacon and mayonnaise; refrigerate.
Grill burgers over medium-hot coals turning once.
During the last 3 minutes, spoon 1/4 cup of cheese mixture onto each burger.
Serve on buns with lettuce and tomato.

title: honey cake
directions: Beat eggs with sugar; add oil and beat.
Add honey and beat, then milk.
Sift flour with baking powder and soda.
Then add a little flour at a time and continue beating on low speed.
When ingredients are mixed, add walnuts and mix.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour in greased and floured 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Do not fill pan with cake mixture more than half.

title: sangria
directions: Combine wine, juices and sugar in large glass pitcher with ice.
Add sliced fruit and stir.
Yields 1 3/4 quarts.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Flatten dough in a pizza pan and seal edges.
Bake 10 minutes at 375°.
Cool.
Mix ingredients.
Spread on crust.
Chop any vegetables desired and layer on top.
Sprinkle with shredded Cheddar cheese.
Refrigerate.

title: spicy chip dip
directions: Brown beef and drain off grease.
Put all ingredients in crock-pot.
Stir well.
Cover and cook on High 1 hour stirring until cheese is fully melted.
Serve with corn chips.

title: joe's favorite meatballs
directions: In medium bowl beat eggs slightly.
Add milk and bread; mix well.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Add chuck, onion, parsley, garlic, salt and pepper; mix until well blended.
Shape into 24 meatballs. Cook meatballs directly in sauce for added flavor.
Skim fat from sauce.

title: grandmother's sugar cookies
directions: Mix sugars and butter.
Add egg and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients.
Use 1/2 teaspoon of dough and roll into ball.
Mash flat with bottom of glass, dipped in sugar.
Bake at 350° until lightly browned.

title: apple walnut cake
directions: Combine apples and sugar; let stand.
Beat eggs slightly; beat in oil and vanilla.
Mix and sift flour, baking soda, cinnamon and salt; stir in alternately with apple-sugar mixture.
Stir in walnuts.
Pour into greased and floured oblong pan (13 x 9 x 2-inch).
Bake at 350° about 1 hour, or until cake tests done. Let stand in pan, until quite cool; turn out on rack to complete cooling.
Frost with Lemon Butter Frosting; decorate with whole walnut meats.
Cut in squares to serve.
Makes twelve or fifteen squares.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Mix well.
Make in balls.
Fry in butter until brown; drain. Make gravy with flour, 2 beef bouillon cubes and 1 tablespoon instant coffee.
Simmer until done.

title: jambasette
directions: Melt butter in frying pan.
Add beef and cook until lightly browned.
Remove from pan and fry onions (diced) until transparent and tender.
Add tomatoes and meat to onion in skillet.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Cook noodles in boiling water. Combine with meat mixture.
Add half of grated cheese.
Place in casserole and cover with remaining cheese.
Let set 1 hour to blend flavors.
Bake 1 hour in 350° oven.

title: orange slice cake
directions: Cream margarine and sugar and add eggs, one at a time. Dissolve soda in buttermilk.
Add flour alternately with buttermilk to creamed mixture.
Roll nuts, candy and date in extra flour.
Add coconut to this and add to mixture.
Bake at 250° for 2 1/2 hours.

title: parmesan chicken
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Melt butter and soak chicken in it for 5 minutes.
Dip chicken in cheese mixture.
Put in pan or dish.
Pour remaining butter on top.
Bake, uncovered, at 325° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Mix flour, sugar, soda and salt.
Add eggs and mix well; add pineapple.
Pour into greased and floured cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix flour, soda and salt; set aside.
Mix butter, sugar, vanilla and water.
Beat until creamy.
Beat in eggs.
Add flour mixture and chips.

title: peach cream pie
directions: Mix flour, sugar and salt.
Spread 3/4 of this mixture in the bottom and around edges of unbaked crust.
Place drained peach halves (hollow up) in crust.
Pour whipping cream over this, being sure each hollow is full of cream.
Sprinkle remainder of flour and sugar mixture over this.
Bake in a 350° oven for about 1 hour.

title: egg noodles
directions: Mix eggs until fluffy with mixer.
Add water and salt.
Then add flour and mix.

title: cherry cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Drop from teaspoon on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: hot salsa
directions: Drain liquid from 1 can of tomatoes.
Pour into blender or food processor.
Pour entire contents of the other can into liquid from previous can of tomatoes.
Add onion, salt, garlic salt, cilantro leaves and jalapenos; blend well.
Add the tomatoes from the drained can; blend just slightly to break up the tomatoes into pieces.
Pour sauce into container and chill.
Will last for a couple of weeks in refrigerator.

title: cheese filled pears
directions: Combine cream cheese, crushed pecans and honey.
Beat until well blended.
Fill pear halves with mixture.
Place in shallow baking dish or pan.
Sprinkle with vanilla wafer crumbs.
Bake 30 minutes at 350° or until tender.

title: spice bars
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients.
Let stand overnight.
Add the remaining ingredients.
Grease a cookie sheet and put the mixture in it.
Spread it to cover all the pan. Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: quick cherry dessert
directions: Cream oleo and sugar.
Add eggs.
Beat until fluffy.
Add the almond extract.
Stir in flour and baking powder.
Mix until smooth.

title: goulash
directions: Cook macaroni until tender.
Meanwhile, brown ground beef and onion in a skillet that has been treated with a nonstick spray. Drain and rinse macaroni; mix all ingredients in skillet.
Heat over a low fire until heated through.
If not moist enough, add 1 can tomato sauce.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: refrigerator bran muffins
directions: Use large mixing bowl.
Pour 2 cups hot water over Kellogg's All-Bran and let cool.
Cream sugar, salt and Crisco.
Add eggs, buttermilk and Nabisco All-Bran cereal.
Sift together soda and flour and add, then add Kellogg's All-Bran.
Bake in 400° oven for 30 minutes.
Store remainder of dough in refrigerator in glass or plastic (not metal) containers.
Cover; will keep for weeks.
Bake as many as needed in muffin tins.
Nuts and raisins may be added for variety.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Cut broccoli tops into small florets.
In large bowl, combine broccoli, onion, raisins and bacon.
Mix together mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar; pour over broccoli mixture and toss lightly to combine.
Chill several hours or overnight.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Season chicken. Combine flour and chili powder.
Dredge chicken in flour mixture and brown in hot oil.
Remove chicken from skillet.
Add onion, green pepper and garlic and saute until tender.
Stir in rice, tomatoes and water.
Arrange chicken over rice and vegetables; cover and simmer 35 minutes.

title: chilli
directions: Cook and stir beef, onion and green pepper in large skillet until meat is brown and onion is tender.
Drain off fat.
Stir in remaining ingredients except beans.
Heat to boiling, then reduce heat to low.
Cover and simmer 2 hours, stirring occasionally. Stir in beans and heat to boiling.
Cook, uncovered, 5 minutes.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Mix in order given.
Bake in 13 x 9 x 2-inch greased pan in moderate oven (350°) or will make two nice 8 x 8-inch cakes.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Crumble sausage, cook and drain.
Line bottom of greased 9x 13-inch pan with crescent rolls, firmly pressing perforations to seal.
Sprinkle with sausage and cheese.
Combine milk, eggs, salt and pepper.
Pour over sausage and cheese.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Serve hot.
This can be assembled the night before in pan and refrigerated, then baked the next morning for a quick and easy breakfast (just serve with juice and coffee.)
Great for when you have company.
You may use just one kind of cheese, or experiment with combining all three kinds.

title: sweetened condensed milk
directions: Process all ingredients in blender until smooth.
Store in refrigerator for at least 24 hours before using.
One can of condensed milk will keep for 2 weeks.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Mix ingredients and place in baking dish.
Top with cinnamon. Bake at 350° until golden brown and firm.

title: pancakes
directions: Melt butter on griddle and add to batter.

title: egg custard pie
directions: Melt butter, add milk, and beat over fire until scalding. Beat eggs slightly.
Add sugar and vanilla.
Brush crust with unbeaten egg whites.
Add milk to mixture and stir.
Strain into 9-inch pie crust.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes.
Turn control to 375° and bake 10 minutes longer.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream butter, shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, 1 at a time. Beat only enough to blend well.
Sift together dry ingredients. Add dry mixture, alternating with the milk, to the creamed mixture.
Mix thoroughly, but do not overbeat.
Fold in flavoring. Pour batter into a greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.
Cool in pan approximately 5 minutes. Invert on a rack to complete cooling.

title: never fail fudge
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Stir over low heat until well blended.
Bring to a boil over moderate heat.
Do not mistake air bubbles for boiling.
Boil slowly, stirring constantly, for 5 minutes or soft ball stage.
Remove from heat.
Add peanut butter and vanilla.
Turn into well buttered 9 x 9-inch pan and cool.

title: favorite meat loaf
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients and mix together. Bake in desired loaf pan or casserole.
Bake for 1 hour or until no longer pink inside.
Drain; let stand 5 minutes before serving.

title: chicken cacciatore(for low-fat diets)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large skillet, lightly brown skinned chicken in corn oil.
Remove from skillet and place in baking dish.

title: corn relish
directions: In a large saucepan, cover corn with water.
Bring to boiling. Simmer 5 minutes.
Drain.

title: white chocolate mousse(by executive chef "song of norway" cruise ship)
directions: Melt white chocolate, butter and milk in double boiler.
Set aside.
Add egg yolks slowly to the melted chocolate and fold in the beaten whites with sugar.
Fold in whipped cream with sugar and put in refrigerator for approximately 6 hours.
Fill glasses with mousse and garnish with shaved dark chocolate, fresh berries, etc.

title: jewish coffee cake
directions: Sift flour, salt and baking powder together.
Cream the butter and sugar.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Add vanilla.
Add dry ingredients, alternating with milk and beginning and ending with dry ingredients.
Stir in cherries and nuts.
Pour into greased 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes.

title: brunch casserole
directions: Use a greased 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish.
Place bread as a liner in bottom of dish, then cheese, then sausage.
Sprinkle these evenly over the bread.
Mix together eggs, milk, salt, mustard and pepper.
Pour mixture over the bread, sausage and cheese.
Chill overnight.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
(If you want for supper, fix in A.M.)

title: jalapeno cornbread
directions: Mix meal and flour; add buttermilk, oil, eggs and corn.
Mix well.
Stir in pepper, onion and cheese.
Grease an oblong baking pan.
Bake at 375° for 35 minutes until done.

title: ground beef and noodles
directions: Cook macaroni in separate boiler until tender.
Cook remaining until done.
Add tomato juice to macaroni, also tomato sauce.
Mix all ingredients together.

title: baked stuffed tomatoes
directions: Cut tops off tomatoes; scoop out tomato pulp.
Mix together bread crumbs, celery, onion and butter.
Stuff tomato shells with this mixture.
Place in greased baking dish.
Bake in moderate 375° oven for 15 to 20 minutes.
Goes good with pork chops or meat loaf.

title: milky way bars
directions: Combine flour, oatmeal, butter, salt, soda, brown sugar, and egg. Pat 2/3 of mixture in bottom of 9 x 13 pan. Melt condensed milk, choc. chips and butter together and pour over crust layer. Sprinkle rest of dry ingredients on top and bake at 350 degrees for 20 minutes.

title: gary's margaritas
directions: Put all in blender.
Fill blender with crushed ice and blend until slush.

title: blue cheese dressing
directions: Put vegetables in food chopper and chop fine.
Mix all ingredients well.
It is better if allowed to sit overnight.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Mix all together.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake until golden brown.

title: homemade pot pie
directions: Roll dough thin.
Cut into squares.
Drop into ham, beef, chicken or venison broth.
Boil 10 to 15 minutes.
Add dry parsley flakes and dry celery flakes to the broth which has been salted to taste.
This may be frozen.
Roll and cut.
Place between wax paper and place in a plastic bag in layers or freeze on a cookie sheet and put in a plastic bag after freezing.
Thaw and cook as directed.

title: holy cow cake
directions: Cook cake mix as directed.
While hot, poke holes in cake and pour caramel over. Crush 1 candy bar and spread over caramel topping.
Leave in refrigerator overnight.
Take Cool Whip and spread over cake. Take the other candy bar, crush and spread over Cool Whip.

title: apple-raisin cake(sugarless)
directions: Beat oil, eggs, sugar substitute, cinnamon, cloves, vanilla and milk.
Add baking powder, soda and flour; mix well.
Add apple which has been peeled, cored and chopped finely.
Then add raisins.
Mix well.
Bake in floured loaf pan at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: orange jello salad
directions: Combine jello, sugar and pineapple in saucepan with water. Boil 3 minutes.
Place in refrigerator until it starts to set. Add Cool Whip, nuts and grated cheese.
Mix well.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: cream cheese chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix cheese, eggs, sugar and vanilla.
Cut one roll in 1/8-inch slices; place on greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Spread cheese mix. Sprinkle with 1/2 of walnuts.
Cut second roll of cookies.
Place on top of cheese.
Sprinkle remainder of nuts.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown sausage and drain.
Combine sausage, stewed tomatoes, tomato paste, 1 tablespoon parsley and 2 teaspoons sweet basil; cook for 45 minutes on low.
Boil noodles until tender; put aside. Combine in bowl cottage cheese, 3 eggs, 3 tablespoons parsley and a pinch of salt and pepper; mix.

title: ice cream
directions: Mix pudding, milk and sugar.
Cook until boiling.
Remove from heat and add evaporated milk.
Add eggs.
Pour into container and fill with half and half.
Freeze.

title: broccoli-ham shortcake
directions: Melt butter in medium sized saucepan over low heat. Add flour and stir constantly until smooth and frothy. Let mixture bubble about 3 minutes, stirring often to prevent browning. Gradually stir in milk. Increase heat to medium and simmer, stirring often, about 5 minutes, until thick and smooth. Add cheese, frozen broccoli and ham. Cook, stirring occasionally, until cheese has melted and broccoli is cooked. Cut corn bread into 4 equal pieces. Slice each in half horizontally. Place bottoms on plates. Top with half of sauce, remaining corn bread and remaining sauce.

title: caraway seed soup
directions: Put caraway seed into the water and let it come to a boil. Simmer slowly for about 5 minutes and set aside.
Melt butter; add flour and brown lightly.
Keep stirring to avoid burning.
Remove from heat and add paprika and salt.
Strain the water into the paprika and salt, stirring all the time.
Return to heat and simmer slowly for about 10 minutes.
Serve with egg drops, or with eggless pasta or noodles.

title: athletic director's pork and beans bake
directions: Place beans into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Arrange chops over beans.
Season chops with salt and pepper.
Top with brown sugar and catsup.
Bake for 1 1/4 hours at 325°.
Place onion and lemon slice atop each chop.
Bake for 15 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: strawberry congealed salad
directions: Combine strawberries and jello in a boiler.
Cook until mixture comes to a boil.
Cool; fold Dream Whip and cheese into jello mixture.
Pour into a mold; chill.
Fruit cocktail may be substituted for frozen strawberries and Cool Whip may be used for the Dream Whip.

title: patio chicken
directions: Prepare Minute rice as directed making fairly large servings per person.
Place rice on individual squares of heavy duty aluminum foil.
Sprinkle with dry soup mix.
You may also add cashews, water chestnut slices or fresh mushrooms to rice.
(Let your taste and imagination be your guide.)
Place on top of rice your chicken pieces and sprinkle with more dry soup.
Top this with 1 tablespoon butter and 1 tablespoon evaporated milk.
Seal edges of foil in individual packages.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours.

title: cucumber salad
directions: In large bowl, mix mayonnaise, sour cream, dill, garlic, lemon juice and salt; add onion, celery and cucumbers.
Toss gently. Chill 30 minutes.

title: chicken broccoli casserole
directions: Melt butter.
Saute onions and celery.
Place cooked rice on bottom of buttered baking dish, layer of cooked chicken breast and celery and onions.
Then cover with soup mix and cover with cooked, chopped broccoli.
Top with cheese.
Bake 30 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: scalloped cabbage dish
directions: In a saucepan melt the margarine.
Stir in flour, salt and dashes of seasonings listed.
Slowly add milk while stirring to avoid lumps.
Cook until fairly thick, stirring constantly.

title: appetizer meatballs
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together in a large bowl.
Roll mixture into 1-inch balls.
Bake approximately 10 minutes in a preheated 375° oven.

title: 90 minute dinner rolls
directions: Mix 3/4 cup flour, sugar, salt and undissolved yeast.
Heat milk, water and butter to 120° to 130°.
Add liquids in dry ingredients; beat 2 minutes at medium speed of mixer.
Add 1/4 cup flour; beat at high speed for 2 minutes.
Stir in enough additional flour to make soft dough.
Divide in 12 equal parts. Shape into balls.

title: hot buttered rum
directions: Heat until everything is well blended.
Add 1 jigger more rum to preserve.
(Spices can be adjusted as desired.)

title: breakfast eggs plus
directions: Grease cake pan (9 x 13-inches); whip eggs and set aside. Cube bread enough to cover bottom of pan with a good layer.
Dump on broccoli and cooked and drained bacon and egg mixture.
Top with cheese.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: cheddar squash bake
directions: Mix squash with egg yolks, sour cream and flour.
Fold in egg whites.
Mix melted margarine with croutons or bread crumbs. Layer 1/2 squash and 1/2 of first mixture and 1/2 cheese.
After second layer, top with crumbled bacon and croutons or bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Serves 8 to 10 people.

title: wild rice casserole
directions: Saute onion and sausage; drain fat.
Add mushrooms, cut fine. Cook to blend.
Add wild rice.
Make white sauce of flour, cream and chicken broth.
Mix these and combine with sausage and mushrooms.
Accent with monosodium glutamate.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve with almonds on top.

title: meringues
directions: Add sugar gradually to beaten egg whites (stiff, but not too dry).
Also, add cream of tartar.
Put brown paper on cookie sheet.
Drop and shape meringue on paper.
Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes at 275°.
Take out and loosen and return to oven for a few minutes longer.

title: broccoli quiche
directions: Grease round pie pan.
Preheat oven to 350°.
In medium bowl, beat 5 eggs and add oil, mixing on low speed.
In another medium bowl, combine remaining ingredients.
Stir first mixture into spinach mixture, blending well, scraping bowl with spatula to be sure all Bisquick is well blended.
Bake 35 to 45 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: sausage grits casserole
directions: Cook sausage; drain.
Spoon into lightly greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch
pan.
Combine
hot
grits, cheese and butter.
Stir until cheese
and
butter melts.
Combine eggs and milk; stir into grits.
Pour
into
sprayed casserole dish over sausage. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Makes about 15 servings.

title: papaya salad dressing
directions: Put all in blender.
Seeds look and taste like pepper.

title: coconut pie
directions: Mix eggs, sugar, butter and buttermilk together.
Mix well. Add coconut and vanilla.
Pour into pie shell. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pineapple nut cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together in large bowl by hand.
Pour into greased 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes (325° if glass pan).
Top with Cream Cheese Icing.

title: old virginia chocolate cake
directions: Heat butter and milk to boiling point (do not boil). Add brown sugar. Add eggs 1 at a time; beat after each addition. Add dry ingredients and beat. Add vanilla. Bake in 9 x 13 pan at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: corn filled corn bread
directions: Melt butter.
Mix with corn, sugar, meal, egg, flour and milk. Pour in iron skillet or muffin tin (well oiled) and bake at 325° for 20 minutes.

title: layered vegetable salad
directions: Layer in order listed.
Don't stir.
Spread dressing on top of salad.
Refrigerate for at least 6 hours.

title: gingered lime gelatin
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving juice; set the pineapple aside. In a bowl, dissolve the gelatin in water.
Stir in ginger ale, ginger and the reserved juice.
Chill until syrupy, about 45 minutes.
Fold in pineapple.
Transfer to a 6-cup mold coated with nonstick cooking spray.
Refrigerate until firm.
Unmold onto a serving platter.
Yield: 12 servings.

title: deviled eggs
directions: Remove egg yolks from whites. Mash yolks and combine with next 6 ingredients.
Refill egg whites, using pastry tube, if desired. Chill.
To serve, sprinkle tops with paprika.

title: stuffed pumpkin
directions: Cook hamburg in frying pan with a little water, adding small pieces of onion and sage, black pepper and some garlic to taste. Cook potatoes.
Mash or cube.

title: gretchen fayhey's quick breakfast casserole
directions: Line buttered 9 x 13-inch baking dish with buttered bread. Spread sausage over bread. Add cheese and spread evenly.
Beat eggs and half and half together.
Pour over sausage and cheese layers. Refrigerate overnight. Bake at 350°, uncovered, for 40 minutes.
Serve hot.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix all together
with electric mixer.
Bake in greased and floured tube pan at 350° for about 1 1/2 hours.

title: bacon hamburger casserole
directions: Cook noodles and set aside.
Brown bacon till crisp, set aside.
Saute onion in bacon drippings till tender, add hamburger meat.
Cook till no longer pink. Mix soup, sour cream, bacon, onion & meat.
Toss with noodles.
Garnish with chopped parsley. Bake at 350°
till bubbly.

title: chiffon bars
directions: Blend flour, brown sugar and butter together.
Pat down into buttered square pan.
Bake at 350° for 8 minutes and remove.

title: cherry nut cake
directions: One recipe makes:
Two	9 x 13-inch, one 7-inch and one 10-inch round or one 13-inch round.

title: bananas allspice
directions: Peel and cut bananas into 2-inch pieces.
Brush with lemon juice.
Roll in mixture of bread crumbs, sugar and allspice. Place each piece on skewer and toast over hot coals or fry in hot, buttered skillet.

title: chocolate pecan pie
directions: Place pecans in prepared pastry shell; set aside.
Combine chocolate and butter in a medium saucepan.
Cook over low heat until chocolate melts, stirring until smooth.
Remove from heat and add corn syrup and remaining ingredients, mixing well.
Pour mixture over pecans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until knife inserted 1-inch from edge comes out clean.
Yield:
One 9-inch pie.

title: pat's shrimp dip
directions: Have mini snack crackers on hand to dip with.
Good party dish.

title: pig eaten cake
directions: Mix and beat
well.
Bake
in 9 x 13-inch pan for 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: impossible pie
directions: Put all together in blender.
Grease and flour 10-inch pie pan.
Pour blended mixture in pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: margaritas
directions: Put in a blender and add chopped ice to tequila mixture and blend.
Get a Margarita glass that has been salted on the rim with a wedge of lime.
Serve immediately with the enchilada casserole.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to directions.
Drain well.
Mix other ingredients in casserole.
Add broccoli.
Mix well.
Top with crushed crackers.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until brown.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Cook chicken breasts in water (chopped).
Combine chopped chicken breasts, onion, mushrooms and 1/2 cup cheese.
Fry each tortilla in butter.
Put spoonful of chicken mixture in middle of tortilla and roll.
Lay in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix cream of chicken soup and sour cream.
Pour over tortillas.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes, until cheese melts.

title: lucky if there's a bite left
directions: Mix together margarine, flour and pecans; press in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes or until golden brown.

title: double chocolate pound cake
directions: Beat the cake mix, oil and eggs well and blend in sour cream. Add chocolate chips and chocolate.
Blend well.
Bake 55 minutes at 350° in greased tube pan.

title: date nut roll
directions: Cook milk and sugar to soft ball stage (235°), stirring constantly.
Add dates and cook to soft ball (236°), stirring constantly.
Add nuts.
Cool.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Saute onions and almonds in butter.
Mix with beans and soup. Pour into greased casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until bubbly.
Last 5 minutes, sprinkle can of chow mein noodles on top.

title: chicken supreme
directions: Sprinkle soup mix evenly in oblong pan. Sprinkle rice over soup mix. Lay chicken pieces on top of rice. Season chicken with salt and pepper. Pour soup and water over all. Bake at 325° to 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: ali's creamy clam chowder
directions: Peel and chop potato into small cubes.
In a medium pot, mix flour and evaporated milk.
Pour the juice from clams in pot.
Add remaining ingredients except clams.
Stir and cook 3 minutes on high.
Turn heat to medium and simmer 13 minutes.
Stir in clams and heat, then serve.

title: pecan kisses
directions: 1. Heat oven to 350°.
In large bowl combine all crust ingredients, (except marshmellows) until crumb mixture forms. Press in bottom of ungreased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 12-15 minutes or until light golden brown. 2. Immediately sprinkle with marshmellows.
Return to oven for 1-2 minutes or until marshmellows just begin to puff.

Cool while preparing topping. 3. In large saucepan heat corn syrup, margarine, vanilla, and peanut butter chips just until the chips are melted and the mixture is smooth, stirring constantly. 4. Remove from heat; stir in cereal and nuts.
Immediately spoon warm topping over marshmellows and spread to cover.
Chill and then cut into bars ... and enjoy !

title: butterscotch sauce
directions: Cook in double boiler until thick as you like.

title: banana pudding
directions: Layer bananas and wafers.
Mix other ingredients and put after each layer.
Save some for topping.
May add cherries or pecans on top if you want to decorate.

title: cowboy cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, flour, salt, soda, baking powder and then the rest of the ingredients.
Add oatmeal and chocolate or butterscotch chips last and gently stir in.
Drop by spoonfuls onto lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for about 12 minutes.

title: cherry yum-yum
directions: Place cracker crumbs in bottom of large dish. Put chopped pecans on top of crumbs. Mix sugar and cream cheese until creamy. Spread over cracker crumbs and nuts. Add Cool Whip. Spread cherry pie filling on top of Cool Whip. Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: candied walnuts
directions: Mix together brown sugar, salt, orange zest and orange juice.
Add walnut halves and bake on cookie sheet (spread out) covered with foil for 20 minutes at 350°.
Cool on foil.

title: applesauce salad
directions: Empty applesauce into saucepan.
Heat until hot.
Remove from heat; stir into applesauce the Jell-O.
Add crushed pineapple. Pour in Seven-Up.
Mix well.
Pour into Pyrex dish or pan.
Chill until set.
Top with whipped topping and sprinkle crushed nuts on top.

title: salad dressing
directions: Blend all ingredients in a blender until smooth; chill before serving.
Yields 1 cup.

title: bean dip
directions: Brown hamburger and onion; drain.
Blenderize beans and add to meat.
Add catsup, cumin, chili powder and salt and pepper to taste.
Layer in casserole dish the meat and cheese, ending with cheese on top.
Heat in 400° oven until bubbly.

title: chicken divan
directions: Put broccoli in buttered casserole dish or an 8-inch Pyrex. Cut chicken in bite size pieces; put on top of broccoli.
Mix soup with mayonnaise and water.
Pour over chicken.
Mix crumbs with butter and spread over casserole. Bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: gingerbread cake roll and spiced cream
directions: Oil bottom and sides of a 15 x 10 x 1-inch jelly roll pan with oil; line with wax paper and oil and flour wax paper.
Set pan aside.

title: mandarin orange and pineapple salad
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Sprinkle gelatin over mixture and stir well.
Spoon mixture into 13 x 9-inch dish.
Combine pecans and coconut.
Sprinkle over salad.
Chill 6 hours or overnight.

title: seven layer bean dip
directions: Place the beans, cilantro and chili powder in a food processor and process until smooth.
Spread the mixture in a 9-inch deep dish pie pan or a shallow serving dish.
Peel and finely chop the avocado.
Toss with the lemon juice and set aside.

title: cheese sauce
directions: Melt butter.
Stir in flour, salt and pepper, stirring constantly until it bubbles.
Stir in milk; keep stirring until sauce thickens.
Stir in cheese until melted.
Makes 2 1/2 cups.

title: chocolate raisin cookies
directions: Melt Crisco; let cool.
Mix together coffee, sugar and cocoa and bring to boil.
Let cool.
Sift flour; add dry ingredients. Add raisins and nuts.
Mix Crisco and sugar; mix well.
Roll into balls as walnut size.
Use sugar icing.
Put on ungreased cookie sheet.

title: cole slaw
directions: Combine cabbage and carrots in a large bowl.
Sprinkle with sugar, salt and pepper; toss gently.
Stir in mayonnaise.
Cover and chill thoroughly.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: refrigerator cookie
directions: Cream sugars, butter and eggs. Add vanilla, sifted dry ingredients and nuts. Form into rolls. Refrigerate. Slice and bake in moderate oven, 350°, for 12 to 15 minutes or until done.

title: marinated garden salad
directions: Quarter potatoes.
Cut beans in half.

In a 4 1/2-quart pot, cook potatoes, beans and carrots in lightly salted boiling water for 15 minutes or until crisp-tender. Drain in large strainer. Transfer vegetable mixture into a large salad bowl.
Pour dressing over vegetables; let stand 10 minutes to cool.
Mix well to coat vegetables.
Cover and chill in refrigerator for several hours or overnight.

title: 7 layer salad
directions: Amounts can be varied.
Also vary broccoli for cauliflower, etc.

title: pay day bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix cake mix, 1/3 cup butter and egg together.
Press into ungreased cake pan.
Bake for 15 minutes and while hot put marshmallows on top.

title: chocolate sauce
directions: In a saucepan, add 1/2 cup water.
Heat until hot.
Mix sugar, salt, cocoa and flour well.
Add to the hot water.
Cook until thick.
Take off heat.
Add 1 1/2 tablespoons butter and 1/2 teaspoon vanilla.

title: steamers
directions: Brown onion, hamburger and green pepper.
Drain.
Put in saucepan or slow cooker.
Add Worcestershire sauce and mix.
Add rest of ingredients.
Stir.
Cook 45 minutes on low.

title: j.j.'s slaw
directions: Shred first four ingredients in food processor.
In mixing bowl, add last three ingredients with slaw mixture.
Mix well. Place in refrigerator.
For best results, leave overnight.

title: meringues
directions: Beat egg whites with cream of tartar until stiff but not dry. Add sugar 2 tablespoons at a time, beating constantly.
Add flavoring and nuts.
Line cookie sheet with foil or brown paper. Drop meringues by rounded teaspoons or larger if desired.
Bake at 275° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Meringues should be slightly browned. Remove from oven and place meringues on rack to cool.

title: peanut butter dressing
directions: Blend ingredients together.
Serve with your favorite salad ingredients.

title: marzetti (lasagne)
directions: Brown hamburger and onion together in large pan; add soups, catsup, salt, pepper and sugar.
Let simmer while cooking wide lasagne noodles.
Layer in separate loaf or cake pan the meat, noodles and Mozzarella cheese.
Cook at 300° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: easy apple cake
directions: Mix cake mix, apple pie filling and eggs.
In separate bowl, mix cinnamon and sugar.
Grease a 9 x 12-inch cake pan.
Spread half of cake mixture in pan.
Sprinkle half the cinnamon and sugar on top.
Repeat layers.
Bake in a 350° oven for 35 to 40 minutes.
Serve warm or cold.

title: pumpkin pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour tube pan.
Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into pan and bake for 1 hour or until done.

title: blonde brownies
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: punch with sherbet
directions: Boil water and sugar.
Add water to syrup.
Add juices and cool.
Add ginger ale and sherbet when served.

title: salmon cakes
directions: Open salmon and drain juice.
Set aside.
Remove bones. In mixing
bowl
mash salmon well.
Add beaten egg to salmon; mix well
with
fork.
Add
juice
from
salmon
to flour and pepper. Add
cracker
crumbs
to
flour
mixture, then add to salmon. Melt shortening in frying pan and fry salmon patties. Fry to golden brown.

title: pork spareribs in barbecue sauce
directions: In a small saucepan, saute onion in oil until transparent. Add remaining ingredients except spareribs.
Mix well.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Pour over spareribs in a large glass baking dish; let stand 1 hour, turning occasionally.
Arrange on shallow rack or broiler pan.
Bake at 350° for about 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Turn ribs and baste with remaining barbecue sauce two or three times during baking.
Cut in portions to serve.
Makes 4 servings.

title: nut filled cookies
directions: Mix together.
Shape into 24 small balls.
Press into small muffin tins and work up around sides, making a small cup.

title: soft brownies
directions: Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Very, very good.

title: lemon chiffon pie
directions: In large bowl, fold lemonade, Cool Whip and milk.
Pour into pie crusts and chill.
Makes 2 pies.

title: easy chipped beef
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Slice beef into very small pieces.
Mix thoroughly all ingredients.
Cool until stiff.
Form into a ball.

title: split pea soup
directions: Combine ham bone, water, peas, carrots, onion and bay leaf in a large kettle.
Bring to boiling; cover.
Simmer 1 hour until peas are soft.
Remove ham bone; cut off bits of meat and add to soup.
Taste and season with salt and pepper if needed.
Remove bay leaf.

title: barbecue beef
directions: Brown meat in fat. Add rest of ingredients.
Cook at 250° for 2 hours. Serve on toasted hamburger buns.

title: smell of williamsburg
directions: Pour 1/2 of water, cider and juice in pot.
Add several sticks cinnamon, ginger, cloves and nutmeg.
Boil slowly.
When it begins to boil down, add the rest of liquids.
Add remaining spices, depending on how strong you wish the smell.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Combine cake mix, oil, sugar and buttermilk.
Add eggs one at a time.
Add poppy seed.
Pour into a well-greased and lightly floured Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for
1 hour.

title: pineapple salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Cut celery leaves from stalks; reserve stalks.
Combine tops in 6 cups water, chicken, bay leaf, 1 teaspoon salt, and pepper in Dutch oven.
Cover and simmer 1 hour or until chicken is tender. Remove chicken; chill and cut in bite size pieces.
Combine broth, potatoes, carrots, onions and celery; cook until tender.
Dissolve cornstarch in 1/4 cup water.
Stir into vegetable and broth mixture and cook until clear and thick.
Stir in chicken.
Put into 3-quart greased casserole.
Combine flour, milk, oil and remaining salt.
Stir and spoon into mounds over top of chicken mixture.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes.

title: chicken bundles
directions: Blend cream cheese and butter together until smooth.
Add chicken, salt, pepper, milk, onions and pimentos.
Stir.
Separate rolls into four rectangles.
Seal perforations.
Spoon 1/2 cup chicken mixture into center and pull four corners of dough to center and seal.
Brush tops with butter and sprinkle on crushed croutons.
Bake on cookie sheet at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes. Yields 4 servings.

title: sausage balls
directions: Combine ingredients with hands.
Mix well.
Will be dry. Pinch off small pieces and roll into balls.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.

title: stacked applesauce cake
directions: Mix sugar, butter and eggs.
Add flour, salt and baking powder.
Mix soda with sour milk.
Add vanilla.
Mix all ingredients together.
Spread in 9-inch round pans, a small amount in each pan.
Makes 8 or 9 layers.
Bake 10 minutes in a 350° oven.
When the layers are done, turn out on flat dish one layer at a time.
Spread applesauce between layers and stack.

title: french silk
directions: Stir together.
Pat down in large 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Stir again.
Pat down and chill.

title: persimmon bread
directions: Mix all ingredients; pour into ungreased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: red and white jello salad
directions: In small saucepan, dissolve the lemon jello in 1/2 cup of boiling water.
Have cream cheese at room temperature or soften in microwave.
Add cream cheese and marshmallows, cut up, to the jello mixture and stir over low heat until dissolved completely. Cool.

title: jambalaya
directions: Dice 8 to 10 whole pieces of chicken.
Cut sausage into rounds (may use shrimp). Saut chicken and sausage until you think chicken is nearly done.

title: applesauce snacking cake(low-fat)
directions: Mix bran, applesauce, egg product and molasses; let stand 5 minutes.
Blend flour, baking soda and cinnamon; set aside.
With mixer, beat sugar and margarine until creamy.
Beat in bran mixture until smooth.
Blend in flour mixture; stir in raisins. Spread batter evenly in ungreased 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking pan. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until toothpick inserted comes out clean.
Cool in pan on wire rack.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar if desired; cut into 48 (2 x 1-inch) bars.

title: pear relish
directions: Grind pears,
peppers
and
onions with coarse blade of food chopper.
Add
salt, sugar and vinegar.
Boil well for 10 to 15 minutes.
Put into hot sterilized jars and seal.
Makes about 6 pints.

title: bran raisin muffins
directions: Grease 12 muffin cups.
Combine bran cereal and milk in a large bowl.
Let stand for 5 minutes.
Add raisins, butter, brown sugar, molasses and egg to cereal; mix well.
Stir in flour until moistened.
Batter will be lumpy.
Do not overmix.
Fill muffin cups 2/3 to 3/4 full.
Bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: ground turkey quick dish
directions: Brown the ground turkey. Cook the instant rice according to directions using a microwave-safe casserole dish.
Combine the ground turkey, rice, tomatoes and beans. Microwave 3 to 4 minutes, until hot.

title: mexican roll-ups
directions: Mix all ingredients and spread thinly on tortillas.
Roll up. Refrigerate for 1 hour.
Slice into bite-size pieces.
Dip in salsa.

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Put in pie shell and cover with the other shell. Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Serves 4 to 6.

title: orange sherbet
directions: Mix all ingredients together in ice cream freezer.
Freeze until hard.

title: candied sweet potatoes(published in asheville times newspaper, 1936)
directions: Boil sweet potatoes until fairly tender, but not done.
Allow the potatoes to cool.
Skin them and cut lengthwise in halves. Arrange the pieces in one layer in a buttered baking dish or shallow pan; do not pack too closely.
Boil corn syrup or maple syrup, brown sugar, butter and salt until thickened.
Pour the syrup over the potatoes.
Bake in 300° oven 45 minutes to one hour, turning pieces carefully and browning on both sides.

title: french strawberry pudding
directions: Crumble wafers.
Put half of the crumbs in bottom of 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Whip butter, sugar, vanilla and eggs together until light and creamy.
Spread over crumbs.
Add whipped cream and spread.
Next add strawberries.
Mix other half of crumbs and pecans and spread over top.
Chill overnight.

title: grandma pearl's chocolate gravy
directions: Mix the sugar, cocoa and flour, then add the milk. Blend and cook on top of stove until it begins to boil and get thick.

title: pork casserole
directions: Combine ingredients in large bowl.
Pour into large baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: incredible edibles
directions: Combine cracker crumbs, sugar, margarine and peanut butter. Pat into greased 11 x 9-inch baking pan.
Melt chocolate over low heat.
Spread over crumb mixture.
Refrigerate until cool.
Cut into squares.

title: one-bowl brownies
directions: Mix all ingredients (will be stiff batter).
Spread in 13 x 9-inch pan, greased and floured.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Do not overcook.
These brownies are chewy.
Store in airtight container.

title: mexican tamales(foil cooking)
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put in pouch.
Seal edges. Cook 25 minutes.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Mix and chill overnight.

title: microwave turtles
directions: Place caramels, milk and margarine in 1-quart glass measuring cup or casserole dish.
Heat on Full power two to three minutes or until caramels are melted.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Sift flour, sugar, salt, soda and baking powder all together and cut in shortening.
Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add yeast and buttermilk and mix well.
Dough will keep 2 days or longer, covered in the refrigerator.

title: crunchy chicken casserole
directions: Mix together chicken, soup, mayonnaise, vegetables, rice, juice, onion, mushrooms and almonds in greased 2-quart casserole. Sprinkle cornflakes and butter on top.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: baked beans
directions: Brown meat, drain off fat. Mix all ingredients together. Cook at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: citrus punch
directions: In a large punch bowl, mix cranberry juice cocktail, lemonade concentrate, orange juice concentrate and water.
Just before serving, add ginger ale.
Garnish with lemon and orange slices. Makes 36 (4 ounce) servings.

title: fresh vegetable lasagna
directions: Stir-fry vegetables 5 to 15 minutes.
Mix cheeses.
Place 1/2 of noodles in a 10 1/2 x 15-inch greased pan.
Add half of vegetables, tomato pieces and puree, then 1/2 of cheeses. Repeat.
Cover pan with foil.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour (approximately).
Let stand 1/2 hour.

title: ice cream
directions: Combine all ingredients and put in ice cream freezer.
Add ice and lots of rock salt.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Cook sugar, margarine, cream and vanilla until it forms a soft ball in cold water, then you add peanut butter and Marshmallow Creme and beat.
Pour into greased 11 1/2 x 7 1/2 x 7/8-inch pan. Set in refrigerator until cold.

title: granola cookies
directions: Combine the granola, flour, cinnamon and salt; set aside. Beat 4 egg yolks and then add the water and honey.
Combine the dry and wet ingredients and mix well.
Beat 4 egg whites until stiff and fold into the batter.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: hopscotch
directions: Melt peanut butter and butterscotch pieces in a double boiler over (not boiling) water, stirring until blended.

title: rachel angel's grated apple pie
directions: Melt margarine.
Beat with sugar and egg.
Add apples and spice.
Bake in an unbaked frozen pie shell at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes.
Use Cool Whip or ice cream on slices.

title: gooba
directions: Rinse barley 3 times; parboil 1 1/2 hours, then rinse and drain.
Saute onions until clear in margarine.
Add mushrooms to onions; saute until mushrooms are tender.
Combine onions, mushrooms, barley and chicken stock.
Pour into greased baking dish.
Sprinkle with garlic powder.
Bake at 350° for 3/4 hour.

title: spanish pork chops and rice
directions: Brown chops in oil over medium-high heat for about 8 minutes. Remove.
Add onions and green pepper; cover and cook 3 minutes. Add tomato, garlic, spices, salt and rice; stir 1 minute.
Add stock; cover and simmer 5 minutes.
Add chops and any accumulated juices.
Cover and cook until rice is done and chops are cooked through, about 20 minutes.
Sprinkle with olives and parsley.

title: russian cream
directions: Heat cream with sugar; soak gelatin in cold water; combine with hot cream.
Cool until slightly thickened.
Whip sour cream and vanilla and combine as first mixture congeals.
Pour into ring mold.
Chill until firm.

title: hot artichoke dip
directions: Combine all ingredients, except chips, in a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Bake at 300° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Serve hot with chips.

title: swiss chocolate cake
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine chocolate chips and water, melt.
Sift together flour, baking soda and salt; set aside. Blend sugar, butter and vanilla.
Beat in eggs, one at a time. Blend in melted chocolate.
Stir in alternately flour mixture and buttermilk.
Pour into 2 greased and floured 9 or 10-inch pans. Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until tested done.

title: peanut blossoms
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Sift together flour, baking soda and salt; set aside.
Cream together shortening and peanut butter. Add sugar and brown sugar; cream well.
Add egg, milk and vanilla; beat well.
Blend in dry ingredients.
Shape by teaspoonful into balls.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 375° for 8 minutes. Remove promptly.
Place unwrapped Hershey Kiss in center of each cookie until cookie cracks.
Return to oven for 3 minutes.

title: harvard beets
directions: Drain beets. Save liquid. Mix sugar, cornstarch and salt. Add vinegar and beet liquid. Cook, stirring constantly, until thick and clear. Add beets and oleo. Heat.

title: date squares
directions: Pour 1 cup boiling water over the dates and soda.
Let stand at least 1/2 hour or more.
Blend the margarine, sugar, egg, vanilla, baking powder and salt. Add dates and water.
Pour into a greased 8 x 8-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: pineapple cheese ball
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Add well drained pineapple and rest of ingredients.
Wrap in wax paper to chill.
Reserve some of the nuts to roll ball in after it has chilled.

title: west indies salad
directions: Spread half of the onion on bottom of large mixing bowl. Spread crab meat on top of onion.
Spread the remaining onion on top of crab meat.
Pour oil on mixture to be followed by vinegar and ice water.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Marinate for 12 hours. Salad should be tossed, not stirred.

title: crab dip
directions: Mix together ingredients except for small amount of cheese to sprinkle on top.
Put mixture into small baking container and sprinkle top with remaining cheese.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until bubbling.

title: cheesecake
directions: Mix melted butter and vanilla wafer crumbs.
Form crust in pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
While crust is cooking, mix eggs, cream cheese, granulated sugar and lemon juice.
Fill cooked crust with filling.
Return to oven for 75 minutes (1 hour and 15 minutes).
Turn off oven; mix sour cream and powdered sugar.
Pour over cheesecake and return to cooling oven.
Remove in 15 minutes.

title: chicken - spiced beef casserole
directions: Grease 8 -inch or 9-inch square casserole.
Place chicken breasts in bottom of casserole.
Top each breast with 4 slices of sandwich beef.
Mix soup, sour cream, mushrooms and almonds; pour over chicken and beef.
Bake uncovered at 325° for one hour.

title: cherry yum-yum
directions: Melt margarine; mix with cracker crumbs.
Whip Dream Whip with sugar, vanilla, 3/4 cup milk and cream cheese.
In a 2-quart Pyrex dish, put a layer of crumb mixture, 1/2 of the Dream Whip mixture and cherry pie filling.
Add rest of the Dream Whip mixture; place layer of crumbs on top.
Chill.
Makes 12 servings.

title: taffy apple salad
directions: Mix pineapple tidbits and marshmallows together; cover and refrigerate.
Stir together vinegar, sugar, egg and flour and cook until thick.
Let dressing mixture cool.
Add diced apples to large mixing bowl.
Stir in pineapple mixture and cooled dressing. Stir in peanuts and Cool Whip.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Cook until the peanuts pop open. Add 1/2 teaspoon of baking soda.
Stir and pour on a buttered dish or greased tinfoil.
When cool, break into pieces.

title: crock-pot chicken and rice casserole
directions: Mix soups and rice in crock-pot.
Place chicken on top of mixture and add chopped celery.
Cook for 3 hours on high or 4 hours on low.
Serves 4.

title: buffet potatoes
directions: Set hash browns aside to thaw.
Leaving a handful of cheese to top casserole, stir all remaining ingredients together in a large bowl.
Stir in hash browns until all are coated.
Pour into a 2 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Top with remaining cheese and chives. Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: karen's pasta salad
directions: Cook noodles as directed on package, then add to next seven ingredients.
Mix Good Seasons Italian dressing as directed on package and add garlic.
Toss salad and dressing and marinate overnight.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Combine wet ingredients.
Mix together.
Bake in two loaf pans until done at 350°.

title: strawberry tango
directions: Combine sour cream, brown sugar and amaretto; mix well. Fold in sliced strawberries. Spoon in serving dish; garnish with whole berries.

title: tortilla roll-ups
directions: Mix cheese and chiles.
Spread over tortillas.
Roll up and cut into bite size pieces.
Chill 2 hours.
Serve with picante sauce (mild).

title: acadiana seafood gumbo
directions: Saute celery, bell pepper and garlic in cooking oil.
Add smothered okra, Ro-Tel tomatoes, seasoning, bay leaf, Worcestershire sauce and bouillon mixture into a large pot.
Then stir in seafood.
Cook for about 1 to 1 1/2 hours, until seafood is tender.
If not spicy enough, add Tabasco sauce to taste.
Add parsley and serve over rice.
Remove bay leaf when cooked.
Serves four to six persons.

title: ashley's grown up punch
directions: Mix directly into punch bowl and serve immediately.
Don't mix ahead or it will go flat.
Raspberries will give a lovely pink tint and add a bit of flavor.

title: picnic beans
directions: In large pan cook and stir ground beef, onion and celery until meat is browned.
Dissolve bouillon cubes in boiling water; stir bouillon and remaining ingredients into meat mixture.
Cover; bake 1 hour and 15 minutes at 375°.
Makes 12 servings.

title: rhubarb crunch
directions: Place rhubarb in greased baking dish.
Combine 1/2 cup sugar, cornstarch and water; cook and stir until thick and clear.
Add vanilla and pour over rhubarb.
Combine remaining ingredients; sprinkle over rhubarb.
Bake in moderate oven (350°) for 40 to 45 minutes.
Serve warm, plain or with whipped cream.

title: pizza dip
directions: Mix sour cream and cream cheese; spread on bottom of large pan.
Spoon sauce on cheese layer.	Top with any or all toppings. Top with cheese.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients together.
Add ground meat, mixing thoroughly.
Form into large ball and place into baking receptacle. Iron skillet works nicely.	Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Enjoy.

title: guacamole dip
directions: Peel and mash avocados; add onion and mix well.
Add other ingredients and mix well.

title: a good casserole dish
directions: Cook together ground beef and onion.
Pour off excess grease. Cook noodles in salt water for 20 minutes; drain.
Heat mushrooms on top of stove.
Combine all ingredients and bake 1 hour at 300°. Put buttered corn flakes on top.

title: baked beans
directions: Combine ingredients in baking dish and add bacon on top.
Bake at 350 degrees for 30 minutes.

title: crunchy fudge sandwiches
directions: Melt butterscotch morsels with peanut butter, stirring until blended (in double boiler).
Stir in Rice Krispies.
Press 1/2 into 8-inch pan.
Chill.
Set remainder aside.

title: spiced tea
directions: Mix all together and store in airtight container.
Use 2 to 3 teaspoons for 1 cup boiling water.

title: beacon hill brownies
directions: Melt chocolate and butter in saucepan over very low heat, stirring constantly.
Cool slightly.
Beat eggs, sugar and vanilla in large mixer bowl on high speed for 10 minutes.
Blend in chocolate mixture on low speed.
Add flour, beating just to blend. Stir in nuts.
Spread in greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes.
(Do not overbake.)
Cool in pan; cut into squares.
Makes 24 to 32.

title: hot lobster ring
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Melt butter.
Stir in flour until blended.
Gradually stir in chicken bouillon or 1 cup bouillon and 1 cup cream.
Add parsley, bread crumbs, egg yolks, lobster meat, salt and pepper.
Whip the egg whites until stiff, but not dry. Fold lightly into the other ingredients.
Bake the lobster mixture in a well oiled 9-inch ring mold until firm, about 20 minutes. Unmold and serve with Mushroom Sauce.

title: easter bunny salad
directions: Put a lettuce leaf on a plate. Put pear half on lettuce leaf, upside down. Add 2 cloves for eyes, 2 almond halves for ears and 1 teaspoon cottage cheese for tail.

title: flaky cake bars
directions: Prepare 1 package 1 layer size yellow cake mix according to package directions.
Pour batter into greased 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Bake at 350° for about 25 minutes, or until done.
Cool.

title: cran raspberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Stir in pineapple, cranberry sauce and wine.
Chill until slightly thick.
Fold in pecans. Place in 2-quart dish.

title: bermuda cheese straws
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Shred cheese in food processor; add flour, caraway seed, pepper, salt, mustard and butter.
Process until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
With processor running, add ice water.
Process until dough forms a ball.

title: apple crisp
directions: Mix apples in 1/4 cup sugar and 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon in a buttered dish.

title: easy roast
directions: Place roast in a heavy roasting pan.
Mix soup, Coke, soup mix and water and pour over roast.
Bake covered at 350° until roast is tender and gravy has thickened.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Cook sausage, onion and thyme in skillet until sausage is browned, stirring to separate meat.
Pour off fat.
Stir in soup, tomatoes and vegetables.
Heat to a boil.
Remove from heat.
Add stuffing.
Mix lightly.
Spoon into 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until hot throughout.
Serves 6.

title: banana bread
directions: Spray loaf pan with nonstick coating.
In large mixing bowl, stir together the flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
In medium mixing bowl, stir together beaten egg whites, banana, sugar, cooking oil and lemon peel.
Add to flour mixture, stirring just until combined.
Fold in nuts.
Pour into prepared pan. Bake at 350° about 50 minutes or until wooden toothpick inserted in middle comes out clean.
Cool in pan for 10 minutes, then remove from pan.

title: caramel banana pie
directions: Cover unopened can of milk with water in a deep boiler.
Bring to a rolling boil for 2 hours and 15 minutes.
Keep adding water to keep can covered.
Let can cool 30 minutes in cool water and open.
Pour over sliced bananas in cooked pie shell.
Cool completely and top with Cool Whip.

title: mom's lo-cal cream cheese pie
directions: Stir cream cheese until soft.
Gradually blend in 1/2 cup milk until mixture is very smooth.
Add remaining milk and pudding mix. Beat slowly with eggbeater for 1 minute.
Pour at once into cooled crust.

title: lemon bars
directions: Make a paste of the oleo, powdered sugar and flour.
Press into a long baking dish; bake for 15 minutes at 325°.
Mix 2 cups sugar, flour, baking powder, eggs, lemon juice and grated rind together.
Pour into hot crust.
Bake for 25 minutes at 350°. Sprinkle powdered sugar on top while hot.

title: baked round steak
directions: Cut round steak into serving pieces and pound flour on both sides.
Brown in skillet and slice onion on top.
Heat mushroom soup in saucepan with 1 can of water, add can of mushrooms.
Put on steak and bake in oven for 3 hours at 300°.

title: hayley's hearty chili
directions: Cook ground beef in a pan.
Season with 1/2 the mount of chili powder, onion powder, salt, and pepper.
Drain fat from ground beef.
Set aside.
In a 3 quart pan, mix in tomato sauce. kidney beans, water, remaining chili powder, onion powder, salt, and black pepper.
Add ground beef.
Mix well.
Add slices of green pepper and onion.
Heat covered on low for 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Remove green pepper and onion before serving.

title: blueberry cake
directions: Cook cake mix as directed on package. Cool.
Combine sour cream, Cool Whip and vanilla.
Frost cake with this mixture.
Put pie filling on top of cake.
Refrigerate.

title: cheese and bacon potato skins
directions: Bake potatoes in a 500° oven for 1 hour or in microwave.
Cut baked potatoes in half and scoop out center, leaving 1/4-inch shell. Deep fry potato skins 3 to
4 minutes.
Drain on paper towel, then season to taste.
Fill potato halves with cheeses. Sprinkle with onion and bacon. Place under broiler 2 to 3 minutes. Top with sour cream.

title: cheese wafers
directions: Cut butter into flour; add cheese and seasonings.
Fold in cereal.
Drop by small rounds on ungreased cookie sheet and flatten with spoon.
Bake at 350° for about 15 minutes.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Mix together; cook at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: eggplant parmigiana
directions: Peel and cut eggplant into 1/4-inch slices.
Dip each slice in eggs, then coat with bread.
In large skillet, heat oil.
Cook eggplant 2 to 3 minutes on each side.
Drain on paper towel. Spread 1/3 cup sauce over bottom of a 13 x 9-inch baking dish. Arrange half of eggplant slices in dish.
Cover with half of sauce, Mozzarella and Parmesan cheeses.
Repeat layers with remaining eggplant, sauce and cheeses.
Cover with foil.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Combine all the ingredients except potato chips.
Top with crushed potato chips.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: crab mousse
directions: Heat soup in medium saucepan, add cream cheese and blend until it disappears.
Dissolve the gelatine packets in the hot water, add to mixture and set aside to cool.
Add the rest of the ingredients into the pot of tomato mixture.
Blend until well mixed.
Turn mixture into a large mold and refrigerate for about 8 hours.

title: chicken taco bake
directions: Mix chicken, soup, enchilada sauce and green chiles.
Line a casserole dish with 1/2 chips.
Pour chicken mix over top. Top with remaining chips and all the cheese. Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: easy peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Place on cookie sheet and flatten with fork.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: bean dip for taco chips
directions: Brown the beef or turkey and drain.
Stir in the salsa, Velveeta
(cut in pieces) and the refried beans.
Stir all together and put in a crock-pot on low for 1 hour, stirring occasionally.
Serve warm on taco chips.

title: oat bran raisin muffins(heart healthy)
directions: Baking Temperature: 425°.
Baking Time: 17 minutes.

title: carolyn's stuffed chicken
directions: Melt margarine and toss stuffing and season mix in pan. Spread 1/2 of stuffing in dish. Top with cut-up chicken.
Mix broth, soup and sour cream and pour over chicken.
Sprinkle remaining stuffing.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: glazed pineapple chicken
directions: Combine all ingredients in bowl.
Pour into Ziploc bag and add chicken to marinade.
Cook chicken on grill.

title: chess pie
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Cream together butter, sugar, cornmeal and flour.
Add eggs, vanilla, lemon juice and milk.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: upside-down german chocolate cake
directions: Use a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Spread chopped nuts in bottom of a greased pan.
Sprinkle coconut on top of nuts.
Mix cake mix by directions on box and spread over nuts and coconut.
Melt margarine and mix with cream cheese and sugar.
Spread this over cake mixture and bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: pismo chicken
directions: Brown chicken slowly in melted butter.
Add salt and pepper and arrange in shallow baking dish.
Brown mushrooms in drippings.
Add remaining ingredients and heat to boiling.
Pour over chicken. Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 30 minutes, then uncover and continue baking for 25 to 30 minutes or until done.
Serves 6.

title: eye of round roast
directions: Heat oven to 250°.
Prepare eye of round and place on rack over water.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Arrange sliced garlic, onion and bay leaves over roast.
(I hold in place with toothpicks.) Cover roast with foil; seal edges around pan.
Bake for 5 hours. Cool completely for easy slicing for sandwiches.
Strain broth for cooking noodles or making gravy.
Excellent!

title: taco dip
directions: Mix together the sour cream and dry taco mix.
Spread onto a jelly roll pan.
Layer on lettuce, onions, tomato and black olives.
Cover for 1 hour in fridge.
Dip with chips.

title: tanis' supreme corn casserole
directions: Drain liquid from corn to just cover the corn about 1/4 inch. Mix remaining ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: adobong carne(beef in soy and vinegar sauce)
directions: Combine all ingredients and let stand overnight.
Put in a pot and bring to a boil.
Let simmer for an hour or until beef is tender.
Serve hot.

title: kraft dinner casserole
directions: Brown ground beef with salt and pepper (to taste) and chopped onion.
Drain.
Cook macaroni from the Kraft dinner.
Add cooked macaroni, stewed tomatoes and Kraft dinner cheese packet to ground beef mixture.
Stir together well.
Tear up several slices of cheese and put into mixture.
Stir again.
Put into casserole dish (1 1/2-quart) and cover with sliced cheese.
Bake in covered casserole dish for 45 minutes in 350° oven.

title: meat loaf
directions: Beat eggs lightly in large bowl; add other ingredients in order given.
Bake in loaf pan
1 hour at 350°.

title: oatmeal apple raisin muffins
directions: Beat eggs; stir in remaining ingredients, mixing just until moist.
Pour into 12 greased muffin cups about 3/4 full.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Mix thoroughly.
Bake approximately 20 minutes at 350°.

title: old-fashioned bread pudding
directions: Cover raisins with brandy; set aside. Spread 1 1/2 teaspoons butter on each bread slice. Cut bread into 1-inch cubes; set aside. Combine brown sugar, cinnamon and allspice; reserve 3 tablespoons of this mixture. Toss bread cubes with remaining sugar mixture. Place 1/2 of bread cube mixture in a lightly greased 1 1/2-quart casserole. Drain raisins; place half of raisins over cube mixture. Repeat layers. Combine eggs, salt and vanilla in medium bowl. Beat at medium speed of electric mixer 1 minute. Gradually stir in milk. Pour mixture in casserole dish. Let stand 5 minutes. Sprinkle with reserved sugar mixture. Bake at 325° for 45 to 50 minutes. Serve warm. Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: green chili stewlos alamos, new mexico
directions: Brown pork in small amount of oil using salt, pepper and garlic to taste.
While meat is browning, empty large can of tomatoes in 4 qt. pan.
Cup up fine with juice or use hands to pulverise.
Add green chili to tomatoes and simmer.
Add browned meat mixture and stir well.
Simmer 1/2 hour.

title: banana cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter; add eggs, milk, bananas and vanilla. Sift together flour, soda, baking powder and salt.
Mix both dry and wet ingredients together.
Bake in 2
layer cake pans at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.
Cake is done when straw comes out clean from the middle.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs.
Add oil, sugar, zucchini and vanilla.
Mix lightly, but well.
Mix dry ingredients and add to egg mixture. Add nuts. Bake in
2 loaf pans for 1 hour at 325°.

title: pecan cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve orange and cherry gelatin in hot water; add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Prepare 6-cup ring mold, or any container or bowl with vegetable spray.
Pour in container and chill.
For ring mold, add 1 envelope Knox gelatine.
You may double or triple recipe.

title: goodies (bark candy)
directions: Mix all ingredients, except bark. Melt bark in microwave according to package directions and mix with other ingredients. Drop small pieces on wax paper. Makes approximately 12 dozen candies.

title: mulligatawny soup
directions: In large kettle cook onion in oil until tender.
Add hot water, bouillon cubes, vegetables, salt, pepper and barley.
Cook for about 45 minutes.

title: creamere pound cake
directions: Cream butter, cream cheese and sugar until light and fluffy. Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each.
Add flour gradually. Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours in 10-inch tube pan.
(Ingredients must be at room temperature.)

title: broccoli-cauliflower salad
directions: Wash, drain and chop broccoli and cauliflower into bite size pieces.
Add onion.
Fry, drain and crumble bacon; add to broccoli, cauliflower and onion.

title: chili-mac skillet
directions: In large skillet, brown meat with onions.
Drain off fat.
Stir in kidney beans, tomato sauce, undrained tomatoes, uncooked macaroni, green pepper, water, chili powder and garlic salt.
Bring to boil; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer for 20 minutes, stirring often.
Remove skillet from heat.
Sprinkle meat mixture with Monterey Jack or Cheddar cheese (both can be used).
Cover and let stand for 2 minutes or until cheese melts.
Makes 6 servings.

title: chicken broccoli orientale
directions: Cook chicken in oil until browned.
Add onion and pepper. Cook 5 minutes or until vegetables are tender-crisp.
Stir in soup, water and soy sauce.
Heat to boiling; reduce heat to low, cover and simmer for 5 minutes or until vegetables are tender. Serve over rice or noodles.
Serves 4.

title: oniony dinner rolls
directions: Measure warm water into large bowl.
Sprinkle in yeast.
Stir to dissolve.
Add sugar, molasses and onion soup.
Add egg and 3 cups flour.
Beat well.
Add shortening and remaining flour.
Beat well.
On lightly floured board, knead bread until smooth.
Cover and let rise in warm place until double in bulk, about 45 minutes. Punch down.
Shape into rolls.
Cover; let rise until doubled, about 45 minutes.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Brush tops lightly with melted butter.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix thoroughly.
Simmer until butter is melted.
Ready to use on all barbecue meats.
Double quantities for a crowd.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Use 1/2 the butter to dot the bottom of a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Mix well pineapple, sugar and flour; pour over butter in casserole dish.
Dot with remaining butter.
Place crumbs over everything.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Place Doritos in bottom of casserole.
Add tuna (do not drain).
In separate bowl, mix all other ingredients and pour over tuna.
Bake in 325° oven for 45 minutes.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Preheat oven at 325°.
Beat eggs until light.
Add oil, sugar, zucchini and nuts; if desired.
Combine flour, baking soda, salt, cinnamon and baking powder.
Add egg mixture and mix until well blended.
Pour batter in loaf pans.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour. Makes 3 loaves.

title: acini de pepe salad
directions: Cook macaroni in boiling salted water.
Drain and rinse in cold water.
Place in large bowl.
Mix juice from oranges and pineapple (reserve fruit) with sugar, salt, flour and eggs in saucepan.
Cook mixture until thick, stirring constantly.
Pour mixture over macaroni and refrigerate overnight.
Next day, add oranges, pineapple and Cool Whip.
Garnish with cherries.

title: *curried shrimp in cream sauce
directions: In a medium sized pan, cook onion in butter until tender, but not brown.
Add undiluted soup and stir until smooth.
Add sour cream and curry powder.
Thicken with 2 tablespoons cornstarch. Heat to boiling point; add shrimp.
Serve over rice.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: lasagne
directions: Cook noodles in boiling, salted water following package directions; drain.
Add oregano to spaghetti sauce.
