In greased 10 x 6 x 1 1/2-inch baking dish, make layers in order of half of the noodles, cottage cheese, Mozzarella cheese slices and spaghetti sauce.
Repeat.
Bake in moderate oven at about 375° for 30 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: honey mustard chicken
directions: Stir salad dressing, mustard and honey together.
Place chicken on grill on rack of broiler pan.
Brush with 1/2 of sauce.
Grill or broil 8 to 10 minutes.
Turn and brush with remaining sauce. Continue grilling or broiling 8 to 10 minutes or until tender. Serves 4.

title: seafoam salad
directions: Drain pears; save juice.
Dissolve jello in 1 cup hot pear juice (add water to make 1 cup if need be).
Mash cream cheese and pears.
Add to jello.
Refrigerate until set.
Add Cool Whip and mix well.
Return to refrigerator until ready to serve.

title: easy fudge
directions: Mix ingredients together in boiler.
Heat until hot.
Mix in nuts and pour into buttered cake pan.
Let cool and cut into squares.

title: grandma white's pecan pie
directions: Mix flour thoroughly with sugar.
Beat eggs lightly; add butter, salt and sugar mixture.
Mix. Add syrup and nuts.
Mix well.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake in 450° oven 10 minutes, then reduce heat to 350°.
Bake 50 minutes more.

title: lemon cheese dessert
directions: Mix cream cheese until soft.
Add pudding mix and cold milk. Beat 2 minutes at medium speed until smooth and creamy.
Chill 5 minutes.
Spoon into dessert shells (shortcakes).
Top with whipped cream.

title: banana bread
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder, salt and baking soda. Mash bananas with rotary beater or fork.
Add lemon juice and mix. Cream shortening and sugar with electric mixer at medium speed or with spoon.
Add eggs and beat thoroughly until very light and fluffy (4 minutes beating in all).
Add sifted dry ingredients alternately with milk and bananas.
Beat after each addition. Cook in oven at 350° for 1 hour.
Makes 2 loaves (pan size 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch).
Cool 10 minutes, then remove from pan.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Slice steak into thin strips. Brown steak in butter in a large skillet.
Remove from pan. Saute mushrooms and onions in pan drippings in skillet. Stir in steak and broth, heating to boiling point.
Combine flour and sour cream in a small bowl, blending well.
Add sour cream mixture to steak, blending well. Season with salt and pepper.
Cook over low heat until heated through, stirring occasionally. Serve over buttered noodles.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix eggs, sugar, cooking oil, grated zucchini and vanilla. Combine remaining ingredients and add to mixture.
Bake in greased loaf pans at 350° for 1 hour.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: graham cracker brownies
directions: Roll graham crackers fine; add milk, chocolate chips, nuts and vanilla.
Spread in a well-greased pan (10 x 14 x 2-inch).
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: grilled stuffed tomatoes
directions: Preheat the broiler. Cut each tomato into 4 slices (discard cores). Arrange slices on a baking sheet.

title: ground beef quiches
directions: Cook beef, garlic powder and black pepper until beef is done; drain and set aside. Combine biscuit mix and cornmeal in a bowl. Cut in butter. Add enough water to form a soft dough. Press onto bottom and sides of miniature muffin pans. Place a teaspoon of beef mixture into each shell.

title: slush
directions: Stir water and sugar well.
Add orange juice, lemonade and whiskey.
Freeze for 24 hours.
To serve, add 2 tablespoons to 7-Up and ice.

title: c.b.'s quintessential steak
directions: Chop the horns off, chop the tail off and slide it across the grill.

title: squash muffins
directions: Beat egg in medium mixing bowl; add milk and squash.
Combine dry ingredients; stir into squash mixture.
Stir in oil.
Spray muffin tins with Pam and heat at 350° until hot.
Spoon batter into tins, filling cups 2/3 full.
Bake at 350° about 20 minutes or until done and brown.
Yields about 1 dozen.

title: salmon-caviar mousse
directions: Mix gelatin with 1/4 cup cold water. Let stand for 5 minutes. Add 1/2 cup hot water and stir until dissolved.

Refrigerate until chilled. In small bowl, beat cream until peaks form; set aside. In large bowl, beat salmon, mayonnaise, dill weed, paprika, hot pepper sauce and gelatin mixture until smooth. Fold in caviar, then fold in cream. Spoon into greased mold. Cover and refrigerate for 3 hours or until firm. Unmold and serve.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix well. Bake, uncovered, in 350° oven until hot and bubbly (about 25 to 30 minutes). Top with 1 can onion rings. Heat until brown.

title: herbed tomatoes
directions: Cut tomatoes into 1/2-inch slices.
Arrange on lettuce leaves and sprinkle with basil and sugar.

title: elegant potato casserole
directions: Cook potatoes; cool and shred.
Heat 1/4 cup butter or margarine with green onions and soup.
Then blend in sour cream and grated cheese.
Stir in potatoes.
Place in buttered 2 1/2-quart casserole.
Mix corn flakes with 2 tablespoons melted butter and sprinkle on top.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Garnish with parsley. Serves 6.

title: elegant crab soup
directions: Saute onion in butter until tender.
Add flour and cook 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Add crab meat (don't break it up), salt, pepper and milk.
Cook over low heat 15 minutes.
Add cream and scotch.
Stir well.
Warm.
Sprinkle with parsley before serving.
Makes 8 cups.

title: party casserole
directions: Add egg noodles and salt to rapidly boiling water, stirring occasionally until tender; drain.
Saute onion in butter or margarine until tender, stir in green pepper and cook 1 minute longer.
In large bowl blend mushroom soup, sour cream, salt and pepper, chicken, ham, olives, pimentos and artichoke hearts.
Mix gently, spoon into buttered 3-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with buttered crumbs.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour, serve with grated Parmesan cheese.

title: walnut hermits
directions: Cream together shortening, brown sugar and eggs.
Add the dry ingredients and milk to creamed mixture.
Add walnuts, raisins and dates.
Drop on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: lemon cake pie
directions: Combine sugar, flour, salt, butter and egg yolks.
Beat until smooth.
Add lemon juice and rind.
Add milk slowly.
Beat egg whites stiff but not dry.
Fold in.
Bake pie shell 5 minutes. Pour in filling.
Bake 40 minutes or until firm in 350° oven.
Pie will have a cake-like topping.

title: onion casserole
directions: Dice onions in fairly large chunks and boil in salted water for about 10 minutes.
Drain and put into a quart casserole dish. Pour one small can (or less) of evaporated milk over onions. Cover generously with grated cheese and bake at 325° until it bubbles and cheese melts.
If too much liquid remains, cook a little longer.

title: hot crab hors d'oeuvres
directions: Mix above and place in pie plate.
Cover with paprika.
Bake at 350° for approximately 15 minutes or until hot and bubbly. Serve hot with crackers.

title: coconut pound cake
directions: Cream the margarine and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Sift dry ingredients together and add alternately with sour cream. Add vanilla flavoring.
Fold in thawed coconut.
Bake in well-greased and floured tube pan for 1 hour and 45 minutes at 325°.

title: brownies deluxe
directions: Melt in top of double boiler 2 sticks of oleo and 4 squares baking chocolate.
In mixing bowl, beat eggs.
Add sugar gradually. Add flour and baking powder.
Add chocolate mixture.
Do not wash boiler.
Add 2 teaspoons vanilla and nut meats.
Spread in large pan.
Bake at 300° for 1/2 hour (will pull away from edge slightly).

title: big pot
directions: Cover ham hocks with water; cook slowly until tender.
Debone. Cook chicken in same sauce ham hocks were cooked, adding enough water to cover chicken if needed.
Debone when done. Put chicken and ham hocks back into broth with 1 cup of water. Bring to a boil.
Add all 3 flavors of rice; cook down low and enjoy.

title: au gratin potatoes
directions: Cook and peel potatoes; cube.
Heat butter with soup.
Blend in sour cream, onions and cheese.
Stir in potato cubes.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes.
Pour into buttered casserole dish and top with crushed potato chips.

title: caramel frosting
directions: Melt
butter
or
margarine
in saucepan over low heat. Stir in	brown
sugar
and salt. Cook 2 minutes over low heat, stirring constantly.
Add
milk
and
stir	constantly
until mixture comes
to a boil.
Remove from heat. Stir in powdered sugar.
Add 1/2
teaspoon
vanilla
and mix well.
Stir until frosting	starts to
"crinkle" as it cools.
Pour immediately onto	warm cake; spread quickly. This frosting sets up fast so work very quickly.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix together all ingredients and bake for 20 minutes at 400°.

title: cranberry mold
directions: You will also need a 13 x 9 x 2-inch serving container.

title: chocolate mousse brownies
directions: In large microwave-safe bowl, melt butter and chocolate chips on High for 90 seconds, stirring every 30 seconds.
Stir in remaining ingredients (except pecans).
Beat until smooth.
Stir in pecans.
Spread into buttered 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Set aside.

title: jean's potato casserole
directions: Mix together the first 9 ingredients.
Top with the crushed cornflakes. Bake at 350° for 1 hour in 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: date candy
directions: Mix sugar, milk and dates.
Cook to creamy consistency. Remove from heat and add nuts.
Beat until thick and pour into buttered dish.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Brown sausage, onion, jalapeno peppers, salt and pepper. Drain.
Mix cornmeal, eggs, salt, onion, milk and creamed corn. Pour 1/2 batter into greased baking dish.
Add meat, then cheese. Top with rest of batter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: zucchini pilaf
directions: Saute zucchini in oil and garlic.
Remove from pan.
Add rice and brown in butter.
Place rice in a saucepan; add soup stock and white wine.
Bring to boil without lid.
Add salt.
Place zucchini on top of rice.
Do not stir.
Cover and simmer.
Add cheese when serving.

title: cherry delight salad
directions: Put Cool Whip in bowl.
Add pineapple, filling, milk and nuts. Stir gently until mixed.
Cool in refrigerator about 1 hour.

title: carrot casserole
directions: Brown onion in butter in skillet.
Add cream of celery soup. Cook carrots separately until almost tender.
Mix carrots with onion and soup mixture in baking dish.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 20 minutes, or until cheese is melted.
Good.

title: crown jewel jello
directions: Mix crumbs, sugar and melted butter.
Press on bottom and up sides of buttered 9-inch spring-form pan.
Chill

title: yellow squash casserole
directions: Drain and save water from cooked squash. Add cheese; stir as it melts. Stir in stuffing, picante, onion and eggs. Add a little water from squash if it seems dry. Put in greased casserole. Sprinkle with bread crumbs. Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes. Serves 6 to 8.

title: red rice
directions: Fry sausages or franks in oil; add tomato sauce.
Add all of the seasonings and spices.
Let sauce boil.
Wash rice and pour off water.
Pour sauce over the rice.

title: corned beef hash
directions: Mix all ingredients together except milk.
Heat milk and pour it on the mixture.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix sausage, stuffing and water.
Add onion, eggs and baking powder.
Roll into balls and bake them for 15 minutes, covered, at 325°.
Uncover, raise heat to 350° and bake for 25 more minutes.

title: orange cinnamon rolls
directions: Using a large bowl, mix 1 1/2 cups flour, 1/2 cup sugar, salt, orange peel and undissolved yeast.
Combine milk, water, orange juice and 1/2 cup butter; heat until warm.
Gradually add to dry mixture.
Beat for 2 minutes at medium speed.
Add egg and 1/2 cup flour to make thick batter; beat 2 minutes on high.
Stir in enough additional flour to make soft dough.
Turn out on pastry cloth; knead until smooth.
Put in greased bowl, turning to grease top.
Cover with towel; let rise until double.

title: crab dip
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Chill 2 hours before serving.
Serve with crackers, chips or raw vegetables.
Makes 2 cups.

title: creme de menthe bars
directions: Mix and pat into 10 x 15 jelly roll pan or 9 x 13 pan.
Bake at 350° for 20-25 minutes.
Let cool.

title: squash fritters
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Drop by tablespoon onto oiled griddle and cook on medium heat until lightly browned.
Turn and brown other side.
Serve immediately.

title: pecan cups
directions: Combine 1 stick margarine and cheese; melt. Combine with flour. Chill mixture for about 1 hour; shape into cups to fit miniature muffin

tins that have been sprayed with Baker's Joy cooking spray. Beat brown sugar, 3 tablespoons margarine, vanilla and egg together; add nuts. Fill cups about 2/3 full. Bake at 350° to 375° for approximately 12 minutes. You might need to cook a little longer until lightly browned, depending on the temperature of your oven.

title: cranberry fluff
directions: Mix cranberries, marshmallows and sugar and chill overnight. Next day before serving, add the remaining ingredients except for whipping cream.
Whip the cream and fold into the mixture, creating the Fluff.
Serve in a crystal bowl.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: broiled tomato halves
directions: Cut tomatoes in half.
Sprinkle with salt, pepper and basil. Top with buttered bread crumbs, then Parmesan cheese.
Broil for 3 to 5 minutes.

title: maple apple ice cream punch
directions: Combine the first 5 ingredients in container or electric blender; blend well.
Pour mixture into punch cups; top each with a scoop of ice cream.
Serves 12 to 16.

title: sticky buns
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle with walnuts and raisins. Thaw dough partially.
Cut each loaf into 8 slices and each slice into 4 pieces.
Line pan in row of pieces.
Mix remaining ingredients together and pour over top of dough pieces.
Let rise until double in size or overnight in refrigerator.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Invert buns onto platter.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix salt, pepper, onion powder, soup, 1/3 c butter and cheese. Place mixture on top of homefries.
Add corn flakes and 1/4 c butter to top.
Bake uncovered in 13 x 9 baking pan for 1 hour.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix hamburger, onion and green pepper.
Cook rice.
Add rice to hamburger mixture; pour tomato sauce over meat loaf.
Cook 1 hour at 350°.
Add tomato juice while cooking.
Make gravy with the tomato sauce.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Mix softened butter with white sugar, eggs, vanilla and almond.
Add cream cheese.
Add sifted flour.
Beat until smooth.

title: gingerbread
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Grease and flour squash 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Beat all ingredients in large mixer bowl on low speed, scraping bowl constantly for 30 seconds.
Beat on medium speed, scraping bowl occasionally for 3 minutes.
Pour into pan.
Bake until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean, about 50 minutes.
Serve with whipped cream or applesauce, if desired.
Makes 9 servings.

title: texas twist
directions: Cook macaroni; drain and set to side.
Cook hamburger meat; drain and set to side.
In big pot, mix all ingredients and cook to just a boil.
Then it's done.
Just serve and eat!

title: garlic shrimp and pasta
directions: Mix cornstarch and broth, set aside.
In a skillet or medium-high heat, heat oil.
Cook shrimp, garlic and pepper until shrimp turns pink, stirring often.
Set aside.
Add parsley and lemon juice.
Stir in cornstarch mixture and add.
Cook mixture to a boil and thicken, stirring often.
Return to shrimp pan.
Heat through.
Toss with pasta.
Serves 6.

title: broccoli quiche(for nonfat diets)
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray quiche dish with Pam or canola oil cooking spray.
Bake for 45 minutes.

title: coconut pecan frosting
directions: Melt together milk, sugar, yolks, vanilla and margarine.
Stir; cook until thickened.
Add coconut and pecans as desired.

title: pasta salad
directions: Double the dressing if it is too dry.

title: apple crunch
directions: Place apples (cut into pieces); mix water and cinnamon and pour over apples.
Mix brown sugar, butter and flour until blended well.
Sprinkle over apples.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: lasagne
directions: Brown sausage and ground chuck. Add sauce. Boil lasagne noodles. Mix egg in cottage cheese. Layer noodles, meat sauce, Parmesan cheese, cottage cheese and Mozzarella cheese. Cook 1 hour in 350° oven.

title: pizza snack
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Crumble, fry and drain sausage. Combine with all ingredients, except biscuits.
Separate each biscuit into 3 pizza rounds.
Spread each with meat mixture and place on cookie sheet.
Bake for 10 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: strawberry scones
directions: In large bowl, stir together flour, sugar, baking powder, soda and salt.
Cut butter into flour mixture until coarse crumbs form. Stir in strawberries.
Add buttermilk and mix with fork just until dough is moistened.
Gather dough into a ball and roll or pat into a 3/4-inch thick circle.
Cut into hearts (approximately 12) and place on greased baking sheet 1 1/2-inches apart.
Brush tops of scones with cream.
Place on bottom rack of a 400° oven for 14 minutes.
Makes 1 dozen.

title: chocolate chip pie
directions: Mix in the order it comes (except pie shells).
Pour into pie shells.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: uncle george's cranberry chutney
directions: In large kettle over medium heat, bring cranberries and water to a boil, reduce heat and simmer 15 minutes.
Remove; add balance of ingredients, then put back on heat for an additional 10 minutes.
Chill and serve as relish for turkey or chicken.

title: cranberry roast pork
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Rub roast with salt and pepper.
Place on rack in a broiler pan.
Bake for 2 hours and 30 minutes to 3 hours or until meat thermometer reaches 175°.
In a saucepan, combine the remaining ingredients and bring to a boil.
Remove the sauce from heat.
About halfway through the baking process, begin to baste the roast with the cranberry mixture.
Repeat every 15 minutes until roast is done.
Serve remaining sauce with sliced roast.

title: sesame chicken(excellent and easy!)
directions: Dredge chicken in flour, salt, pepper and paprika.
Melt margarine and oil in 9 x 13-inch glass dish in the oven.
Put chicken in pan and sprinkle with 1 1/2 tablespoons sesame seed and bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
Turn chicken and add scallions, remaining sesame seed, mushrooms and white wine.
Lower oven to 350° and cook for another 20 minutes.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain the pineapple and oranges, saving the juice.
Combine with the eggs, sugar and flour.
Cook over low heat until thick. Add jello and stir until dissolved.
Cook before adding fruit and marshmallows.
Chill several hours or overnight.
Makes a large salad.

title: jello shots
directions: Following and adding to instructions on package: add 2 cups boiling water to gelatin, stirring about 2 minutes or until dissolved.
Pour liquid into a storage container.
Add 1 cup of cold water and 1 cup of alcoholic beverage.
Stir well and refrigerate
until solid.

title: no cook icing
directions: Combine egg whites, cream of tartar and sugar in large mixing bowl.
Add vanilla and mix.
Add boiling water and beat until stiff at high speed with electric mixer or by hand for approximately 10 minutes or until stiff.
This will ice a large cake.

title: sausage-cornbread bake
directions: Grease 2-quart baking dish.
Brown sausage and onions in skillet and drain well.
Combine eggs, corn meal, milk and oil. Pour 1/2 of corn meal mixture into prepared dish.
Sprinkle with sausage mixture and cheese.
Pour remaining batter over top and bake 30 to 40 minutes at 420°.

title: strawberry pizza
directions: Combine flour and powdered sugar; add butter, mixing well. Pat dough out in a 14-inch pizza pan; bake at 350° for 10 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: tabbouleh with a tang
directions: Prepare couscous according to package directions.
Fluff with a fork.
Halve tomatoes and dice cucumber.
In large bowl, toss together couscous, halved tomatoes, diced cucumber, chopped mint and citrus vinaigrette.
Season with salt, pepper, extra lemon juice and hot pepper sauce to taste, if desired.
Chill.
Makes 4 servings.

title: crock-pot chicken
directions: Place carrots, onions and celery in crock-pot.
Add chicken, chicken broth, water and seasonings.
Cook on low for 8 to 10 hours.
Yields 6 servings.

title: chocolate zucchini cake
directions: In a bowl with an electric mixer, cream together 1 stick of butter, oil and sugar; beat in eggs, 1 at a time, beating well after each addition and beat in buttermilk and 1 teaspoon vanilla. Stir in 1/4 cup cocoa powder, flour, baking soda, cloves, cinnamon and salt until the mixture is just combined and fold in zucchini (patted dry with paper towels), chocolate chips and walnuts.
Pour batter into 2 well buttered 9-inch round cake pans and bake in middle of preheated 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes or Bundt pan for 60 minutes, until tester comes out clean.
Let cool 10 minutes and turn out onto racks and cool completely.

title: mom's biscuits
directions: Combine flours, sugar and baking powder in bowl. Cut in margarine. Add milk and stir lightly. Knead 10 times.
Shape into balls or roll out and cut.
Use greased pan.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Makes 10 to 12 biscuits.

title: green bean delight
directions: Pour green beans into a 9 x 12-inch baking dish.
Mix soup and sour cream.
Pour this over beans and top with Velveeta.
Bake at 350° until cheese bubbles.

title: spinach salad
directions: Cook bacon until crisp.
Cool on paper towel; crumble when cool.
Add the next 4 ingredients to bacon drippings; blend well. Cook on high until mixture boils.
Add sugar if desired.
Remove stems and tear spinach in medium size pieces.
Combine with diced onions in large bowl.
Pour hot dressing over top of spinach; toss lightly.
Sprinkle with grated egg and crumbled bacon.
Serve immediately.

title: barbecue beans
directions: Mix beans, sugar and barbecue sauce in large saucepan.
Cook peppers and onions in microwave about 15 to 20 minutes. Mix with bean mixture.
Add allspice.
Simmer on low heat until hot.
Do not boil.

title: pretzel surprise
directions: Bottom Layer:
Mix pretzels with sugar and melted margarine. Layer in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for 6 minutes.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into lightly greased 8 x 8-inch glass casserole dish.

title: pistachio cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour a Bundt pan.
In a large bowl, combine all ingredients.
Follow cake mix package directions for mixing.
Pour batter into pan and bake for 50 minutes or until cake tests done.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Break spaghetti into 1-inch pieces, if desired, and cook according to package directions. Drain. Rinse with cold water and drain. Combine spaghetti, cucumber and next 3 ingredients. Chill. Serve on lettuce and top with tomato wedges. Yields 10 to 12 servings.

title: slow cook chili
directions: Cook 7 to 8 hours on Number 4 in crock-pot.

title: sweet-sour chicken
directions: Brown chicken in butter in large skillet.
Cover; simmer 35 to 40 minutes.
Remove chicken; set aside.
Drain pineapple, reserving syrup.
Combine sugar, cornstarch and salt in skillet. Gradually stir in vinegar, soy sauce and reserved syrup.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Add pineapple, green pepper, onion and reserved chicken.
Cover and simmer for 5 to 10 minutes.
Serve over rice.
Makes 4 servings.

title: gourmet carrots
directions: Combine last 7 ingredients and beat for 3 minutes.
Pour over carrots and onions.
Let stand in refrigerator 24 hours.
Keeps indefinitely.

title: crab rolls
directions: Saut green pepper and onion until tender.
Add crab and heat through. Set aside to cool.
Beat cream cheese with garlic and onion powder, salt and pepper.
Stir in cheeses and crab mixture.
Beat egg white slightly and mix into crab mixture. Chill several hours.
Separate crescent rolls and place one tablespoon mixture on dough and roll up and seal.
Brush with egg white and bake 375 degrees for 10 to 15 minutes or until browned.

title: easy nacho appetizer spread
directions: On two plates, two 7-inch circles, spread each item in order given in an even layer.
Chill until ready to serve.

title: chicken or beef borscht
directions: Cook chicken until done.
Cut into cubes to be added later. Cook vegetables until done, then add the cooked chicken.
Mix 1 can cream of tomato soup with 1 can of evaporated milk.
Add this to the soup just before serving.

title: easy and basic red (tomato) sauce
directions: Basic Mixture:
In large pan, lightly saute onions and garlic in olive oil.
Add the tomatoes (i.e. whole, crushed and puree); then add allspice, chives and paprika.
Simmer on low heat for several hours (the longer the better).
You may stop here, cool and store (e.g., freeze or refrigerate) for later use or use as directed.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook and drain squash.
Mix and pour in casserole dish greased with butter.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 40 minutes or until top begins to brown.

title: chow mein
directions: Cook celery and onions in 2 tablespoons hot oil for 5 minutes. Add salt, bean sprouts and cook, covered, 5 minutes.
Place on platter.
Fry pork in remaining oil until cooked.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Combine sour cream with cream cheese.
Add celery, onions, salt, lemon juice and red pepper.
Mash 2 cans of shrimp with a fork.
Add to the cheese mixture.
Sprinkle red pepper on top. Mix 1 can of shrimp in whole.

title: lasagna
directions: Fry burger.
Add Ragu in one dish.
Cook lasagna in boiling salted water.
In separate dish mix yogurt and cottage cheese. Then grate cheese.
Grease casserole dish.
Lay a layer of lasagna, then a layer of white mix, layer of cheese, Ragu, then yellow cheese.
Repeat.
Place in oven at 350° for 1 hour.

title: diet slaw(low-fat, low sugar, low salt)
directions: Beat egg; add vinegar, Sweet 'N Low and salt.
Cook until thick (about 1 to 2 minutes). Cool.
Add milk.
Pour over chopped cabbage.

title: shrimp etouffee
directions: In a large pan, melt butter.
Saute diced onion until clear. Add shallots, stirring constantly.
Add shrimp soup; heat and stir.
Add shrimp pieces.
Cook until pink.
Serve over rice and Italian or French bread.

title: chicken diane
directions: Place chicken between sheets of plastic wrap.
Pound slighlty with mallet.
Sprinkle with black pepper.
Heat 1 tablespoon each of oil and butter in large skillet.
Cook chicken over high heat for 4 minutes on each side.
Transfer to platter.
Add chives, lemon juice, parsley and mustard to pan.
Cook 15 seconds, whisking constantly.
Whisk in broth.
Stir until smooth.
Whisk remaining butter and oil.
Pour sauce over chicken.
Serve immediately.

title: sicilian potatoes
directions: Cut potatoes in half.
Coat well with oil.
Put cut side up in greased baking dish.
Mix garlic powder, salt and pepper. Sprinkle potatoes with mixture, along with oregano, cheese and paprika.
Bake at 350° until tender.
Makes 8 servings.

title: crescents
directions: Blend all together.
Roll into fingers and curve into crescent shapes.
Bake on a cookie sheet at 250° for 2 hours.
Take from oven and roll in powdered sugar.
(Can bake for 30 minutes in a 300° to 350° oven.)

title: broccoli rice casserole i
directions: Combine all ingredients in a casserole except broccoli. Put in oven on low heat until butter and cheese have melted and can be blended with other ingredients. Slightly thaw broccoli; leave enough ice in it for moisture. Mix broccoli gently into mixture. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: mom's meat loaf
directions: In large bowl, beat eggs. Add milk, saltines, onion, salt, sage and pepper. Add beef and mix well. Shape into an 8 1/2 x 4 1/2-inch loaf in an ungreased shallow baking pan. Combine remaining ingredients. Spread 3/4 cup of this over meat loaf. Bake at 350° for 60 to 65 minutes until no pink remains. Drain. Let stand 10 minutes before slicing. Serve with remaining sauce. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: potato salad
directions: Dice the potatoes, eggs, pickles, pimento, onion and tomatoes. Toss in the mayonnaise; chill.
Season with the remaining ingredients; taste as you go.

title: apple bread pudding and sauce
directions: Combine eggs, sugar and flour until smooth.
Add milk and blend well.
Set custard in refrigerator.
Butter 11 x 7 x 1 3/4-inch pan and line bottom with the sliced bread.
Cover with 1/2 chopped apples and raisins and 1/3 of custard.
Repeat for second layer.
Top with remaining bread and custard.
Drizzle melted oleo over top.
Bake at 375° for 45 to 60 minutes until custard is slightly firm.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Combine vegetables and water in large pan; simmer for 15 minutes.
Leave in liquid.
Add soup, milk, margarine and cheese. Heat until cheese melts.
tags: cream of celery soup or broccoli soup

title: mandarin orange cake
directions: Mix first four ingredients.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Mix the last three ingredients to make the frosting.

title: applesauce salad
directions: Add cinnamon candy to 2 cups boiling water to dissolve.
Add jello; stir to dissolve.
Add applesauce.
Chill.
Makes 4 to 6 servings

title: general glover cheese spread
directions: Combine all ingredients and beat with mixer on low speed until well blended.
Serve with crackers.

title: cheese dip
directions: Mix margarine and flour.
Mix in all other ingredients.
Cook over low heat until thick.
(If dip gets too thick, add water.) Serve warm with chips.

title: fresh corn chowder
directions: Cut corn off cob.
In saucepan, combine corn, onion, 1/2 cup water and 1/2 teaspoon salt.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat.
Cover and simmer about 15 minutes or until corn is barely done; stir occasionally.
Stir in 3 1/2 cups milk, butter, salt and pepper, combining remaining milk and flour mixture to corn.
Cook and stir until thick and bubbly.
Slowly stir in about 1 cup of the hot mixture into beaten egg.
Return to hot mixture in saucepan.
Cook over low heat 2 more minutes.
Stir.
Do not boil.
Serves 6.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain and mix juice from fruit and slice bananas into it.
Let set for about 10 minutes.
Remove bananas.
Mix juice with pudding and cook over low heat until thick.
Cool mixture and mix all together.

title: white chilli
directions: Combine beans, broth, garlic and onion.
Cook until tender. You may need to add more liquid.
Add chillies and spices to bean mixture.
Add diced chicken and simmer at least 1 hour.
Serve topped with grated cheese.
Offer other garnishes such as sour cream, ripe olives, chopped tomatoes, tortilla chips, salsa and guacamole.
Serve with wedge of crusty cornbread.

title: leg of lamb with artichokes
directions: Rub cut edges of lamb with 1 clove of garlic; sprinkle with juice of 1/2 lemon.
Roll lamb; tie at 1 1/2-inch intervals.
Cut slits in lamb; insert slivers of 1 clove of garlic.
Rub with remaining lemon juice, oregano, salt and pepper.
Place in roasting pan.
Roast at 400° for 30 minutes.
Reduce oven temperature to 350°.
Roast to 130° on meat thermometer, basting frequently with pan drippings.
Skim drippings.
Add tomato sauce, water and lemon slices.
Roast for 15 minutes.
Add artichoke hearts.
Roast for 15 minutes or to 150° to 160° on meat thermometer for medium, basting frequently.
Place lamb on heated platter.
Arrange artichoke hearts around lamb.
Strain sauce; serve with lamb.
Yield:
10 servings.

title: diet zucchini bread
directions: Blend all together in a mixer for 3 to 4 minutes.
Add 2 cups grated zucchini.
Pour into Pam sprayed loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: easter fruit salad
directions: Combine Eagle Brand milk, Cool Whip and vanilla. Add canned fruit (drained), cherries and nuts.
Chill overnight.
A nice salad to serve for Christmas or Easter with ham.

title: calico salad
directions: Combine cauliflower, green pepper, celery, carrots and onions in a large bowl.
Mix together remaining ingredients.
Toss mixture with vegetables.
Chill at least 2 hours.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken; debone and cover bottom of casserole with bite size pieces.
Cover with
soup.
In a separate bowl, mix stuffing, milk, chopped onion, eggs, sage and broth.
Pour over chicken. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Very good.

title: oatmeal with raisins and cinnamon
directions: Combine water, salt and raisins in a small saucepan; bring to boil.
Stir in oats and cinnamon.
Reduce heat and simmer for 1 minute or until water is absorbed.
Remove from heat and serve warm.
A serving amount is 1/2 cup at 93 calories.
Diabetic Exchange:
1 starch.

title: chocolate halfway cookies
directions: Cream Crisco.
Add yolks, water and vanilla.
Sift dry ingredients 3 times.
Add to creamed Crisco mixture.
Mix well. Pat out on greased pan and sprinkle chips on top.
Beat egg whites stiff.
Add 1 cup brown sugar slowly.
Beat and spread on top. Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.
Cut when cool.

title: shoo-fly cake
directions: Crumb first four ingredients together in a large bowl.
Set aside 1 1/2 cups crumbs.
To remaining crumb mixture add molasses, water and soda.
Stir until well blended, do not use a mixer. Grease and flour bottom of a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle remaining crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: hot sausage balls
directions: Mix with hands; make into small balls.
Place on cookie sheet and freeze.
When frozen, transfer to a plastic bag.
Remove only the amount needed for baking.
Bake at 325° for 35 minutes.

title: chicken and broccoli casserole
directions: Boil chicken about 20 minutes; add broccoli, 1/2 stick butter, salt and pepper to taste.
Cook broccoli until tender.
Combine soup and mayonnaise.
Add 3 spoons of broth to soup and mayonnaise.
Cut chicken into bite size pieces.
In a casserole dish, layer chicken, broccoli, cheese and soup mixture.
Repeat, this time making cheese come out on top.
Cook 30 minutes at 350°. Serves 6.

title: chocolate pecan pie
directions: In large bowl, stir eggs, corn syrup, chocolate, sugar, butter and vanilla until well blended.
Stir in pecans.
Pour into pastry shell.
Bake in 350°
oven for 50 to 60 minutes, or until knife inserted between center and edge comes out clean.
Cool on wire rack.

title: crock-pot roast
directions: Put all ingredients in crock-pot.
Put in enough water to cover meat.
Cook slow 6 to 8 hours.
Remove meat; slice.
(Serve with gravy.)

title: drop donuts
directions: Mix all ingredients well, then fry in Crisco oil in a deep fryer until golden brown.
Take out and sprinkle with powdered sugar.
It is easiest, if the dough is rolled into little balls before frying.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Cook noodles; drain and return to pot.
Halve pepperoni; add to pasta.
Stir in pizza sauce, 1 cup Mozzarella cheese, mushrooms, olives and Parmesan cheese.
Transfer to 12 x 7-inch baking dish. Top with remaining Mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.

title: hot crab dip
directions: Drain crab meat.
Pour lemon juice over crab meat.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Add to crab meat and juice.
Put in saucepan over low heat, stirring occasionally until creamy.
Serve with any type of crackers.

title: chicken rice casserole
directions: Wash rice; place in 3-quart casserole dish. Mix mushroom soup, onion soup and water. Pour 2/3 of mix over rice.
Place chicken, skin down, on top of rice. Pour remaining mix over chicken. Salt and pepper to taste. Cover casserole with foil. Bake at 400° about 1 hour or until done.

title: pumpkin chiffon pie
directions: Combine the 3/4 cup sugar, cinnamon, nutmeg and salt in a saucepan.
Stir in the milk, canned pumpkin and beaten egg yolks. Add softened gelatin and cook over medium heat until the mixture begins to thicken and boil.
Remove from heat and stir in bourbon. Chill until partially set.
Beat egg whites until soft peaks form.
Slowly add the 2 tablespoons sugar.
Pour into baked pie shell and brown.

title: funnel cakes the amish way
directions: Beat eggs and add milk.
Sift flour, salt, sugar and baking powder.
Add egg and milk.
Beat until smooth.
Hold finger over bottom of funnel.
Pour some batter into hot deep oil (375°) swirling into circles, center to outer edge (3 inches round).
Fry until golden brown.
Drain on brown paper bags.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: spicy blue cheese stuffed celery
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients.
Cut celery into serving size stalks and stuff with mixture.
Sprinkle with parsley and chill until serving time.
Makes about 12.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix crushed pretzels with 3 tablespoons sugar and melted butter.
Pat into a 9 x 13-inch dish and bake at 350°
for 10 minutes.
Cool.

title: sweet and sour smokies
directions: Mix barbecue sauce and grape jelly together; pour over Little Smokies in crock-pot.
Cook on high until hot; turn to low to keep warm.

title: custard pie deluxe
directions: Beat eggs until yolks and whites are well blended.
Add sugar, salt and vanilla.
Slowly add whole milk and evaporated milk, stirring constantly.
Line 9-inch pan with pastry; rub few drops of cold water over pastry.
Add filling; sprinkle top with nutmeg. Bake at 425° for 15 minutes.
Reduce to 325° for 15 to 20 minutes until a knife comes out clean.

title: corn bread
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Add milk, eggs, oil and salt.
Mix well.
Pour into greased 8 x 8-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: pepperoni pizza dip
directions: Beat sour cream, cream cheese, oregano, garlic powder and red pepper.
Spread in a square pan.
Pour pizza sauce on top.
Layer pepperoni, then pepper.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Top with cheese.
Bake another 5 minutes.
Dip with tortilla chips or any kind you like.

title: easy punch
directions: Combine the first 3 ingredients.
Float the sherbet on top. Serves 20 to 25.

title: christmas nut thins
directions: Combine butter and sugar, creaming until light and fluffy. Add eggs, beaten well.
Add flour and salt and mix until smooth. Stir in chopped pecans and vanilla, mixing well.

title: crab balls
directions: Drain, squeeze and pick crab.
Mix everything else and then add crab.
Chill thoroughly. Form into balls.
Keep well chilled until party or serving.
Add a pretzel stick to each ball and pick up by pretzel stick.

title: spanish steak
directions: Pound flour into meat.
In large skillet, brown meat in hot oil.
Drain off excess fat.
Combine remaining ingredients; pour over steak.
Cover and simmer 45 to 50 minutes or until meat is tender.
Makes 6 servings.

title: purple cow
directions: Combine in blender.
Process until smooth and thick.
Serve in tall glasses.

title: apple chicken salad
directions: In a small bowl, combine first 7 ingredients.
Chill until ready to serve.
Place lettuce leaf on a serving plate and top with the chilled chicken salad.
Garnish with alfalfa sprouts if desired.

title: apple crisp
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients until crumbly. Press half in 9-inch square pan, heavily greased. Add diced apples. On stove, combine cornstarch, sugar, water and vanilla. Cook over slow heat until thick and clear. Pour over apples. Top with remaining crumbles. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: white fudge
directions: Stir all ingredients (except nuts) together over low heat until Crisco is dissolved.

Bring to boil and boil 8 to 10 minutes or soft ball stage, stirring constantly over low or medium heat. Remove from heat and beat with mixer until thick enough to pour. Stir in nuts and pour into a greased, oblong pan or baking dish.

title: twix type candy bar
directions: Separate cookies and use only 1 side per candy bar.
Top cookie with thin layer of hand-formed caramel.
Place in pre-lined candy cavity and cap.

title: spaghetti casserole
directions: Set cooked spaghetti aside.
Brown beef and onion; drain.
Set aside.
Melt butter; stir in flour.
Add milk; stir until thick. Add salt and pepper to taste.
Layer ingredients in 13 x 9-inch casserole in this order: spaghetti, meat mix and sausage.
Repeat until ingredients are gone.
Cook in 350° oven until bubbly.

title: oven caramel corn
directions: Heat oven to 200°.
Divide popcorn between 2 ungreased baking pans (13 x 9 x 2-inch).
In saucepan, heat sugar, butter, corn syrup and salt.
Stir occasionally until bubbly around edges. Continue cooking over medium heat for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat; stir in soda until foamy.
Pour over popped corn, stirring until corn is well coated.
Bake 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes.
Makes about 15 cups.

title: ann's pound cake
directions: Mix sugar, margarine and butter well, then add eggs and then add remaining ingredients.
Pour batter into well-greased and floured Bundt pan and bake at 325° until toothpick inserted comes out clean.

title: butterscotch cake
directions: Cook pudding as directed.
Pour into cake mix the oil; mix well.
Spread into 9
x 12-inch pan.
(Can spray with Pam.) Sprinkle chips on top, then sprinkle nuts.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes.

title: orange salad
directions: Mix and set aside until cool the orange jello, hot water and orange juice.
Then add orange sections and can of crushed pineapple (not drained).
Let set in refrigerator.

title: coconut pecan frosting and filling
directions: Combine milk, sugar, egg yolks, butter and vanilla in a saucepan.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until thickened, about 12 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add coconut and pecans.
Beat until cool and of spreading consistency.
Makes 2 2/3 cups or enough for tops of three 8 or 9-inch layers.

title: savory chicken casserole
directions: Spread rice evenly in a greased 4-quart baking dish.
Pour undiluted soup over rice and add water.
Sprinkle onion soup mix over rice mixture.
Lay chicken, skin side up, on top.
Sprinkle salt, pepper and paprika lightly on top.
Cover with lid or foil. Bake at 225° for approximately 2 1/3 to 3 hours or until rice and chicken are cooked to your preference.

title: pepper steak
directions: Cut meat in small pieces and sprinkle with paprika.
Brown meat in butter.
Add garlic and broth.
Cover and simmer 30 minutes.
Stir in onions and green peppers.
Cover and cook 5 minutes more.

title: cherry surprise
directions: Layer cherry pie filling, sprinkled coconut, layer of crushed pineapple, sprinkled coconut.
Sprinkle dry cake mix over top. Cut 1 quarter margarine up over top.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Beat eggs, add sugar, oil and pumpkin.
Mix dry ingredients and add to pumpkin mixture.
Bake in a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan for 40 minutes at 300°.

title: easy hot chocolate mix
directions: Blend and store in sealed container.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.
Add sugar and set aside.
In large bowl put 3 cups flour, add yeast and combine.
Pat egg and oil into flour mixture of yeast; mix well.
Add remaining 3 cups flour and form into a large dough ball.
Put in a well oiled bowl and place a wet kitchen towel over dough and refrigerate.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Drain and rinse shrimp.
Set aside.
Mix all other ingredients until smooth, then stir in shrimp.
Chill overnight for best flavor.

title: creole liver and limas
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cut liver into bite-size pieces and brown with onion and celery in nonstick skillet.
Add remaining ingredients, except limas.
Place lima beans in a 1-quart casserole dish and pour liver mixture over them.
Bake for 45 minutes.
Divide evenly.
Makes 2 servings.

title: crackling bread
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Mix dry ingredients; stir in cracklings.
Add milk; place in greased skillet, preferably iron, and bake for 30 minutes.

title: my best fruit cake
directions: Cream the
butter and sugar together and add eggs.
Add flour and
spices.
In
another bowl, mix all fruit well.
Add nuts and sprinkle
with
1/2 cup of flour.
Add cake mix; mix well.
Dough should drop from spoon slowly.
Pour into 2 tube pans which
have been well greased and floured.
Cook 2 hours in oven that has been preheated to 300°.

title: swedish cheese cake
directions: The milk must be whole milk.
Heat milk to lukewarm.
Make a thin paste of flour with part of the milk.
Soak rennet tablet in water for 3 minutes.
Add paste and rennet to the milk and stir well.
Let stand 40 minutes.
Stir curds, put in cheese cloth and drain off whey.

title: brownies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease bottom only of a 9 x 13-inch pan. In large bowl, combine all brownie ingredients.
Beat 50 strokes by hand.
Spread in greased pan.
Bake 33 to 35 minutes.
Do not overbake.
Cool completely.

title: grandma utterback's sweet rolls
directions: Pour hot milk over sugar, shortening and salt. When lukewarm, add 4 cups flour and the eggs; beat well.
Add yeast dissolved in 1/4 teaspoon sugar. Add more flour until beater will no longer carry it. Turn out on floured board and knead lightly, working in a little more flour as needed.
Put in a greased bowl and let rise to twice its bulk. Work down and let rise again.

title: hot fudge sauce
directions: In heavy saucepan, combine all ingredients.
Stir over low heat until chocolate is melted completely.
Serve warm.
Yield: 1 2/3 cups.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Make paste with cocoa and food coloring.
Cream sugar, shortening and eggs.
Blend well.
Add cocoa and food coloring mixture to creamed shortening and egg mixture.
Combine sifted and measured flour and salt.
Add alternately with buttermilk and vanilla to creamed mixture.
If you use electric mixer, remove blades and fold in vinegar and soda.
Pour batter into three equal portions in 8-inch pans, greased and lined.
Bake in 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: lemon blueberry pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Beat egg yolks in a medium bowl. Stir in sweetened condensed milk, ReaLemon brand juice and rind. Pour into prepared crust. Bake 8 to 10 minutes. Cool. Chill. Top with blueberry filling. Garnish with whipped topping. Refrigerate leftovers.

title: pizzelles
directions: Beat margarine until smooth.
Add sugar gradually and beat well until light.
Add eggs and vanilla or anise.
Beat until light and fluffy, about 10 minutes with electric mixer.
Add flour, baking powder and salt.
Allow to stand until pizzelle iron heats up.
Use paper towel with oil on it and rub over iron. Throw out 1st pizzelles (too much oil absorbed).
Use 1 tablespoon of mixture per mold.
Pick up pizzelles with a fork, put on paper towel to drain oil off and cool.

title: easy peach cobbler
directions: In 1-quart shallow casserole, combine peaches, sugar, 1 tablespoon Bisquick and cinnamon.
In medium bowl, mix remaining 2/3 cup Bisquick with brown sugar.
Cut in margarine until mixture is size of small peas.
Stir in milk until moistened.
Drop by spoonfuls onto peaches.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes or until toothpick inserted into crust comes out clean.
Let stand 5 minutes.

title: yum yum salad
directions: Combine and bring pineapple and water to a boil.
Add jello and stir until dissolved.
Add 2 cups water and fold in Cool Whip. Add Cheddar cheese (grated).
Add chopped pecans. Let sit in refrigerator until firm.
This is a very good salad.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Preheat oven to 375° (350° for glass pan).
In a 3-quart bowl, mix brown sugar, melted shortening, salt and pumpkin pie spice. Add and stir until smooth sweet potatoes, canned milk and egg. Pour into 9-inch pie shell.
Bake 45 minutes or until firm.

title: strawberry squares
directions: Combine butter and 2/3 cup sugar; cream together well.
Add flour, baking powder and coconut.
Blend until a crumbly mixture; press 1/2 into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix cinnamon, 1/2 cup sugar and strawberries together.
Spread over crust.
Sprinkle remaining crumb mixture over berries and press lightly.
Bake at 375° for 35 minutes or until golden.

title: daddy's pickles
directions: Wash and slice cucumbers.
Dissolve 3 cups of pickling lime in 2 gallons of water. (Use large enamel cooker or crock.)
Add sliced cucumbers and let soak for 24 hours, stirring occasionally. After 24 hours, rinse the cucumbers and soak in clear water for 4 more hours - change the water every hour.
Drain cucumbers after 4 hours.

title: bob hall's magic garlic and herb salad dressing
directions: Mix and shake well before serving.

title: taco salad
directions: Cook hamburger and drain.
Add drained kidney beans and warm. Mix lettuce, onions, and tomato and toss with
1/2 bag nacho chips and 1/2 cheese.
Add hamburger and beans and toss; add dressing. Garnish with remaining chips, cheese and tomato.

title: chili cheese ball or log
directions: Mix well and shape into a ball or log.
Roll in chili powder to cover completely.
Chill for 2 days.

title: pepperoni dip
directions: Mix well. Place in 1 loaf Hawaiian bread. Have extra loaf for dipping.

title: fig jam using strawberry jello
directions: Mash the figs well (can use a potato masher).
Cook all three ingredients 20 minutes or until flakes from spoon.	Pour in small quantities in containers.

title: double apple salad
directions: Mix Cool Whip and mayonnaise.
Mix all ingredients and chill.

title: chicken salad
directions: Squeeze juice from celery and discard.
Grind all ingredients and mix with Kraft mayonnaise to desired consistency.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Combine first five ingredients and set aside.
In a small bowl, combine sugar, oil and vinegar.
Pour this over first mixture and chill overnight.

title: sallie's special baked beans
directions: Add some t.l.c. and bake for at least one hour in 325° oven. Serve with your favorite fried chicken, hot dogs, baked ham or whatever.
Um-m-m-m good.

title: t. j. miracle soup
directions: Cut vegetables.
Add soup mix.
Add water until vegetables are covered.
Bring to a boil and boil for 10 minutes.
Cover and lower heat until vegetables are cooked (don't overcook).
Place vegetables in a 5-quart pan or larger to cook.

title: magic chocolate or peanut butter frosting
directions: In top of double boiler, combine milk, water, salt and chocolate or peanut butter, cooking and stirring until thick. Remove from heat; cool.
Stir in vanilla and spread on cake.

title: cream cheese swirled carrot cake
directions: Grease and flour a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Heat oven to 350°.
Beat cream cheese, sugar, vanilla and egg on medium speed until smooth. Reserve.
Prepare mix as directed on package.
Pour into pan. Spoon cream cheese mixture by tablespoonsful in 10 to 12 mounds onto batter, not touching sides of pan.
Cut through batter with knife in S-shaped curves in one continuous motion.
Turn pan 1/4 turn and continue cutting to swirl.
Sprinkle with chopped nuts. Bake 35 to 40 minutes or until cake pulls from sides of pan and springs back when touched lightly in center.
Cool.

title: honey bars
directions: Mix well with hands.
Pat into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Ice, while hot, with:

title: j.r.'s chili
directions: Brown the beef with the onion powder and garlic powder.
Add beans and tomatoes.
Bring to a boil.
Make a paste from the water, chili powder, flour and sugar.
Add 1 teaspoon salt and stir into first mixture.
Simmer until somewhat thickened.

title: hot crab dip
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Blend all but crab meat and 1/2 of Cheddar cheese in mixer.
Stir crab meat in with spoon.
Put into 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Sprinkle the half of cheese on top. Top with paprika.
Bake at 325° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: marinated pork chops or chicken
directions: Marinate pork chops or chicken for 4 to 6 hours or overnight. Bake in oven for 30 minutes at 350° or until done, or cook on grill 30 to 45 minutes or until juices are clear.

title: refried beans
directions: Place beans and onions in a pan with water.
Bring to a boil. Remove from heat; let stand 2 hours, then return to heat and bring to a boil.
Simmer for either 3 hours or until beans are tender. At this point, melt light spread.
Using a potato masher or fork, start mashing beans, adding light spread slowly and combining until desired consistency.

title: aloha ham loaves
directions: (Pimiento-conical shaped sweet pepper.)

title: pink punch
directions: Add boiling water to jello.
Stir until dissolved.
Add cold water and juice to sugar.
Add ginger ale just before serving. Serves 40.

title: tamales de dulce(sweet tamales)
directions: Soak corn husks in warm water overnight to soften.
Pat with paper toweling.
Mix tortilla flour and 2 2/3 cups water; let stand 20 minutes.
Meanwhile, in a large mixer bowl, beat together lard, sugar, salt and cinnamon until fluffy.
Beat in flour mixture until well combined.
Mix raisins, fruit, peels and nuts.

title: hearty hamburger soup
directions: Melt oleo in Dutch oven.
Add onion, carrot and green pepper. Cook until transparent, not brown.
Add beef and cook until crumbly and gray.
Stir in tomato juice, potatoes, salt and pepper.
Cover and simmer (stirring occasionally) until vegetables are tender (20 to 25 minutes).
Combine flour with 1 cup milk and beat until smooth.
Stir into soup mixture.
Add remaining milk to soup and simmer until very hot.
Stir frequently.
Do not boil.
Makes 8 servings.

title: easy chicken pie
directions: Place chicken in baking dish.
Mix chicken broth and celery soup, heating and stirring until smooth. Set aside.
Mix all other ingredients.
Pour over cut up chicken.
Pour flour mixture over it all and bake at 325° for 30 minutes or until brown.

title: savory shrimp stir fry
directions: Toss shrimp into salt and pepper mixture to coat.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In large bowl, measure all ingredients. With mixer at low speed, beat ingredients until well mixed, occasionally scraping bowl.
Drop dough by 2 level tablespoons 3-inches apart onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 15 minutes or until lightly browned.
With pancake turner, immediately remove cookies to wire racks; cool.
Store in tightly covered container. Makes about 2 dozen.

title: black bean soup
directions: Pick over and wash beans.
Soak overnight in cold water to cover then drain.
Add 2 1/2 qts. water, cook over low heat about 1 1/2 hours.
In soup kettle, saute celery and onion in butter until tender. Blend in flour cook 1 minute.
Stir into beans gradually.
Add to this mixture the remaining ingredients.
Simmer about 3-4 hours.
Remove from heat, discard bay leaves.
If desired, add 1/2 c. Madeira.
When serving float a very thin slice of lemon on top of bowl of soup (optional).

title: frozen yogurt pie
directions: Use same flavor of yogurt and fruit.
Strawberry, blueberry and peach are some choices.

title: triple chocolate cake
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix by hand until blended, 2 minutes. Pour into greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.
Cool in pan for 15 minutes; finish on rack.

title: chocolate eclair dessert
directions: Line a 9 x 13 glass dish with graham crackers. Mix pudding and 3 cups milk. Fold in Cool Whip. Spread 1/3 of mixture over crackers and add 2 more layers. End with graham crackers.

title: chinese casserole
directions: Combine ingredients in casserole, except noodles.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°.
Serve on noodles.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli until tender; drain.
Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: bow tie pasta salad
directions: Pour dressing over pasta, asparagus, tomato and mushrooms. Cover and refrigerate.
Add Colby cheese just before serving; mix lightly.
Arrange lettuce on serving platter.
Top with pasta mixture.
Sprinkle on Parmesan cheese.
Makes 6 servings.

title: homemade vanilla ice cream
directions: Blend eggs and sugar.
Add Eagle Brand milk, vanilla and milk. Mix well.
Mixture is now ready for freezing.

title: apple dumplings
directions: Combine apple slices, water, sugar, butter, cinnamon and nutmeg in large saucepan.
Bring to boil.
Mix together flour and milk; cream until well blended.
Drop dough from spoon into boiling apples.
Cover.
Reduce heat and simmer for 20 minutes or until apples are tender.
Serve warm or cold topped with
milk.

title: rice krispies squares
directions: Mix sugar and syrup.
Cook until it bubbles.
Stir in peanut butter.
Add Rice Krispies, then press in buttered pan and cool. Melt butterscotch and chocolate chips over hot water, then spread over Rice Krispies.

title: mexican lasagne
directions: Brown meat, onions and drain. Add seasoning, olives, mushrooms, tomato paste, & Rotels - simmer (15 mins.). Add cottage cheese, 1 pkg. Mexican cheese. Spray Pam in a 13 x 9 in. pan. Place noodles, meat, cheese. Repeat.

title: pineapple sweet potatoes
directions: Cream together margarine, sugar and eggs.
Add flour, pineapple. milk and sweet potatoes.
Pour batter into baking dish and bake for 50 minutes at 375 degrees or lower.
Makes 2 quarts or 6-8 servings.

title: dutch potato salad
directions: Boil small red potatoes until tender.
Do not remove skins. Let cool, then cut them into smaller pieces, maybe halves or quarters.
Cut up onion, red peppers and celery.
Make mix of sour cream and mayonnaise; add salt and pepper to taste.
Mix all ingredients, then cut up hard-boiled eggs and mix gently into potato salad.
Then enjoy.

title: crisys steak
directions: Roll steak in flour.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Put in frying pan with 1/4 to 1/2 cup of oil (any kind).
Fry until brown on both sides.
Remove from frying pan into large baking pan.
Lay in layers.
Pour 1 1/2 quarts of water into frying pan.
Cook until it boils.
Pour into large baking pan with meat.
Cover with foil and bake 1 1/2 hours at 450°.
Sprinkle garlic powder on top before you cover (2 teaspoons).

title: white cookies with raisins
directions: Cook on top of the stove until thickened. Cool.

title: easy potato casserole
directions: Combine potatoes, onion, green pepper, soups, sour cream, salt and pepper.
Toss thoroughly to coat potatoes.
Spoon mixture into a greased, shallow 2-quart casserole.
Bake 75 minutes in 325° oven.
Sprinkle with cheese and bake additional 15 minutes.

title: ham and cheese roll
directions: Make
this
into a roll in wax paper.
Roll walnuts for outside cover if you use them.

title: spice bread
directions: Heat milk to lukewarm (105°).
Stir in yeast and pinch of sugar.
Allow it to proof for 10 minutes or until begins to foam. Stir in eggs, melted butter, sugar, salt, spices and vanilla extract.
Add enough flour to make soft dough.
Turn dough out onto a floured board and knead until smooth and elastic, about 10 minutes.
Place in a greased bowl, turning to grease the top. Cover and allow to rise until doubled in volume, 1 1/2 to 2 hours. Divide dough into 4 pieces.
Roll each piece out into a 6-inch oval, about 1/2-inch thick.
Place the loaves on a greased baking sheet and leave to rise, covered, for 1/2 hour.
Preheat oven to 375°.
With your thumb, make indentations in the dough in decorative rows, then brush the loaves with beaten egg yolk.
Bake for 15 to 20 minutes until golden.
Makes 4 loaves.

title: custard pie
directions: Beat eggs until yolks and whites are blended.
Add sugar, salt, nutmeg and vanilla.
Mix thoroughly.
Add milk slowly, stirring constantly.
Pour into pastry-lined pie pan.
Bake in hot oven (425°) until an inserted knife comes out clean.

title: sybil's stew
directions: Soak the dried beans, dried peas, lentils, etc., in water overnight.
Put dried beans into kettle with water.
Bring to a boil; simmer for 2 1/2 hours with stew meat.
Add tomatoes, onion, celery, potatoes, carrots and seasonings; simmer 1/2 hour longer.

title: slow-cooked short ribs
directions: In a large resealable plastic bag, combine flour, salt and pepper. Add ribs in batches and shake to coat. In a large skillet, brown ribs in butter. Transfer to a 5-quart slow cooker. In the same skillet, combine remaining ingredients. Cook and stir until mixture comes to a boil; pour over ribs (slow cooker will be full). Cover and cook on low for 9-10 hours or until meat is tender. Yields 12 - 15 servings.

title: eggplant parmesan
directions: Cut
eggplant into 1/2-inch thick sections and place in the bottom
of	a
14-inch Dutch oven.	Mix everything except Parmesan and
pour
on top of eggplant.
Cover and cook for 50 minutes. Sprinkle on Parmesan cheese to taste.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into a greased casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: everlasting rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1/2 cup warm water with the 1 tablespoon sugar.
Let stand in deep bowl 45 minutes.

title: cheesy chip dip
directions: Fry and drain ground beef.
Set aside.
Place cheese in microwavable bowl and heat approximately 3 minutes or until creamy.
Add ground beef and diced tomatoes.
Stir well and enjoy with tortilla chips.

title: never fail pie crust
directions: Mix flour, Crisco and salt. Beat egg, water and vinegar.
Add to flour mixture.
Mix well.
Makes 2 covered pies or 4 pie shells.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Cook over high heat until it threads.
Add raw peanuts. Cook until bubbles, and turns amber color.
Add soda, salt and butter. Pour into buttered cookie sheet.
Break up when cool.

title: apple cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Mix eggs, oil and vanilla. Add apples and nuts.
Stir until mixed.
Pour into greased, floured tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Remove from oven. Place in heavy brown paper bag immediately.
Close tightly.
Let stand until cool.

title: squash au gratin "b"
directions: Saute onions in 3 tablespoons butter until tender.
Arrange half of squash in buttered baking dish.
Cover with half of onions.
Repeat.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs and dot with butter. Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: lemon brownies
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients like pie crust until it crumbles.
Pat into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.
While baking, mix eggs, 1 1/2 cups sugar, 3 tablespoons flour and juice of 1 lemon.
Pour over hot crust.
Bake 20 minutes longer at same temperature.
Sprinkle with 4 teaspoons sugar while still hot. Yields one 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix ingredients except cheese.
Bake for 45 minutes to 1 hour. After baking, top with cheese.
Corn bread mix raises to top to make a delicious casserole.

title: cream cheese cookies
directions: Combine all ingredients, mixing well.
Make into balls the size of walnuts.
Flatten with fork a little and bake in 350° oven about 10 to 12 minutes.

title: oven-fried beef chimichangas
directions: Place steak in an ovenproof Dutch oven coated with vegetable cooking spray.
Cover and bake at 325° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours or until tender.
Remove steak from Dutch oven and let cool to touch.

title: crumble topping
directions: Melt butter.
Add 1/2 of it to other ingredients.
Keep adding a little butter or margarine until crumbly.
Good for pies, cupcakes, cobblers, etc.

title: cucumbers with dairy dressing
directions: Place the cucumbers in a colander; sprinkle with salt.
Weight the cucumbers with a heavy plate; let them drain for 1 hour, then transfer to a large bowl.
Combine remaining ingredients; pour over cucumbers.
Toss well.
Serve chilled.
Makes 6 servings.

title: german potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes in skins.
Let cool and then peel and dice. Toss in chopped onion, bell pepper, celery and eggs.

title: deviled eggs
directions: Put
eggs
in a pan and cover with water.
Boil about 4 minutes, until hard-boiled.
Pour out hot water and slowly add cool
water;
let eggs stand for a few minutes (this makes the shells
come
off easier).
Take off shells and let eggs chill before
cutting
in half.
When cool, cut eggs in half lengthwise. Mash
yolks
in a bowl and add the rest of the ingredients.
Use enough salad dressing to make a thick paste of the yolks.
Fill each half with the yolk filling and chill.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Layer in order, starting with lettuce, onion, green pepper, peas, mayo mixture, cheese and bacon in a 13 x 9-inch glass dish. Cover tightly and refrigerate overnight.

title: hoppin' john
directions: Combine all ingredients except rice. Cook until done. Add rice. Cook 20 to 30 minutes more.

title: seven layer dip
directions: Layer in order and serve with Nacho chips.

title: molasses cookies
directions: Mix together brown sugar, shortening, egg and molasses.
Add the remaining ingredients.
Chill dough.
Form into 1-inch balls. Roll into sugar.
Flatten slightly with bottom of glass or fork. Bake at 325° for 10 minutes until set but not hard.
If desired, ice with butter icing.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Scramble and drain.
Use 8 x 11-inch dish.
Bake at 350° to 375° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Make 12 hours ahead.
Can be frozen.
For 1 1/2 recipe, use 2 pounds sausage.

title: lemon sponge pie
directions: Cream the sugar and butter; add flour and beaten egg yolks. Mix in the lemon juice, lemon rind and milk gradually.
Add beaten egg whites, but do not break whites all up.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes, then 250° for 1/2 to 3/4 hour.

title: dirt
directions: Prepare pudding as directed.
Blend in softened cream cheese. Fold in Cool Whip.
Put whole Oreos in blender to make crumbs (will look like potting soil).
Get container (if you use a real flower pot, put Oreos over drain hole).
Alternate crumbs with pudding mixture, starting and ending with crumbs.
Let sit overnight in refrigerator.
Put silk or plastic flowers to look like a real plant.
Fills a 8 to 10-inch pot.

title: marzipan
directions: Mix all ingredients; knead smooth.
Paste can be softened with a very little amount of lemon juice if it is too stiff.
Let stand covered 24 hours before using.
When ready to use, form into desired shapes.

title: fruit quick bread
directions: Dissolve raisins in boiling water and soda.
Let soak 3 hours or overnight.
In a large bowl, cream the shortening, eggs, sugar and vanilla.
Add flour, baking powder and salt.
Mix well.
Stir in raisin mixture, candied fruits and nuts.
Pour into greased pans and bake at 325° until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean, about 1 hour.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes and eggs.
Get well done.
Dice potatoes and mash eggs.
Mix all ingredients well.
Put in refrigerator for about 45 minutes to an hour.
Then serve.

title: egg white drop candy
directions: Beat the egg whites until stiff, then add baking powder and then sugar, a little at a time.
Put in vanilla and then pecans. Spoon out on a baking pan.
Bake at 250° for at least 45 minutes.

title: savory bear
directions: Combine the vinegar, peppercorns, bay leaves, cinnamon, onions,
thyme,
basil,
rosemary and celery and pour over the bear meat in a bowl.
Marinate in refrigerator for 24 hours.

title: spaghetti bake
directions: Mix ground beef, tomatoes, tomato sauce, onion, sugar, salt, oregano, basil, garlic and chili powder; simmer 30 minutes.
Cook and drain spaghetti (do not rinse).
Add to meat mixture and add mushrooms.
Put 1/2 mixture in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with Mozzarella cheese.
Add remainder of meat mixture.
Top with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, covering the first 20 minutes.

title: broccoli and cauliflower salad
directions: Mix
sour
cream
with mayonnaise.
Add dry powder mix. Mix well.
Add to washed and cut up cauliflower and broccoli. Toss. Sprinkle
shredded
Cheddar cheese on top.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: peanut balls(kids love these)
directions: Melt oleo and peanut butter.
Remove from heat.
Stir in sugar, crumbs and flavoring.
Mix well.
Shape into balls about the size of quarter.
Place on cookie sheet and chill.
Melt chocolate and paraffin.
Dip balls into chocolate with toothpick or fork.
Place on wax paper.
Makes 40 balls.

title: frosted pecans
directions: Beat egg white, add sugar and vanilla.
Beat well.
Add 2 cups pecan halves.
Mix well with spoon.
With a teaspoon or your finger, put 1 pecan half at a time on a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 250° for 20 minutes.

title: lemon-pine dessert
directions: Dissolve jello with 1 cup boiling water and add 1/2 cup pineapple juice as total liquid required.
Cool until partially set.
Beat in sour cream and Philadelphia cream cheese.
Fold in nuts and crushed pineapple.
Pour into molds and chill.

title: chocolate-zucchini cake
directions: Cream margarine, oil and sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Add flour mixed with cocoa, baking powder, soda and salt.
Add zucchini.
Add milk and lemon juice.
Pour into greased 9 x 12-inch pan.
Add 1/2 cup chocolate chips on top.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Combine margarine, butter, cream cheese and sugar; beat until light and fluffy.
Add salt and vanilla.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add flour and mix well.
Pour into a well-greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Place in cold oven and set at 275°.
Bake for 1 1/2 hours or until it tests done.
Let cool in pan for about 15 minutes before removing from pan.

title: spice nut cake
directions: Cream shortening, vanilla and sugar; add eggs and beat well. Add sifted dry ingredients alternately with buttermilk.
Stir in nuts.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: mexican dip
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Heat until cheese is melted. Crock-pot is great for this!
Stir frequently.
Serve on corn chips or nachos.

title: kids mix
directions: In a plastic bag, mix all ingredients.
Now shake the bag like the dickens.
Then reach in, grab a handful and munch away.

title: cole slaw
directions: To the mayo, slowly beat in vinegar with fork. Add sugar and then slowly blend in milk.

title: easy biafran stew
directions: Cut up and brown chuck roast.
Cut up chicken.
Coarsely chop onion and green pepper.
Put all ingredients in stew pot and simmer for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: countryside chicken bake
directions: Combine all ingredients together.
Spoon into glass baking dish.
Sprinkle top with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Serves 6 to 8.

title: cherry winks
directions: Sift flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Combine shortening and sugar; cream well.
Blend in eggs.
Add milk and vanilla.
Blend into sifted dry ingredients.
Add pecans, dates and cherries.
Shape into balls using a level tablespoon of dough for each cookie.
Roll each ball of dough in crushed cornflakes. Place on greased baking sheet. Top each cookie with 1/4 cherry. Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: tangy barbecue wings
directions: Cut chicken wings into 3 sections. Discard wing tip. Place chicken into 2 greased 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking pans. Bake, uncovered, at 375° for 30 minutes; drain. Turn wings; bake 20 to 25 minutes longer or until juices run clear.

title: italian style green beans
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Microwave 3 to 5 minutes.
Stir and serve.

title: festive cranberry mold
directions: In saucepan, combine water, cranberries and sugar; bring to a boil, reduce heat and simmer 5 minutes or until all berries pop. Add gelatin; stir until dissolved.
Stir in undrained pineapple and grapes.
Pour into 5-cup ring mold.
Chill until firm. Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: taco salad
directions: Cook ground turkey (beef) with taco seasoning and chopped onion until brown.
Mix lettuce (chopped), cubed tomatoes and beans in pot.
Let meat cool.
Add meat to mixture.
Put in cheese.
Crush Doritos and mix into complete mixture.
Add Italian dressing and stir.
Serves 4 to 5 firefighters.

title: strawberry punch
directions: Mix and boil first 3 ingredients.
Let cool and add cooled remaining ingredients when ready to serve.
This serves 100.

title: breakfast pie
directions: Brown sausage; drain.
Line pie shell with cheese, then sausage.
Beat eggs, milk, salt and pepper and pour over sausage. Bake 30 minutes at 375°.

title: date kisses
directions: Beat egg whites, salt and cream of tartar until soft peaks form.
Beat in vanilla and sugar until very stiff and glossy. Fold in dates and coconut.
Drop from teaspoon 2-inches apart onto ungreased brown wrapping paper on a cookie sheet.
Bake in 325° oven for about 20 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool slightly.
Remove from paper.
Makes 3 1/2 dozen.

title: chocolate lover's ice cream pie
directions: In medium bowl stir together crushed cookies and butter.
Press on bottom and sides of 9-inch pie pan.
Freeze until firm (10 minutes).
Spread ice cream over crust.
Cover and freeze until firm (6 hours or longer).
Just before serving, drizzle pie with chocolate syrup.

title: pizza for breakfast or lunch
directions: Place 4 pita rounds on cookie sheet.
Spread 1 tablespoon of ketchup one each round.
Sprinkle shredded cheese on each round. Add about 6 to 8 rounds of pepperoni to each pizza (can add chopped onions, etc.).
Place pizza round into 400° oven and cook until cheese melts, 5 to 7 minutes.

title: crab swiss bites
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients well.
Separate rolls into 3 layers each.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Spoon on crab mixture.
Top each with a few water chestnuts.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes or until golden.

title: saturday brunch
directions: Combine soup mix and rice in a 1 3/4-quart shallow casserole dish.
Add boiling water, stirring until soup mix is dissolved. Set aside.

title: tortilla chip dip
directions: Mix seasoning with refried beans and spread in bottom of dish. Spread a good cup of sour cream on top of beans. Sprinkle green chilies on top on sour cream. Then layer onion and tomatoes. Put cheese on top. Microwave on High (uncovered) for approximately 5 minutes or until the cheese on top has melted. Serve hot with tortilla chips.

title: self-frosted date cake
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and cool.
Cream together sugar and shortening.
Add eggs, flour, soda and salt.
Pour all ingredients into large greased and floured cake pan.

title: perfect white bread
directions: Begin yeast in warm water.
Combine milk, sugar, salt and shortening.
Cool to lukewarm.
Stir in 2 cups flour.
Beat well. Add yeast mix.
Slowly add remaining flour while mixing.
Knead 8 to 10 minutes.
Shape in a ball.
Place in lightly buttered bowl; turn and cover.
Let rise 1 1/2 hours; punch.
Let rise again for 45 minutes.

title: carolina lemon pound cake
directions: Combine sugar and butter in mixing bowl.
Beat well until creamy.
Add eggs.
Sift flour, baking powder, soda and salt together and add alternately with buttermilk.
Add lemon juice and rind.
Pour in greased and floured tube pan.
Bake for 1 hour at 325°.

title: streusel topped fruit pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Spoon pie filling into pastry shell. In bowl combine flour and brown sugar.
Cut in butter until mixture is crumbly; stir in nuts.
Crumble over pie filling.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes or until top is golden and filling is bubbly. Remove to wire rack to cool.
Makes 8 servings.
If using a purchased frozen crust, buy a "deep dish" crust and follow package directions.

title: death by chocolate
directions: Prepare brownie mix according to package directions.
Cool and break into small pieces.
Prepare chocolate pudding according to package directions.

title: sausage corn bake
directions: Grease
and
heat muffin pans, corn stick mold or skillet. Beat
egg
with
fork,
add milk and oil.
Stir in meal, sugar and sausage.
Blend well.
Pour batter into hot greased pans. Bake in
preheated
oven
25 or 30 minutes.
This bread should be
baked
thin
and quite brown.
Makes about 14 muffins, 18 sticks or one medium-size skillet full.

title: (no water) pound cake
directions: Combine powdered sugar and cake flour with butter; mix thoroughly.
Add eggs and powdered sugar; beat at least 3 minutes with mixer.
Pour in greased loaf pan and cook at 350° for 40 minutes or until done.

title: citrus salad
directions: In a large bowl combine the fruit, sour cream, marshmallows and coconut.
Cover and refrigerate for several hours.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: chicken velvet soup
directions: Melt butter and whisk in flour.
Cook until flour bubbles. Stir in 2 cups of chicken stock, milk and cream.
Stir in remaining stock, chicken and broth.
Season with salt and pepper.

title: buttery pan rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water and set aside until bubbly.
Sift flour, measure 2 cups of it with sugar and salt.
(Don't sift instant type flour.)
Add 6 tablespoons butter, egg, yeast mixture and cooled milk to the flour.
Beat at high speed with an electric mixer about 2 minutes.
Add remaining flour by hand.
Cover bowl and let batter rise in warm place until doubled (about 45 minutes). Pour half of the 1/4 cup butter into 9 x 13-inch pan, tilting to coat bottom.
Beat down batter and drop by spoonfuls into buttered pan, making about 15 rolls.
Drizzle remaining butter over dough. Let rise until almost doubled (about 30 minutes).
Bake in a 425° oven for 12 to 17 minutes.

title: broccoli or spinach quiche
directions: Thaw broccoli or spinach; let liquid drain off.
Mix first six ingredients together.
Add cheese; next add broccoli or spinach. Mix well together.
Put in unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Let set before serving.

title: country chicken salad
directions: Combine all ingredients in bowl.
Chill until serving time. Yields 4 servings.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Mix whipped topping and milk.
Add drained fruit and mix well. Stir in lemon juice and mix until thickened.
Spoon into crust. Sprinkle with coconut, if desired.
Refrigerate several hours. Makes 2 pies.

title: ham loaf
directions: Mix well all ingredients.
Place in baking dish.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Remove from oven and cover with sauce.

title: outdoor potatoes
directions: After dicing potatoes, bell pepper and onion, put a stick of butter on a large piece of aluminum foil.
Put all seasonings on to suit taste.
Wrap in foil.
Put on fire until done.
Goes great with anything you cook outdoors.

title: corned beef pasties
directions: Combine flour, lard or butter and salt in a large mixing bowl. Dig in with hands and work together until you have coarse crumbs. Sprinkle in water and work into ball.
Don't use anymore water than necessary to avoid toughness.
Divide dough into 6 portions. On a lightly floured board or surface, roll each ball into 6-inch circles.
Combine corned beef, potato, onion and carrot.
Mix well. Divide into 6 portions and place one portion in center of each pastry circle.
Fold over filling and crimp edges.
Brush with beaten egg and bake at 400° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Serve hot, warm or at room temperature.
May be frozen before baking for later use.

title: green beans with dill
directions: Place frozen beans in saucepan with water, dill weed or seed, beef flavor base and salt. Cover; bring to a boil.
Separate beans with fork.
Reduce heat and simmer 10 minutes or until tender. Drain. Toss lightly with butter.

title: filet mignon with madeira wine sauce
directions: Sprinkle meat on both sides with salt and pepper.
Heat the oil in a skillet and when very hot, add the meat.
Cook on high heat about 5 minutes.
Cook longer if you want medium or well done meat. Turn the meat and continue cooking over high heat about 5 minutes. Remove meat to warm platter and keep warm.
Pour off fat from skillet.
Add shallots and wine to skillet and cook over high heat for 30 seconds.
Add the broth and bring to a full rolling boil, stirring to dissolve the brown particles that cling to the bottom and sides of skillet.
Season with salt and pepper to taste.
Cook until reduced by half.
Meanwhile blend 2 teaspoons butter with the flour in a small mixing bowl.
Stir into the simmering sauce and cook briefly until thickened.
Swirl in the remaining teaspoon of butter.
