Strain the sauce over meat and dot the center of each filet with a dab of parsley.
Makes 4 servings.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Cream sugars and butter.
Add applesauce, one cup at a time, with 1 teaspoon baking soda, until you have used 4 cups.
Mix well and then sift flour with nutmeg, cloves and cinnamon.
Add the sifted flour and spices to the mixture.
Add raisins and nuts. Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 20 minutes in a large Bundt pan.

title: carrot cake
directions: In mixer bowl, blend oil, sugar, vanilla and eggs.
Sift flour, salt and baking soda and add to first mixture.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Spread in a lightly greased 9 x 13-inch pan or 2 (9-inch) round pans.
Bake at 350°.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Melt butter, then add to sugar and peanut butter.
Mix well. In double boiler, melt chocolate and paraffin wax.
Make small balls with peanut butter mixture and dip with toothpick in melted chocolate.
Set on wax paper and refrigerate.

title: cherry congealed salad
directions: Mix together well and set aside to congeal.
Refrigerate.

title: microwave chili
directions: Crumble beef in a 2-quart casserole dish.
Stir in onion. Cover.
Microwave 5 to 6 minutes on High.
Drain and stir in remaining ingredients.
Cover.
Microwave 14 to 18 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes, covered.

title: enchiladas
directions: Brown onion and ground beef.
Add 1/2 cup sauce to mixture and 1/2 cup cheese.
Heat sauce; dip tortillas in sauce.
Fill each tortilla with 2 tablespoons of meat mixture; roll and place in pan, seam side down.
Cover enchiladas with sauce and grated cheese.
Heat for 20 minutes in 350° oven.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix together and pour in an unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 300° and cook 30 minutes longer. Serve plain or with whipped cream.

title: coffee rings
directions: Cut biscuits in half.
Place in greased tube pan.
Pour melted margarine on top.
Sprinkle on brown sugar and nuts.
Bake about 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.

title: jalapeno corn bread
directions: Cook in greased (I use Pam) pan at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: apple brownies
directions: Cream butter and sugar together.
Add remaining ingredients. Bake in ungreased 8 x 8-inch pan at 350° for 40 minutes.
Cut in squares.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream shortening.
Add sugar and cream together until fluffy. Add egg.
Sift flour and add soda and salt.
Add chips, nuts and vanilla.
Cook at 300° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Let cool on pan, then remove into container.

title: o'brien potato casserole
directions: Thaw potatoes until they break apart.
Mix other ingredients with potatoes. Add corn flake crumbs on top.
Melt another 1/4 cup oleo and pour over top.
Bake at 350° for at least 1 hour.
Test for doneness (depends on oven).

title: eye of round
directions: Dry roast with paper towel.
Pierce roast in several places across top and bottom.
Sprinkle seasoned salt and lemon pepper over surface and rub in.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Stir well.
Pour over roast.
Cover and marinate in refrigerator for 8 hours or overnight.
Turn once or twice.
I use large freezer bag for roast and marinade.
Easy to turn and can be thrown away.

title: melt away cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Combine butter, sugar and vanilla. Gradually stir in flour, salt and then the pecans.
Drop by heaping teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake until peaks are very light brown, approximately 7 minutes.
Transfer to cooling rack.
While still warm, sift generously with confectioners sugar.

title: beans and meat
directions: Cook pinto beans in soda water and change water.
Cook ground meat, chili powder and onion powder until clear.
Put all together and cook at low temperature.

title: swiss egg bake
directions: In a saucepan, combine soup, milk, onion and mustard. Cook and stir until smooth and heated through. Remove from heat.
Stir in cheese until melted.
Pour 1 cup of sauce into each of two 10 x 6 x 1 1/2-inch baking dishes.

title: king ranch casserole
directions: Boil chicken and bone; save 1 cup broth.
Grate cheese.
Tear tortillas into pieces.
Place tortillas in large casserole dish with layers of chicken, onions and cheese.

title: beans and eggs
directions: Note:
Measurements are approximate, use your judgment.

title: aunt helen's pound cake
directions: Combine ingredients.
Pour into greased and floured Bundt pan. Bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: buffet cheese-scalloped carrots
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook carrots and drain.

title: "mini chicken pancakes"
directions: Boil chicken parts until meat falls off the bone.
Remove bones and dice chicken.
Mix with cream of celery soup, salt, pepper and onion salt.
Make a batch of Bisquick pancake mix, following directions on box.
Add to chicken and soup mixture. Fry like a mini pancake.
Serve hot!!!

title: stuffed bell peppers
directions: Boil pepper pods after seeds have been removed in salt water for 5 minutes; let cool.
Cook meat in skillet with onion, salt and pepper together until meat is done.
Add 1/2 can of tomato soup and rice all together.
Stand your peppers in a baking dish and stuff each one.
Add rest of soup on top of peppers.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Ease out of oven and put a slice of cheese on top of each pepper.
Put back in oven until cheese melts.

title: toffee crunch cookies
directions: Beat butter at medium speed with a mixer until creamy. Add cake mix, eggs and water, beating until blended.
Stir in brickle chips and pecans.
Drop cookie dough by teaspoons onto ungreased cookie sheets. Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes or until edges are browned.
(Top will look moist.)
Transfer to wire racks to cool. Yields 7 dozen cookies.

title: pineapple muffins
directions: On wax paper or in small bowl, stir together flours, baking powder and salt.
In a medium bowl, beat together butter, honey and egg until blended.
Add flour mixture and undrained pineapple; stir only enough to moisten flour mixture.
Batter will be thick.
Fill buttered muffin pan cups (each 1/3 cup capacity) 2/3 to 3/4 full.
Bake in preheated 425° oven until a cake tester inserted in center comes out clean, 15 to 18 minutes. Serve at once with butter pats.
Muffins taste better fresh than reheated.
Makes 12.

title: pepsi roast
directions: Place roast in pan which can be tightly covered.
Spread can of soup over roast.
Sprinkle dry onion soup mixture over the top. Pour Pepsi into pan and cover tightly.
Put into oven at 325° and roast for 3 1/2 to 4 hours.
Makes its own gravy.
Yield:
4 to 6 servings.

title: rocky road fudge candy
directions: In saucepan, melt chips with Eagle Brand and 2 tablespoons margarine.
In large bowl, combine pecans and marshmallows.
Pour chocolate mixture into nut mixture.
Add vanilla.
Spread into wax paper-lined 13 x 9-inch pan.
Chill 2 hours and cut into squares. Makes about 40 squares.

title: turkey casserole
directions: Combine the mayonnaise, soup and milk.
Cook the peas according to the directions on package.
Drain.
Add the peas and turkey to the soup mixture.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: gone-all-day stew
directions: Mix together tomato soup, water and flour until smooth.
Add remaining ingredients and cook in slow cooker for 4 to 5 hours. (Can also be cooked in covered roasting pan at 275° for 4 to 5 hours.)
Makes 8 large servings.

title: convenient cole slaw(keeps indefinitely in refrigerator)
directions: Grate vegetables, then cover with boiling water.
Let stand 1 hour.
Drain in colander, then return to kettle.
Pour remaining ingredients over top.
Mix well and put in jars.
Store in refrigerator.

title: ranch potatoes
directions: Peel and slice potatoes and boil until tender.
Drain potatoes and place in a pan that has been sprayed with a nonstick coating spray.
With potatoes spread flat, pour butter over hot potatoes and sprinkle with salt and white pepper.
Sprinkle cheese evenly over potatoes.
Pour Ranch dressing onto cheese.
Spread dressing evenly over potatoes/cheese.
Sprinkle bacon and green onions on top of Ranch dressing.
Serve warmed or chilled.

title: mamaw vera's boiled oatmeal cookies
directions: Cook margarine, cocoa, milk and sugar for 1 1/2 minutes; hard-boil.
Remove from heat.
Add other ingredients quickly and mix well.
Drop cookies from spoon quickly on waxed paper.

title: coconut sour cream layer cake
directions: Prepare cake mix according to directions on package, making 2 (8-inch) layers.
When completely cooled, split both layers. Combine sugar, sour cream and coconut; blending well; chill. Reserve 1 cup sour cream mixture for frosting.
Spread remainder between layers.
Combine reserved sour cream mixture with whipped topping; blend until smooth.
Spread on top and sides.
Seal cake in airtight container and refrigerate for 3 days before serving. Keep refrigerated.

title: chicken with duck sauce
directions: Line pan with foil.
Pour mixture of first 3 ingredients over chicken and bake until done at 350°.

title: buttermilk pecan pie
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Cream butter and sugar, adding sugar 1/2 cup at a time.
Blend in vanilla.
Add eggs one at a time.
Combine flour and salt; add small amount at a time.
Add buttermilk. Sprinkle pecans in bottom of prepared pie crust.
Pour custard over pecans and bake for an hour and 30 minutes.
Best if served at room temperature.

title: italian vegetable salad
directions: In a large salad bowl, combine everything except dressing and cheese. Toss ingredients together.

title: rainbow fruit salad
directions: Combine all ingredients. Served chilled, with a dollop of sour cream.

title: stewed rabbit chinon
directions: To make bouquet garni (used to season rabbit while baking), combine parsley, bay leaf, thyme and marjoram in a small, double cheesecloth and tie secure with a string.
Set aside for later use.
Season the rabbit pieces with salt and pepper, then dredge in flour.
Heat the bacon drippings in a frying pan, then add the rabbit pieces and brown on all sides.
Remove the rabbit and place in a baking dish.
Add the wine, broth, bouquet garni (made previously), the large onion and garlic cloves, then cover.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 1 hour and 30 minutes, or until the rabbit is tender.

title: "duane's" clam linguine
directions: Cook linguine according to package directions.
Open clams; put juice into a saucepan.
Bring to a slight boil.
Turn heat to low and simmer.
Add package of cheese and garlic; stir.
Add soup and the clams; stir very well, until consistency desired.
Pour over linguine and serve.

title: peanut butter cups
directions: Melt; put mixture in pan.
Add dab of peanut butter (which has been heated by putting jar in hot water).
Cool in fridge.
Put melted chocolate on top to finish.

title: butterscotch pie
directions: Bring milk almost to a boil and add butter.
In a bowl, mix brown sugar, white sugar and syrup together and add hot milk slowly.
Mix remaining ingredients and add slowly to hot milk mixture.
Place back on stove and cook until thick.
Let cool. Pour into 9-inch pie shell.

title: quiche
directions: In large bowl, beat eggs until foamy.
Gradually add soup and cream, mixing well.
Add cheese, meat and vegetables (onion optional) and stir until well mixed.

title: hush puppies
directions: Drain corn.
Combine flour, cornmeal, baking powder, sugar and salt.
Add milk and rest of ingredients.
Drop by tablespoonfuls 3 inches apart on buttered baking sheet.
Bake at 425° for 10 to 15 minutes until golden brown.
Serve with butter.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: sauerkraut balls
directions: Fry sausage, onions, sauerkraut; add bread crumbs. Combine cream cheese and other ingredients and to mixture.	Chill. Form into about 60 to 70 balls.	Dip into 2 beaten eggs, then roll in one cup flour and 1 1/2 c. bread crumbs.
Fry in skillet or oven --not to dark-- serve warm.
Dip in Ketchup with horseradish.
Can be made ahead and frozen; when thawed, heat in shallow pan on low heated oven.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Cook vegetables as directed on package. Place on bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cut up Velveeta cheese and place on vegetables.

title: peanut pie
directions: Run peanuts in blender and mix with other ingredients.
Cook in uncooked pie crust.
Bake at 325° for 35 minutes.

title: swedish pancakes
directions: Combine eggs, milk and butter.
Add all dry ingredients gradually.
Cook 10 minutes.
Makes 16 to 18 pancakes.

title: blackberry pie
directions: Combine sugar, flour, cornstarch and salt; toss with blackberries.
Line a 9-inch pie plate with pastry.
Add blackberry mixture.
Adjust top crust; cut slits to allow steam to escape.
Bake in a 400° oven for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: ham loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients well and form into 2 loaves.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: easy time holiday squares
directions: Cream margarine.
Then at medium speed, gradually add sugar. Add 1 egg at a time, beating well after adding each one.
At low speed, gradually add flour and mix well.
Finally add the lemon extract.

title: blue ribbon pie crust
directions: Mix flour, salt and baking powder.
Cut in shortening until mixture is cornmeal-textured.
In a 1-cup measure, beat together vinegar and egg, then fill to 1-cup mark with cold tap water.
Mix together flour and vinegar-egg-water mixtures.
It will be soft and sticky.
Working on a very well floured board, roll out a piece of the dough to approximately 1/8-inch thick and 2 to 3-inches wider than your pie pan.
Put in lightly floured pie pans.
Roll out equal size circles for top crusts.

title: love cake for mother
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Bake in a hearty, warm oven.
Serve to mother every day.
Serve large slices.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix all together.
Cook until thick.
Pour into baked pie shell.

title: cherry cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water in pan on burner; stir in cranberry sauce while hot and stir over heat until dissolved.
Let chill until thick and syrupy.
Add sour cream by folding in gently.
Add pineapple, pecans and marshmallows.
Chill and serve. Serves 8 to 10.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Cook Beans a chopped onions about 10 minutes.
Stir soup until all lumps are gone.
Then pour in beans.
Mix well.
Bake about 10 minutes.
Take out.

title: string bean salad
directions: Boil string beans with just enough salt to season.
Strain, cool and chop.
Mix the rest of the ingredients.

title: skillet barbecue chicken
directions: Brown chicken in hot oil. Stir in barbecue sauce, water, corn and pepper. Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer 5 minutes. Stir in rice. Cover.
Remove from heat.
Let stand 5 minutes.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Cook all ingredients in a saucepan over medium heat until thick.
Pour into a precooked pie shell.
Top with meringue and bake to brown meringue.

title: kourabiedes(greek butter cookies with confectioners sugar)
directions: In a large bowl, combine the flour and baking soda.
In another bowl (large) beat well the butter until fluffy.
Add the sugar, egg yolks, vanilla and brandy (orange juice may be used as a substitute for brandy).
Then add flour mixture, a little at a time, mixing constantly.
Soft dough will form.
Knead the dough.
Cut into shapes.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes (until light brown).
Let cool and dust with confectioners sugar until well coated.
Makes approximately 65 cookies.

title: herbed potato wedges
directions: Scrub potatoes, then cut into 8 wedges.
Using an 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish, melt the butter in microwave, using full power 45 to 60 seconds.
Stir in herbs and salt to taste.
Add potatoes, coat with mixture.
Cover with plastic wrap.
Cook on High 8 to 10 minutes or until tender.
Season to taste.

title: kitchen summer sausage
directions: Mix well.
Cover and refrigerate.
Knead once a day for 3 days.
On the fourth day, make 3 rolls, 2 1/2 x 6-inches.
Bake at 170° for 11 hours, uncovered.

title: sage chicken
directions: Skin, debone and cube chicken.
Saute in hot oil until brown. Drain excess oil and fat.
Add cream of mushroom soup, sage and mushrooms with liquid.
Stir well.
Simmer, covered, 45 minutes to 1 hour or until chicken is tender.
Add noodles.
Stir and serve immediately.

title: apple pudding
directions: Stir flour and baking powder.
Blend egg and milk; add to dry ingredients.
Mix well; pour over sliced apples. Dot with butter; sprinkle with 1 tablespoon sugar.
Bake in moderate oven (350°) for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Test for doneness.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Saute onion and celery in butter.
Butter casserole dish.
Put cooked rice in bottom of pan.
Combine onion and celery to the cooked broccoli and mushroom soup.
Put this mixture on top of rice.
Put cheese on top and bake at 350° until cheese is melted. Pour water off of broccoli.

title: pineapple glaze for ham
directions: In a pan combine 1/4 cup juice and the cornstarch, stir until smooth.
Add rest of ingredients, bring to boil stirring over medium heat.
Glaze will be slightly thick.

title: divinity fudge or bonbons
directions: Combine sugar, water and honey.
Stir while heating until sugar dissolves.
Boil without stirring until syrup forms a hard ball when tested in cold water (265°).
Remove from heat and quickly beat salted egg whites until stiff.
Slowly add syrup to egg whites, beating constantly.
Beat until candy thickens and begins to lose its gloss; add flavorings and quickly drop by teaspoons onto greased plate or waxed paper.
Put half a nut meat on each piece while still warm.

title: open house punch
directions: Combine sugar and water.
Heat until dissolved. Cool and chill.
Add other juices. Chill until ready to serve.
Gently combine with cold ginger ale in punch bowl. Garnish.
Serves 50.

title: matador mania
directions: Brown hamburger and onion together in skillet.
Drain and add taco seasoning, refried beans and sour cream and heat mixture thoroughly.

title: buddy bars
directions: In large bowl, beat peanut butter and butter until smooth. Add sugar, eggs and vanilla; beat until creamy.
Blend in flour and salt.
Fold in 1 cup chocolate chips.
Spread into ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Immediately sprinkle with remaining chips.
Let stand about 5 minutes and then spread chips evenly over top.
Cool completely and cut into bars.

title: pecan pie bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Grease 13 x 9-inch pan. Reserve 2/3 cup of the dry cake mix for filling. Combine remaining cake mix, margarine and 1 egg; beat at a low speed until well blended. Press in bottom of greased pan. Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes or until light golden brown.

title: almond twist coffee cake
directions: Combine margarine, sugar and 1/4 teaspoon almond extract. Heat until butter is melted.
Cut each bread loaf into 4 pieces. Roll pieces into 18-inch "snakes".
Coil dough on a lightly greased pizza pan.
When joining "snakes" to each other, moisten the ends and pinch firmly together.
Spoon butter-sugar mixture over top of dough.
Let rise in a warm place for 30 minutes. Bake for 15 minutes at 350°.
Sprinkle sliced almonds on top. Cover with foil and continue baking for 15 minutes.
Cool about 10 minutes.
Make a glaze from remaining ingredients and drizzle over top of cake.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: In a large saucepan, cook broccoli in a cup of water (do not drain).
Put milk, cheese, chicken bouillon and flour into a blender and mix.
Add this mixture to broccoli, then add half and half.
Cook, stirring frequently over medium heat until hot and soup thickens.

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: Combine sugar and vinegar; stir until clear.
Let set 5 minutes.
Combine remaining ingredients in bowl.
Stir in sugar and vinegar mixture.
Mix well; put in jars in refrigerator.

title: tropical garden punch
directions: Mix well together, chill.
Serve in punch bowl.

title: pasta plentiful salad
directions: In large bowl, combine vinegar, water, oil and seasonings. Add remaining ingredients, except spinach leaves.
Lightly toss until evenly coated with dressing.
Cover and chill to blend flavors.
Garnish with spinach leaves, if desired.

title: sand bakklse
directions: Mix all together and add 1 3/4 cups sifted flour.
Chill dough and press into sandbakklse tins as thin as possible.
Place on ungreased baking sheet and bake at 350° until delicately browned, 12 to 15 minutes.
Tap molds on table to loosen.

title: banana-nut-ring
directions: Drain pineapple; measuring juice, add water to make 1 1/2 cups.
Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Add measured liquid, chill until thickened.
Fold in bananas and nuts.
Spoon into 6-cup ring mold.
Chill until firm, about 4 hours.

title: dump cake
directions: Use 9 x 13-inch ungreased pan.
Pour ingredients directly in pan in order given (do not stir).
But it is best to smooth each layer with a big spoon.
Bake 1 hour or longer at 350°.

title: 7-up salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in 1 cup of boiling water, then add remaining ingredients.
Refrigerate until set.

title: company chicken
directions: Wrap dried beef around breasts and place in buttered baking dish.
Season with scant salt and pepper to taste.
(Dried beef is salty!)
Place drained mushrooms on chicken.
In separate pan, heat together soup, milk and butter.
Add wine and pour over chicken.
Cook uncovered at 300° for one hour and 15 minutes.
Add sour cream and artichoke hearts and bake 30 minutes more.

title: pizza fondue
directions: Brown meat and onion in oleo in a fondue pot.
Mix cornstarch and seasonings in pizza sauce.
Add sauce and stir well.
When this bubbles, add cheese by thirds, stirring after each addition. When all the cheese is melted, use dunkers and enjoy.

title: corn pudding
directions: Melt the butter; stir in flour, salt, pepper and sugar.
Cook until bubbly.
Add milk and cook until thick.
Stir in the corn and eggs; beat until frothy.
Pour into a buttered 1 quart casserole dish and bake in a hot water bath at 350° about 45 minutes or until custard is set.
Or, mix the egg yolks into the corn mixture and beat the egg whites until stiff.
Fold into the mixture and proceed baking.

title: spaghetti bread
directions: Add ingredients into pan in order listed.
Add oil and water last.
Set bread machine on " white bread" setting.

title: onion mushroom roast
directions: Set oven to 275°.
Put in large pan the roast on a large piece of foil.
Mix onion mix with soup; spread over roast, then fold foil loosely, leaving room around meat, but seal top.
Roast 3 to 4 hours.
Serves 8.

title: italian biscuit-topped casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. Chop green pepper and onion. Press garlic. Slice carrots, zucchini and mushrooms. Cook sausage, green pepper, onion and garlic over medium heat until brown and crumbly (about 6 minutes); drain off excess liquid. Add carrots and cook 3 minutes, stirring frequently. Add zucchini and mushrooms; cook 3 minutes, stirring frequently. Stir in spaghetti sauce and 1 teaspoon Italian seasoning. Bring to a simmer and cook 2 minutes. Pour sausage mixture into 9 x 13-inch casserole dish. Place biscuits around outer edge of dish. Melt butter and stir in cheese and remaining 1/2 teaspoon Italian seasoning. Brush over tops of biscuits. Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until biscuits are golden brown. Serve immediately.
tags: prepared chunky garden vegetable spaghetti sauce

title: sweet potato cups
directions: Cook sweet potatoes in a small amount of boiling water until tender.
Cool slightly, peel and mash.
Add margarine, raisins and orange peel.
Beat until fluffy.
Add a small amount of orange juice if potatoes seem too dry.
Stir in raisins.
Cut a slice off the top of each orange and scoop out pulp.
Heap potato mixture into orange shells.
Top with marshmallows and bake at 350° about 20 minutes.

title: cajun cornbread
directions: Mix dry ingredients together.
Add grated cheese, onions and peppers.
Add eggs and oil; mix.
Add creamed corn.

title: swiss steak
directions: Trim fat from steak; cut into serving pieces.
On a board, with a meat mallet, pound flour into steak.
In skillet, over medium-high heat, in 2 tablespoons oil, cook meat until well browned on both sides.
Remove steaks from skillet.
In same skillet, heat other 2 tablespoons oil.
Add onions, green pepper and garlic.
Cook until onions are lightly browned.
Stir in tomatoes, salt and pepper; heat to boiling.
Return steaks to skillet.
Reduce heat to low.
Cover; simmer 1 1/2 to 2 hours, until meat is fork-tender.
Remove steaks.
Cook tomato mixture until thickened.
Spoon over steaks.
Great served over rice or noodles.

title: german beef dip
directions: Slice beef into 1/4 in squares.
Mix all ingredients (except bread) together in a glass bowl, cover with Saran Wrap and refrigerate overnight.

title: fuzzy navel cake
directions: Place in
greased
and floured Bundt pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 40 minutes.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Beat shortening, sugar, vanilla and eggs until light.
Blend in flour, soda and salt.
Stir in nuts and chips.
Drop by teaspoon 2 inches apart on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes in moderate 375° oven.

title: chicken curry salad
directions: Combine mayonnaise and seasonings.
Mix with chicken, fruit and celery.
Place a bed of lettuce on 2 dinner plates and spoon 1/2 of chicken mixture on top of each.

title: chili con quesa
directions: Saute onion in margarine.
Puree and add tomatoes and pepper. Mix chili sauce and cornstarch and add when bubbly.
Reduce to medium heat.
Add cheese, stirring frequently.

title: corned beef delight
directions: Cut up onion and pepper into very small pieces and put into a frying pan or electric skillet.
Add a small amount of water so ingredients will not stick.
Boil this for about 15 minutes.
Pour off nearly all of the water and add can of corned beef.
Stir in with onion and peppers and add can of tomato sauce or small amount of catsup.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Stir together until evenly mixed and simmer on low heat for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: prune cake
directions: Mix flour, sugar, salt, cinnamon and nutmeg in bowl.
Dissolve soda in mashed prunes.
In another bowl, beat eggs.
Add oil, buttermilk and prunes.
Gradually add dry ingredients.
Add vanilla.
Fold in nuts.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° until done, about 30 minutes.
Cut in squares while hot.
Pour hot sauce over squares.

title: corn fritters
directions: Mix and fry in oil.

title: marinated chicken wings
directions: Mix all ingredients until well blended. Add chicken-add or decrease number of wings, making sure they are well covered-marinate at least 6 hours, overnight is o.k. Remove wings put on baking sheet bake. Bake 1 hour in preheated oven 350 degree. For crisper wings, bake longer until they are cooked, as you like.

title: sweet pickles
directions: Cover cucumber slices with alum and water for 24 hours; drain. Cover with vinegar and pickling spices for 24 hours.
Drain off vinegar and spice.
Add 3 cups of sugar for 3 days each.
Turn jar upside down and shake occasionally to dissolve sugar.
Pickles may be stored in this jar.
Cover tightly.
There will be almost enough liquid to cover pickles.

title: strawberry party punch
directions: In large bowl, combine strawberries and sugar. Mix well. Stir in 1 quart of the strawberry soda. Let stand at room temperature for 1 hour. Stir in lemonade concentrate. Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: chocolate cocoa cream cake
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Beat in eggs.
Add flour, powder and soda, alternating with milk.
Add vanilla and cocoa.
Pour into 2 greased and floured 9-inch layer cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes or until cake tests done.
Remove from pans and cool.
Fill when cool.

title: coconut pie
directions: Combine all ingredients in order and mix well.
Pour into well-greased 10-inch glass pie pan and bake 45 minutes to 1 hour at 300° until golden brown.
Makes its own crust.

title: creamed onions
directions: In medium saucepan, place onions, 1 teaspoon salt and enough cold water to cover.
Bring to boiling.
Reduce heat and simmer, covered, 20 to 25 minutes or until tender.
Drain onions; reserve 1/2 cup liquid.

title: hamburger-rice casserole
directions: Bring water to boil in saucepan. Add rice and salt, then remove from heat and set aside. Brown ground beef in hot fat. Add celery and onion; cook 5 minutes. Add butter, soy sauce, brown sugar, mushrooms and soup. Add pan of rice and water. Mix thoroughly. Pour into buttered 3-quart baking dish. Cover and bake in preheated 350° oven for 30 minutes. Uncover and bake for 30 minutes more.

title: lena's uncooked relish
directions: Grind vegetables and cover with water and salt.
Let stand 2 hours; drain.
Add celery seed to taste.
Pour vinegar, sugar and mustard seed over the mixture.
Pack in jars cold.

title: sausage balls(yields 50 balls)
directions: Mix all ingredients together thoroughly.
Shape into small balls.
Bake in a 350° oven for about 20 minutes.

title: chicken divan pot pie
directions: Preheat oven and baking sheet to 425°.
In medium saucepan, combine butter, flour and pepper.
Cook over low heat until mixture becomes thick and bubbly.
Stir in milk and broth until mixture is thick.
Add cheese and stir until melted.
Fold in chicken and broccoli.

title: fruity tea
directions: Put 2 tablespoons instant tea, sugar and juices into plastic jug. Add water to make 2 quarts. Shake well. Chill and serve over ice.

title: chicken parmesagna
directions: Dip chicken in egg and bread crumbs.
Brown in oil.
Place in a shallow baking pan and layer with sliced Mozzarella cheese, Parmesan cheese, sauce and then another layer of Parmesan cheese. Cook at 350° for 30 minutes, uncovered.
Add 10 minutes to cooking time if you forgo browning in oil.
Serve over pasta.

title: world's best cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.

Cream together butter, sugar and brown sugar until light and fluffy. Add egg. Mix well. Add oats, corn flakes, coconut and nuts. Stir well. Add flour, soda, salt and vanilla. Mix well. Form into balls the size of a small walnut. Place on ungreased cookie sheet. Flatten with a fork dipped in water. Bake for 12 minutes.
Allow cookies to cool on cookie sheet before removing. Makes about 8 dozen.

title: peanut butter and oatmeal cookies
directions: In a bowl, stir together flour and baking soda.
Set flour mixture aside.
In a large mixing bowl, beat margarine with electric mixer on medium to high speed about 30 seconds or until softened.
Add peanut butter, sugar and brown sugar to margarine. Beat until thoroughly combined, scraping sides of bowl occasionally.
Add egg whites and vanilla.
Beat until well combined.
Add flour mixture, then beat on low speed until combined.
Stir in oats.

title: pineapple bread pudding
directions: In large bowl, cream butter, vanilla pudding mix and cinnamon until fluffy.
Add eggs, 1 at a time, beating well after each.

title: drop dumplings
directions: Sift flour, salt and baking powder together.
Rub in shortening with knife or fingertips.
Add milk to soft dough. Then drop a tablespoon at a time on chicken or meat stews the last 15 to 20 minutes.
Pan must be covered closely and must not be removed during cooking.

title: cheese-filling for shells
directions: Combine all ingredients in large bowl.
Stuff cooled and drained shells.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes, using previously described sauce.

title: frosted pumpkin bars
directions: Combine all ingredients and pour into a greased and floured cookie sheet (15 x 11-inch).
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Take sirloin; cut in small strips.
Salt and pepper and dredge in flour.
Brown in grease.
When meat is done, cut up onions and green peppers; cook until soft.
Take out of grease.
Make a little gravy.
Add can of tomatoes and tomato sauce.
Add about 1/4 cup of sugar; mix well.
Add meat to sauce.
Simmer for about 1 hour or longer.
Serve over rice.

title: chicken simplicity
directions: Saute onion and bell pepper in butter until tender.
Add chicken strips, salt and pepper and cook until chicken is done. Add can of soup and simmer about 30 minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: mandarin orange cake
directions: Disregard cake mix instructions.
Mix cake mix, orange juice, eggs and oil well, then add mandarin oranges.
Mix again.
Bake in 3 (9-inch) layers at 350°.

title: graham cracker crust
directions: Mix and put in pie pan and bake at 300° for 10 minutes.
Cool before filling.

title: camp stew
directions: Cook chicken; debone.
Cook beef and pork; cut in small pieces.
Add potatoes, carrots and onion.
Cook until tender.
Add other ingredients.
Simmer for several hours.

title: caramel apple cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Reserve 3/4 cup apple filling. Spoon remaining filling into crust. Beat together cream cheese, sugar and vanilla until smooth. Add eggs and beat well. Pour over apple filling. Bake 35 minutes or until center is set. Cool. Mix reserved apple filling and caramel topping in a small saucepan. Heat about 1 minute. Arrange apple slices around outside edge of cheesecake. Spoon caramel sauce onto the cheesecake and spread evenly. Decorate with pecan halves around edge. Sprinkle with chopped pecans. Refrigerate until ready to serve. Makes 8 to 12 servings.

title: crustless egg custard
directions: Mix flour and sugar; add beaten eggs to this mixture.
Grease pan and dust with flour.
Pour mixture in pan and put butter on top in small pieces.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: chess cake
directions: Mix cake mix, butter and egg with hands; put into bottom of ungreased 9 x 13 pan.
Spread on bottom.
Mix remaining ingredients with hands.
Pour and smooth over bottom.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.
Top should be golden brown.

title: ginger sausage balls
directions: Combine meat, garlic, ginger and the egg yolks.
Beat egg whites until stiff and fold into the meat mixture.
Heat oil in a large, heavy saucepan.
Drop meat by teaspoonfuls into the oil a few at a time, frying about 5 minutes until cooked through.
Drain on paper towels.
Serve hot.
Makes about 40.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix, pat out on pan and bake at 350° until brown.

title: holiday brunch cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients; add apples.
Mix well.
Add eggs, one at a time; mix well.
Add oil, vanilla and water; mix.
Add nuts. Bake at 350° using a Bundt pan for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
